name: CHILDREN'S LEARNING PLACE
detail:
State agencies regulate and overseethe quality and compliance of every childcare center.  At Children's Learning Place (CLP), our staff is trained to follow systems that have been designed to not only meet state regulatory standards, but where possible, exceed them.

We monitor our staff in order to maintain the highest standards for security, safety and health as well as curriculum education and staff performance.  In addition, our directors are responsible for conducting evaluations monthly.  Routine procedures must be executed by Teachers and Directors to ensure all quality standards are met. They include a daily school check list and elaborate monthly and quarterly evaluations. There are management and staff evaluations, daily communications between the school, the director, and parents.  These evaluations are further critiqued by the executive director.

To further warranty the soundness and inclusiveness of our school, Parent Surveys are utilized in conjunction with Parent-Teacher meetings.  These surveys and meetings are studied to be sure of the effectiveness of our school and, in addition, offer parent feedback.

Definitive rules and regulations govern our school:
    We strive at all times to keep the health and contentment of our children first and foremost.
    Our schools are cleaned and maintained under the strictest of procedures.
    There are routine assessments for compliance of curriculum, procedures and the general happiness and well being of each child.
    We have consistent evaluations for maintenance and cleanliness of our schools.
    Directors and staff are obligated to fulfill their duties to the highest degree.
    We sponsor continuing education courses for our staff.
    We set the standards high and expect those standards to be respected and fulfilled.

detail:
Christopher House levels the playing field for low-income children by partnering with families to provide a continuum of high-quality schools from birth through high school and adult educational programs that create stable, self-sufficient families.

Founded in 1906 as a settlement house to help immigrants adjust to life in the U.S., Christopher House has continually evolved to meet the needs of Chicago’s low-income population over the last century. In the 1950’s, we became one of the first Head Start providers in the country. In the 1980s, in active response to a dramatic surge in teen pregnancies, we launched a teen parent program that is among the most effective in the state. In 2009, with several partners, we launched the Chicago Benchmarking Collaborative in an effort to promote better service for families across Chicago through the use of data-driven decision-making. Today, Christopher House is a network of six sites serving nearly 4,000 low income individuals throughout Chicago’s North and West Sides. In August 2013, we opened our new center and our first elementary school in the drastically underserved Belmont Cragin neighborhood.

name: HAPPY CHILD DCC A MONTESSORI SCHOOL LLC
detail:
Montessori education offers our children opportunities to develop their potential as they step out into the world as engaged, competent, responsible, and respectful citizens with an understanding and appreciation that learning is for life.

Each child is valued as a unique individual. Montessori education recognizes that children learn in different ways, and accommodates all learning styles. Students are also free to learn at their own pace, each advancing through the curriculum as he is ready, guided by the teacher and an individualized learning plan.

Beginning at an early age, Montessori students develop order, coordination, concentration, and independence. Classroom design, materials, and daily routines support the individual’s emerging “self-regulation” (ability to educate one’s self, and to think about what one is learning), toddlers through adolescents.

Students are part of a close, caring community. The multi-age classroom—typically spanning 3 years—re-creates a family structure. Older students enjoy stature as mentors and role models; younger children feel supported and gain confidence about the challenges ahead. Teachers model respect, loving kindness, and a belief in peaceful conflict resolution.

Montessori students enjoy freedom within limits. Working within parameters set by their teachers, students are active participants in deciding what their focus of learning will be. Montessorians understand that internal satisfaction drives the child’s curiosity and interest and results in joyous learning that is sustainable over a lifetime.

Students are supported in becoming active seekers of knowledge. Teachers provide environments where students have the freedom and the tools to pursue answers to their own questions.

Self-correction and self-assessment are an integral part of the Montessori classroom approach.As they mature, students learn to look critically at their work, and become adept at recognizing, correcting, and learning from their errors.

Given the freedom and support to question, to probe deeply, and to make connections, Montessori students become confident, enthusiastic, self-directed learners. They are able to think critically, work collaboratively, and act boldly—a skill set for the 21st century.

detail:
Chicago Montessori started as a one-room preschool in 2005 and now serves over one hundred students. It is the only school in the city of Chicago to be fully accredited by Association Montessori International (AMI). We are one of only two schools in the state, and one of only 18 schools in the country, to be fully accredited by AMI for ages 0 - 12. We are proud to uphold the highest of standards for Montessori education in Chicago.

AMI was started by Dr. Maria Montessori in 1929 to preserve the integrity of her life´s work with children, train teachers, and oversee the direction of schools around the world under her original guidelines. The AMI accreditation demonstrates our commitment to the highest quality Montessori education available.

name: UNIVERSITY VILLAGE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
The mission of University Village Montessori School (UVMS) is to respect and to nurture a passion for learning in the young child. We strive to give children the best possible start in life through the development and enhancement of cognitive, linguistic, motor, social-emotional, and self-help learning skills in an authentic Montessori environment.

The philosophy of UVMS comes from the work and writing of Dr. Maria Montessori. Authentic Montessori education derives its methods from the belief that all children learn by interacting with others, and the world around them. This learning comes in known stages that are realized through careful scientific observation. Therefore, it is the role of the adult to create and environment based on the stages of development, to observe children’s interactions in it and with others, and to develop a plan for continued learning based on those observations.

We only employ teachers who are fully certified and state licensed, and are specialists in different aspects of early childhood education.

name: MEHER MONTESSORI ACADEMY
detail:
Mission Statement

The form of service that a Montessori school takes has a practical value, when it is performed with an attitude of love. It recognizes the importance of the task, when it comes to dealing with the child’s nature in the prime of their development. Their carefree hearts and restless pranks reflect qualities which are inherently divine and blissfully innocent. Our mission is to see how far we can recognize and make use of the child’s potential, while nurturing these essential aspects of their nature. The teachers thus have a unique opportunity through their roles. A little patience, a little kindness, infinite understanding and sweet love, are the means by which they can express this gratitude.

name: HEAD START OF MFS DUPAGE
detail: We offer affordable & accredited educational programs for children ages 6 weeks to 5 years of age. Monday thru Friday, we provide a nurturing and diverse classroom environment for children to learn and play.

name: YMCA SAFE & SOUND STEEPLE RUN ELEMENTARY
HAPPY TIMES PRESCHOOL
detail:
We believe that birth to age six is the most important and fertile years for learning. We believe that each child is a unique individual deserving of nurturing care and respect.

Our primary goal is to provide a positive, creative learning environment in which each child may fully develop socially, emotionally, physically, and academically.

We would love to have you visit our  school!  Visiting hours flexible, please call or send us an email to schedule an appointment. Your child is welcome to attend and participate in class, if  desired.  We hope we can meet with you soon!

name: ABCD ACADEMY FOR CHILDREN II
detail:
At ABCD Academy your children get noticed, feel appreciated, and their opinions are heard and accepted.
By applying modern early childhood education methods we provide a developmentally appropriate environment in which our preschoolers learn to speak both Polish and English, acquire the skills of solving problems, making friends, and overcoming difficulties through fun and play activities.

name: JELLYBEAN LLC
detail:
Jellybean Learning Center is based on sound principles of child development.  Our goals are to give children a sense of self worth by helping them develop at their own individual pace while learning basic skills.  We want the children to feel confident and secure enough to explore and grow in a stimulating educational and social environment.

We are committed to promoting and supporting all aspects of a child’s growth in an atmosphere of respect.  Your child is an individual who is an integral member of a group, and whose uniqueness is acknowledged and appreciated by that group.  Children participate in a variety of individual and group activities designed to develop language and reading readiness skills enhancing physical, social, emotional and intellectual growth, skills and attitudes which will increase their ability to succeed in school.

name: CORNERSTONE CHRISTIAN ACADEMY - MATTOON
detail: Cornerstone Christian Academy is a state licensed child care center.  The Mattoon facility opened in January 2014 and has a licensed capacity of fifty-three children.  Two classrooms define the educational space, one for our toddlers/twos and one for our preschool program.  Our mission is to provide quality care to children and families where children receive daily thematic and Biblical academic instruction based on developmentally appropriate practice, along with a strong Christian foundation.

name: PHENOMENAL KIDS ACADEMEY, INC
detail: Phenomenal Kids Academy offers academic studies, homework assistance, dance, karate, music and voice lessons, nutrition, fitness, field trips, and Spanish. Before and After care from ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: KINDI ACADEMY
detail:
Kindi Academy is an innovative private school that serves students from 15 months to eighth grade. We began as a group of parents who aspired to provide our children with a balanced education based on rigorous academics and devotion to divinely inspired ethical values.

We have an intense and challenging mathematics, science, and language arts program. Our curriculum draws on research-based and proven "best practices" of learning, instruction, and technology.

name: INTERNATIONAL DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
International Day Care Center is inter-racial, multi-faith and multi-cultural facilitie.  The children and all staff in all of our programs come from different ethnic backgrounds. We fully support and celebrate the wonderful diversity of human family.  At International Day Care Center we strive to help every child in our care develop their own understanding and appreciation of others differences.  We support each child reaching theyr individual potential.
International Day Care center currently provides Full and Part day programs for children from 15 month thought twelve years of age.

name: KU CHAMPIONS AT ADLER PARK SCHOOL
GRAND AVENUE PRESCHOOL & DAY CARE, INC
detail: Welcome to Grand Avenue Preschools a private, nationally accredited early childhood center. Our schools have provided care and education in the western suburbs of Western Springs, LaGrange Highlands and LaGrange since 1981. Grand Avenue is a family owned and operated preschool. On-site management from the ownership group ensures that quality, is a habit, that is reinforced and managed each and every day.We hope you will spend a moment visiting our web pages and to schedule a visit to one of our schools.  Your family and children are always welcome.

name: THE CHURCH OF JESUS CHRIST TINY TOTS ELA
LITTLE KNIGHTS INC
detail: Little Knights is licensed by the state of Illinois and we provide care for children from the ages of six weeks to six years. It is our desire to provide quality care for your child and peace of mind and convenience for you all while providing a safe, loving environment for all children. We are open from 6:30am to 6:30pm, Monday through Friday, and offer part time care. ​

name: BRIGHT HORIZONS LEARNING CENTER INC
detail:
Over half of everything that we learn throughout our entire lifetime is learned in the first 5 years, and the ground-rules are set for much of the remainder…*

Bright Horizons Learning Center Inc. is just not a Childcare Center. It is a place where all children in our care are involved in educationally, stimulating, creative, quality fun programs that will equip them for their life journey. The program created for our children at Bright Horizons Learning Center Inc. ensures that all our children have the opportunity to expand their development in all areas and develop at their own individual pace.

We endeavor to work in close harmony and collaboration with all our parents in their child’s development by keeping them informed of both their child’s progress and the center’s activities.

Thank you for choosing us here at Bright Horizons Learning Center Inc. and we, as professionals, will put everything into your child’s first five years of learning.

name: TOGETHER WE LEARN INC
detail: Together We Learn is an interactive preschool program. The focus is on family and the importance of parents learning together with their children! Together We Learn offers ½ day and full day preschool program options. We also offer parent/child classes for ages 2 and up! Additional programs and tutoring are available. All classes are taught by certified teachers, use of an integrated curriculum, and always include ideas and activities for parents to share at home to foster the importance of learning together. Thank you so much for your interest in our school! We look forward to getting to know you and your child! We are always here to meet the individual needs of every child and help parents continue education at home through social, physical, intellectual and emotional development. Remember parents are a child’s first teacher! Together we play, together we grow, and together we learn!

name: EDWARDSVILLE YMCA EARLY CHILDHOOD DEV.CT
detail:
The YMCA Early Childhood Development Center is a full day daycare dedicated to enriching the lives of children from infancy to 6 years old. We promise to provide a loving, caring, honest, and respectful environment for your child to learn and grow in. Each classroom and the curriculum taught in that room is designed to meet the needs of the children in that particular age group. We will provide the children with opportunities and experiences to stimulate a child’s physical, social, intellectual and emotional development. The program is licensed and follows a constructive philosophy with open-ended art activities, science, fine and gross motor skills and hands-on discovery in an enriching environment.

The YMCA understands the sensitive needs of your child. We offer developmental age appropriate activities that ensure your child gets the most out of our YMCA Early Childhood Development Center experience.

name: CHAMPIONS EARLY LNG CTR AT WOODLAND
detail:
Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not. 

A loving, safe, fun environment with trusted adults to care for and guide your child is the foundation of all our programs. What sets us apart are our highly trained educators who deliver the thorough and engaging Early Foundations curriculum for infants through 6-year-olds. While your child is feeling cared for and having fun, our professional teachers are skillfully fostering your child's cognitive, emotional, social, and physical development to its greatest potential. Our curriculum and methods also prepare students for seamless transitions into each next level of education. Once in Kindergarten, our Extension and Enrichment Program collaborates with Woodland Primary to reinforce and extend your child's learning day, thus maximizing his/her readiness for first grade. And while loving staff and rich curriculum are essential, we also commit to ongoing teacher coaching, extensive evaluations, and continual professional development that result in the highest quality education and care for your child.

name: TURTLE EXPRESS FOX RIVER GROVE
detail:
Enrolling your child in a day care program is probably one of the most important decisions you will ever have to make. You are actually allowing other people to begin your child’s education, to care for them and protect them.  We at Turtle Express continually strive to provide the widest variety of programs and to maintain an exceptionally high level of quality care.

We intend to guide your child as they grow intellectually, physically, socially and emotionally during the year through developmentally appropriate and fun activities.  A tour of the center will show you the atmosphere that provides the children with a comfortable environment.

name: CARING 4 KIDS DAYCARE COMPANY
detail: Caring 4 Kids Daycare offers a robust environment for children to grow and learn.  Our staff has over 100 years of combined experience nurturing young minds and eagerly awaits the opportunity to do the same for your child. We are open from 6:30am until 6:00pm, offering flexibility for any schedule including before school care and after school care.  Preschool and Kindergarten children are learning and developing at an astounding rate around this age. Caring 4 Kids Daycare remains on the cutting edge of early childhood education by closely monitoring and updating our educational programs. Our committed staff also regularly attend continuing education in early childhood education – Making Caring 4 Kids Daycare a leading daycare provider for Frankfort, IL.

name: BUTTONS & BOWS COOP NURS I
detail: We are excited to share information about Buttons and Bows with you as we know that choosing the right preschool is a difficult and important decision. We are very proud of our 53 year history as a not for profit, DCFS liscensed preschool in Elmhurst. We offer Two, Three, and Four Year Old Classes for children. Each of our classes strives to enrich the lives of the children through age appropriate activities. Our curriculum promotes social interactions and creative play along with independent skill development. Pre-reading and phonetic skills and kindergarten readiness are a focus in our four-year-old classes. We offer many activities, such as Mom’s Night, Dad’s Night, Morning with Santa, Thanksgiving Feasts, and a Children’s Art Gallery that promote family involvement.

WALTER HAMMOND DAY CARE, INC.
detail: We are a daycare center- with a staff of well educated teachers.

name: LAURETTA M ENO CHILD CARE CENTER
detail: Blessing Lauretta M. Eno Child Care educators are caring professionals dedicated to meeting each child's individual needs by providing developmentally appropriate activities in a quality environment that is safe and nurturing.  We serve the whole child in an atmosphere of compassion and respect.  We strive for continuous improvement through cooperation and partnerships with families. The Center is accredited by the National Accreditation Commission for Early Care and Education Programs (NAC) and holds Star Level 3 status under the State of Illinois' Child Care Quality Rating System (QRS).

Head Start services are offered to families with children ages 3 and 4 in Brown, Cass, Hancock, McDonough, Pike, Schuyler, Scott, and rural Adams Counties.

EARLY LEARNING
detail: Early Learning is a private center for child care and education for children aged 15 months through six. Located conveniently near the intersection of Prospect and Kirby Avenues in Champaign, Illinois, we've been offering child-initiated learning activities in a homelike, caring environment since 1976.

name: BUNDLES OF JOY OF CHAMPAIGN LEARNING CTR
LA PETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

name: HAPPI TIME ON AVONDALE
detail:
At Happi-Time Day Care we want your family to know that your child is not only safe and happy, but also learning and exploring. Your child will enjoy activities that build their skills to provide them with a step up into the next stage of their development.  

We provide loving and nurturing infant care for your youngest child while they enjoy activities such as tummy time exercise, along with plenty of hugs and cuddling. Your growing toddler will explore the world as they create finger paint masterpieces and build skyscrapers out of blocks. Your ever-excited preschool child will prepare for school through a curriculum that focuses largely on literature and science based activities. For your oldest child, our school age program provides activities for relaxation afterschool, space and time for homework, and a summer camp that also includes a summer reading program.

7:00 AM to 5:30 PM

name: FIRST SCHOOL, INC.
detail:
At First School we have developed an environment where your child is an independent learner utilizing the first years of life when vital learning occurs at it's best and fullest. Reading is the key to independent learning and therefore we have developed a program that guides your child through steps enabling him or her to become an early reader. 

Children who learn to read before elementary school are better learners reading at their own individual pace and at First School we provide your child with that opportunity. Our classes are structured to allow the individual child to progress at his/her own rate and level and each of our classes includes an early education curriculum that develops social skills side by side with his/her academic knowledge.

The concepts and experiences in our program are sequential and developmental. Our curriculum has a Montessori basis which utilizes hands-on activities and equipment. The language program we use is phonetic as well as visual because some children learn best aurally while others do visually. 

We have incorporated a computer program and a four station light tracing table to reinforce the hands-on activities. Your child will learn language, math, science, art, music, and fine and gross motor skills while developing important social and self-help skills. First School is an exciting experience fostering a joy for learning now and all through your child's life.

name: HUGS & BUGS
detail: Our goals at Hugs & Bugs, Inc. are to meet each child's needs.  Our center is designed to help children grow, develop, and explore their world.  Our center encourages a variety of activities in a loving and caring environment.  We strive to give each child a safe and secure environment.

name: AMER LUTH CH CHRISTIAN NUR SCH & DAYCARE
CHAMPAIGN COUNTY HEAD START
detail:
In 2003, the Rantoul Head Start program moved to a renovated building on the former Air Force base on Illinois Route 45. Architects designed a child and family-friendly facility serving families living or working in Rantoul and surrounding rural areas. In addition to eight classrooms, the building has a multi-purpose room, a kitchen, offices, a conference room and a library. The center has a playground designed for infants and toddlers as well as a playground for children 3 to 5-years-old.

The program offers full-day, school-day and part-day classes for children 3 to 5 years of age. For children under 3-years-old, full-day and 3 1/2 hour sessions are available. Transportation is provided for the preschoolers enrolled in school-day and part-day classes. All meals are prepared at the center.

Head Start collaborates with the Spectrum Early Childhood program to provide dual enrollment for children with a diagnosed disability. For children with a disability who are not dually enrolled with Spectrum, Champaign County Head Start/Early Head Start (CCHS) contracts with individual therapist to provide on-site therapy. CCHS coordinates with Child and Family Connections to bring therapy services on-site to any children younger than 3-years-old who have a delay or disability.

name: PRINCE OF PEACE COMM EARLY LEARNING CTR
CHILDREN'S CENTER DAY CARE
detail: Children's Center Day Care is a non-denominational, not for profit day care center sponsored by the Urbana First United Methodist Church.  We are conveniently located in downtown Urbana near Lincoln Square Village, the Urbana Free Library, and the MTD bus routes. Children's Center proudly participates in the Quality Rating System which surpasses DCFS regulations.  We are the recipiant of two stars for our program as well as our teaching staff.

name: CHILD DEVELOPMENT LABORATORY
detail:
The missions of the CDL parallel the three-part Teaching, Research, and Service missions of the University of Illinois. As a Laboratory School, we support these academic missions by:
    Facilitating student observations of children
    Allowing select research/teaching projects to occur at the school
    Serving as a center for teacher training

name: BRADLEY LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Bradley Learning Center recognizes and respects the uniqueness of each child. Established in 1970, the center's primary function is to foster a love of learning in each child. Our curriculum skillfully weaves artistic and practical disciplines into everyday academics. Students learn to follow their curiosity, to think creatively, and to work both independently and cooperatively with others.
At Bradley Learning Center we celebrate diversity and strive to instill integrity, compassion, and confidence in each child. We give each child support and encouragement to become his or her own unique self.

name: CHAMPAIGN CO. HEAD START-CHAMPAIGN WEST
detail: The Brookens Administrative Center is the central office for the Champaign County Head Start / Early Head Start program. Many years ago, this building was used to serve Junior High School students within Unit 116's Brookens Junior High School, but now serves the community in another way. Several agencies including Urbana Park District, Senior Services, Planning and Zoning, Auditors Office, Mental Health Board, Circuit Clerk and County Board rent office space in order to meet the community’s needs.

name: LIGHTHOUSE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Lighthouse Learning Center provides educational programs to pre-school and school-aged children from 6 weeks to 13 years. We are locally owned and operated Christian-based learning center serving the Taylorville, IL area. We offer our students a homey classroom, patient and licensed teachers, and a friendly staff.

Our goal is to not only educate young minds with academics that will prepare them for school, but we also instill good morals and social skills. Lighthouse Learning Center offers students an educational, fun, and nurturing educational experience in a safe atmosphere.

name: HOMEWORK & HANGOUT
detail: Homework and Hangout is an after school program that offers snacks, homework help and a safe place for school age kids to play.

name: IMMANUEL LUTHERAN EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail:
We believe that the Chrstian education and care of children is a cooperative effort that includes parents, children, teachers, and congregational members as partners with families. Immanuel Lutheran Church and its Early Childhood ministry are involved in caring for children and providing early education through activities and experiences that help develop skills necessary for school and for a Christ-centered life.

Immanuel provides a Christian atmosphere for children as young as two, and utilizes songs, prayers, and daily activities centering around the love of Jesus. The classroom experiences will help fulfill spiritual, cognitive, physical, emotional, and social needs of the children, and learning occurs through individualized, small and large group activities.

name: STEPPING STONES CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Stepping Stones Children's Center strives to provide the kind of quality care and educational environment that parents have come to expect for their children.  Continuing education for staff and administration, program improvements that follow the guidelines for developmentally appropriate practices and a strong focus on parent/center communication, are key components in our program. 

We are pleased that you and your child are considering our program at STEPPING STONES CHILDREN’S CENTER.  We consider it a privilege to share in your child’s growth and development.  We trust the time your child spends at the center will provide many worthwhile and enjoyable experiences.

If you have further questions concerning what we can offer to meet your child’s and your family’s individual needs, please call or stop by.  We look forward to speaking with you we and hope this will be the first step to a long, happy relationship.

name: FAMILY & CONSUMER SCIENCES CHILD DEV LAB
THE LITTLE SCHOOL HOUSE
detail:
Little School House Vision and Goals:
To develop socially, emotionally, physically, and cognitively. To develop problem solving and conflict resolution skills.

How do we plan on reaching these goals?
Use developmentally appropriate practices to provide a safe, supportive, and nurturing environment where children develop at their own rate in the four areas of development described above. Support the relationship between children, their families, and the staff. Provide a learning environment that supposets children to develop skills necessary to construct their own knowledge and prepare them for their next school environment.

name: LITTLE FOOTSTEPS ACADEMY INC
detail:
Our mission is to offer a home-like, educational environment to the children of working parents during working hours, thereby partnering in the parenting process.  The children shall be made to feel as if the daycare were their home away from home in a sanitary, secure, healthy, caring family-style environment.

Our mission is also to service both the child and parent according to child and parent’s individual needs.

name: LITTLE LEARNERS EDUCATIONAL CENTER INC
detail:
Little Learners Educational Center is committed to providing an environment of trust and respect between the Little Learners family and your family. We take pride in the highest quality curriculum that enhances the emotional, physical, social, and cognitive development for each
child.

The focus of Little Learners  Educational Center is to develop a nurturing environment and challenging curriculum that promotes development and focuses on early childhood learning. Many studies suggest that high-quality early learning programs improve the likelihood of
success throughout a person’s life. Here at Little Learners children will receive an excellent educational foundation that will serve as a stepping-stone for their formal education.

name: A MOTHER'S TOUCH
detail:
Thank you for considering A Mother’s Touch for the care and education of your child. I began A Mother’s Touch in 1994 in order to fill an important need within our community. After the birth of my third daughter, I was looking for an early childhood center that was warm and nurturing, while providing rich educational experiences. When I was not satisfied with my options, I decided to start my own center.

I created A Mother’s Touch as a nurturing place where babies are rocked and cuddled, toddlers are free to explore, preschoolers paint, laugh and make lasting friendships, and all children are respected, listened to and valued.

Early childhood education is my passion, and your child is my priority. I invite you to join me on this wonderful journey of childhood

name: RED WAGON CHILD CARE CENTER INC
detail: Welcome to the Red Wagon Child Care Center. We have been family owned and directed at the same location since 1986. Our center provides year-round care for children six weeks through six years old. We strive to provide a safe, healthy, and stimulating environment for children to grow and develop in. Our dedicated, caring staff are experienced, degreed, and trained in Early Childhood Education and CPR/First-Aid. Staff members regularly continue their education and attend workshops and seminars throughout the year.
business hours: Monday through Friday, 6:45 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: SALEM METHODIST PRESCHOOL
detail:
We believe each child is a unique individual, created in God's own image. We recognize the importance of prayer in relation to everyday life and the need to instill solid Christian values in young children. Our staff will encourage your child to express these values.

We desire that your child will learn that he/she is a special part of God's creation and that we all need to live in harmony with many people of different races and beliefs. We will provide an opportunity for your child to grow cognitively, socially, spiritually, emotionally, and physically.

It is our purpose to prepare your child with the necessary skills needed to grow in these areas and to relate to others in all areas of life, beginning with these formative years!

name: CHILDRENS LEARNING CENTER II
detail:
Children's Learning Center strives to provide the highest quality educational programs for children from 18 months old to 12 years old. Our programs were created to encourage our children to expand their physical, cognitive, emotional and social skills.

Thank you for visiting our new Internet site. As an up-to-date business, we want to give you the opportunity to stay in touch with our company and our offers. A new content management system will enable us to always keep you up to date.

At present, our web site is still under construction. We are making an effort to present you with our entire spectrum of offers as soon as possible. At this point we can provide you with information regarding your child's daycare needs. Please check this site later, as it will offer much more information.

If you are not familiar with our company and your first contact with us is online: We would be pleased to hear from you! Please let us know what your needs and questions are, we will be more than happy to help.

name: TRAIN UP A CHILD CHRISTIAN ACADEMY
detail:
Our Mission
Train Up A Child Christian Academy, a private Christ-centered childcare facility, providing a warm exciting and nurturing early childhood program that will enhance their personal growth as well as their academic education and Christian values for each child to grow physically, emotionally, intellectually, socially, and spiritually.   We believe and follow the command of Jesus to train children in the way they should go and when old they will not depart from the truth of Jesus Christ and become successful life long learners.
business hours: 6:00 a.m. to  6:00 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: LITTLE ACHIEVERS CHILD CARE DEVELOP CTR
HAPPY DAYS CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
Happy Days Child Development Center is where your child can gain the tools needed to reach their potential. We take childhood education very seriously and are committed to helping your child succeed while having fun at the same time. By maintaining small class sizes, we ensure your child gets the individualized attention they deserve.


We are passionate about education and providing your Child with the tools to be successful in life. Our philosophy is to focus on the needs of the individual child by providing a stimulating atmosphere for learning along with a secure loving environment.


We offer full or part-time care at an affordable price for children 6 weeks to 12 years of age and have 3 locations to serve you in the Chicago Land Area – Berwyn, Cicero, and South Holland. Call to Schedule a Tour Today, we want to be your partner in nurturing your child’s dreams!

We offer full-day and half-day educational child care, preschool, pre-kindergarten, kindergarten, and before-and-after school care facility.

Happy Days Child Development Center is OPEN ALL YEAR AROUND to meet the schedules of working parents. We are conveniently located in Berwyn, Cicero, and South Holland.

We would like to work together with you to assist and watch your child grow and thrive.

name: ORCHARD STREET CHRISTIAN CHURCH CHILD DC
BLUE CAP SUNSHINE KIDS INF/PARENT CTR
detail: Blue Cap's Sunshine Kids Child Care staff provide children with a safe, secure, and loving environment. It is a place where children come together to learn, play and grow socially, emotionally and physically into joyful and caring adults. Our goal is to help each child become independent, self-confident and eager to learn. This is best achieved by allowing children to learn at their own pace and in ways that are best suited for them. Moral support and encouragement for their efforts will be given along the way. Our curriculum identifies goals in the following areas of development: independent living skills, social, emotional, physical and language.

name: TEDDY BEAR DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
Your children deserve the very best in child care. Bring them to a warm, inviting environment that will stimulate their minds and provide a place to grow, learn and play.

Teddy Bear Day Care has six day care centers serving Chicago’s Southwest neigborhoods. We offer programs for children aged 6 weeks to 12 years including Kindergarten, Pre-kindergarten, Head Start and our Little Bear infant and toddler care and Big Bear Day Camp camp programs. Our staff is qualified and dedicated and we care for over five hundred children annually. We provide computers in every classroom, quality nourishing meals including hot lunches and nutritious snacks and have outdoor play areas.

We are proud to be members of the PSO-Illinois’ Child Care Association, ensuring the quality of our facility and caregivers. Our Pre-K and Kindergarten programs are accredited by the state of Illinois. Teddy Bear Day Care Centers are proud partners with Head Start.

Contact us today to arrange a tour of our award-winning educational and computer-ready facilities and sit down with us to discuss how we can best serve the needs of your child and help them get a great start on their future!

name: PRECIOUS HEART DAY CARE CENTER
detail: Are looking for a day care center? Visit Precious Heart Day Care Center in Broadview, IL. We have certified and state licensed teachers. We accept children ages 6 weeks to 12 years. We look forward to hearing from you.

name: MINI ACADEMY
detail: MINI  ACADEMY  can  be your  child's   home  away.  We  want  you be  able  to carry out  your  daily activities, confident in  the knowledge  that   your  child is  receiving  the  very  best  in  care  education. Studies  show that  children  who  have positive,  productive   experiences  in  child  care  are  better  prepared  socially and academically  at  school,  which  means  they  have a  better chance  for  educational success.  The  key, however is  the level  of  quality that  a child care  setting  offers. High  quality  is  no  longer  a  plus,  it  is -must.  We  believe  that  a  child's lifelong  attitude  toward  learning  can  be  enhanced  by  positive  early experiences to  child's  development.

detail:
Children's Home Center is a fully licensed daycare facility located in the Calumet City, Illinois area. We come highly recommended with our excellent preschool curriculum where we treat all the children like they are own. Our teaching is geared towards making learning fun. Your children will love our professional, caring workers and our fun activities that are developed for your child’s learning. You and your child will experience an extremely helpful and fun daycare environment with Children's Home Center; you won’t be disappointed you choose us!                

At Children's Home Center we understand that the child care facility you chose for your child to attend is a very important decision and we want you to know that we have a high rated facility that can provide many references. Our friendly, professional, caring staff all love children and enjoy teaching and taking care of them.

This daycare is committed to following basic principles of honesty, good judgement, and fairness. We incorporate those priciples into everyday settings. We provide an environment with a definite learning program that concentrates on active learning and problem solving with a high degree of child/adult interaction as well as child/child interactions. We the child's mind and freedom, while keeping them within the bounds of authority. We provide a classroom atmosphere that is friendly, encourages learning, and is conducive to building character. We believe our daycare program will provide our students with a foundation that will assist them in becoming lifelong learners and to develop into productive citizens.

detail:
Our mission is to create innovative child care programs that help infants and young children reach their full potential. We honor each child and family needs. Jennifer's Kids Learning Center does not discriminate on the bases of race, color, national origin, religion, or socio-economic status.

name: A-KARRASEL INFANT & TODDLR INC
detail:
A-Karrasel is a Childcare Center that focuses on the development of the whole child. We strive to create warm classrooms where the care and education for each child is of the utmost importance.

During the first five years of life, children need constant attention and stimulation to promote their growth. Here at A-Karrasel, their days are filled with Music, Books, Art Projects, Sensory and Science Exploration, Math Lessons, Small and Large Motor Stimulation and Social Interaction. Our goal is to help each child during these early years by giving them the essentials they need to grow into a questioning knowledgeable, self-confident individual.

name: DIST.#65 SCH.AGE CHILD CARE WILLARD SCH.
EVANSTON HOSPITAL CORP. CHILD DEV. C.
DIST. 65 SCHOOL-AGE C C LINCOLNWOOD SCH
detail:
A timeline and history of the Evanston School District 65 Early Childhood and Community Based Programs:

    1965 Evanston Head Start opens at Foster Center under the directorship of Joseph E. Hill.  Program soon expanded to Noyes and Washington Schools.  The program started as a summer program.
    1971 A committee was formed to establish the 4C's (Community Coordinated Child Care) now known as the Child Care Network of Evanston.
    1972 The 4C's collaborated with School District 65 to offer after-school child care.  After-school care was offered in five elementary schools.
    1973-1974 A second Head Start, operated by Evanston CEDA Neighbors at Work, merged with District 65's Head Start program, providing services for an additional 30 children.
    1974 District 65 initiated an after-kindergarten care program for A.M. students.  Enrolled students were bused to two schools.
    1976 The Early Childhood Center opened at Miller School.  This program was the dream of Superintendent Joseph E. Hill.  The school hosted five programs: Head Start, after-kindergarten/child care program, Community Child Care, Services for Pre-Primary Age Children (SPPAC), and Family Focus.
    1979 The Early Childhood Center moved to Kingsley Elementary School with the exception of the after-kindergarten program.  The early childhood program remained at Kingsley until 1990.
    1982 Then Superintendent, Dr. Robert Campbell, expanded the after-school program to include before school programming and made it available at all 12 schools.  The program was one of the first to operate within a public school system in Illinois.
    1990 The program split up with Head Start and Community Child Care moved to Timber Ridge School, SPPAC moved to Park School, Family Focus moved briefly to Oakton School and then to a space in the strip mall at Dempster and Dodge (Family Focus/Our Place - Teen program)
    1995 Head Start and Child Care program moved to Haven Middle School
    2002 Superintendent, Hardy Murphy, Ph.D., dedicates new education center for early childhood programs (and district administrative offices).  District 65's Head Start, Community Preschool/Child Care program, Early Adventures (state pre-k), Pre-Primary diagnostic program (SPPAC) and the Family Center are housed at the Joseph E. Hill Education Center.

    1990 The program split up with Head Start and Community Child Care moved to Timber Ridge School, SPPAC moved to Park School, Family Focus moved briefly to Oakton School and then to a space in the strip mall at Dempster and Dodge (Family Focus/Our Place - Teen program)
    1995 Head Start and Child Care program moved to Haven Middle School
    2002 Superintendent, Hardy Murphy, Ph.D., dedicates new education center for early childhood programs (and district administrative offices).  District 65's Head Start, Community Preschool/Child Care program, Early Adventures (state pre-k), Pre-Primary diagnostic program (SPPAC) and the Family Center are housed at the Joseph E. Hill Education Center.

name: MCGAW YMCA CHILD CARE CENTER
detail:
At the Y, we believe the values and skills learned early on are vital building blocks for quality of life and future success. That’s why our infant/toddler, preschool, and school age programs are staffed with teachers who understand the cognitive, physical and social development of kids.

We respect and nurture your child’s need to feel connected and supported in trying new things. At our center, babies develop trust and security, preschoolers experience early literacy and learn about their environment, and school-age kids make friends, learn new skills, and receive homework assistance. We’re committed to building confident kids today and bright futures tomorrow.

name: CHIARAVALLE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
Chiaravalle Montessori School provides families with a quality child-centered education based on the philosophy and methods of Maria Montessori.

Chiaravalle strives to provide a respectful, cooperative, diverse environment in which children may develop the full range of their abilities.

name: SCHOOL FOR LITTLE CHIDLREN OF EVANSTON
detail:
School for Little Children is a NAEYC-accredited, part-time preschool located in the heart of downtown Evanston. For almost 80 years, SLC has provided a high-quality, play-based education for young children ages 2 through 5 years.

Through the use of child-centered activities, SLC offers an approved curriculum based on current early learning standards and NAEYC accredited criteria, which encourages the social, cognitive, language and motor development of children. Well known in the Evanston community, SLC boasts high teacher/child ratios in all of its classes and promotes a strong community among our families.

name: TEEN BABY NURSERY
detail: Teen Baby Nursery (TBN) is a NAEYC Accredited, full-day child care and early education program with a capacity for 16 children whose parents attend Evanston Township High School. Specializing in infant and toddler care for children of teenage parents, Teen Baby Nursery is committed to ensuring that children enter school ready to learn.

name: CHILDTIME/ST. FRANCIS HOSPITAL
detail: We help children learn to love their world. At Childtime, your child gets what he or she needs to develop their best mind, their love of learning, their personality, their bright future. We provide nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: TODDLER TOWN
detail:
What if all those swipes, taps, and clicks could help your preschooler build the skills necessary for success in school?
We have the way! Through our exclusive partnership with ABCmouse.com, we can offer your family access to award-winning content, online books and interactive activities that are both entertaining AND educational. We encourage all parents to get actively involved in your child’s education. Though children learn many of the key foundational literacy skills in school, repetition and practice at home reinforces those skills. Remember, you can become your child’s most influential teacher. The actions, conversations and connections you have at home are vitally important to their success. Read to your child. Teach him/her about responsible and safe screen time as they navigate online. Help them build confidence, and encourage their curiosity and desire to discover more. When you are excited about learning, they will be too!

name: HAVEN FOR TOTS
detail:
On behalf of the Haven for Tots Child Development Center staff, board members, and the entire congregation of United By Faith Lutheran Church, we would like to thank you for the opportunity of caring for your precious child. It is the special ministry of all of us to provide your child with a safe, healthy environment in which to grow and develop in every way. We have chosen our special ministry of child day care for the benefit of our community, with a commitment of providing a Christian centered environment filled with experiences to enrich every aspect of your child's life and to serve every family's needs.

As a Lutheran Church of Christ, we would also like to invite you to share, at any time, your presence with us during Sunday School, Bible study, worship services or any of our other activities. So, along with the opportunity to guide your young child, we may also share many other close experiences.

name: FLOSSMOOR COMM UNITY CHURCH WEEKDAY PS
detail: The Weekday Preschool at Flossmoor Community Church is dedicated to providing an opportunity for your child to grow and develop in a nurturing, educational environment. Guided by early childhood education professionals, each child is encouraged to explore and discover the joy of learning. Realizing one's own unique potential is a lifelong goal and the foundation is laid in the preschool years. Yet, since 1953, FCC Weekday Preschool has believed that childhood is much more than preparing for the future--it's a time to be valued simply for it's own delight.

name: FOREST PARK CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail: The Forest Park Montessori Child Development Center was founded in 1965. It was initially based in Oak Park, Illinois as the Oak Park Montessori Child Development Center. The school moved to its current location in Forest Park, Illinois and changed its name in the late sixties.  Goals include love of learning, self-motivation, increased self-esteem, and concentration.  To achieve these goals at Forest Park Montessori, we have to create a place where children can be themselves in an atmosphere of freedom and responsibility. Parents are brought into this atmosphere as much as possible through a host of interesting activities. Often friendships made in this “family” will last a lifetime. Parents and children are invited to join us in this educational adventure. The educational policies of the school are the responsibilities of the Educational Director, Marian Zeidman. It is her task to give guidance and inspiration to the faculty. She is ready to answer parent inquiries and welcomes the many visitors who are interested in our programs and wish to observe the classes in action.

name: HOWARD MOHR COMMUNITY CENTER
detail: The Howard Mohr Community Center, named for the late State Senator and Forest Park Mayor, is owned and operated by the Village. The Community Center provides activities for all Village residents while paying special attention to young children and seniors. Support services include a food pantry for temporary emergency relief for residents and Meals on Wheels for residents of any age based on a needs assessment. The Community Center is home base for many senior activities with day trips scheduled out of the Center every week.

name: KANGAROO KORNER DAY CARE CENTER
detail: Kangaroo Korner is a state licensed learning center in Forest Park, IL offering affordable, high-quality programs for children ages 15 months to 8 years. We provide experiences that enrich and enhance each child's cognitive, language, social, emotional, and creative development. Within our program's daily schedule, each child has opportunities to create, explore the environment, learn problem solving and personal interaction skills, and learn concepts through first-hand experiences. Our staff serves as positive role-models, and provides care that is supportive, nurturing, warm, and responsive to each child's individual needs.

It is our belief that in such an environment your child may grow as an individual with a positiive self-concept and an ability to relate to others.

detail: Welcome to Poko Loko Early Learning Center. We specialize in infant and toddler daycare, preschool through kindergarten education, and have full day and half day programs available. We have three locations in the Northern Chicago Suburbs: Glenview, Libertyville, and Wheeling. Our certified staff is trained in quality, individualized child care, and education for all children. Our curriculum is theme based and includes a variety of topics, thus helping to ensure a well-rounded child ready to enter grade school.

name: CREME DE LA CREME GLENVIEW INC
detail:
Crème's passion for child development has spawned research to enhance the learning experience in young minds. In fact, Crème has been bringing out the greatness within children since 1980, earning awards for the best daycare and the best childcare centers throughout Colorado, Georgia, Illinois, Kansas, New Jersey, Ohio, Texas, and Virginia.

Crème's exceptional early learning programs have been featured in both national and local media such as: CBS Evening News, NBC Nightly News, Good Morning America, U.S. News & World Reports, Education Week, The Washington Post, The Chicago Tribune, The Denver Post, The Kansas City Star, The Chicago Sun Times, and Chicago Tribune.

THORNTON TWSP H.S.DIST 205 INFANT CARE
detail: Welcome to the Thornton Township District 205 Infant Care Center.  We are a licensed daycare with certified staff from District 205.  The Infant Care Center was established over 25 years ago to serve infants and toddlers of teen parents who attend Thornton, Thornridge, or Thornwood that are in need of childcare service while attending high school.  Children six weeks to four years of age may be enrolled in the Infant Care Center.  Transportation is available for teen parents and their children.  Specially equipped buses will transport the students to and from the Infant Care Center to their home   school. Trained staff screen the children twice a year in order to identify and diagnose children with developmental delays. Prevention/intervention techniques are shared with parents during the screening.  Our program is designed to help children develop a positive self-image within an environment that encourages physical, social, emotional, and intellectual growth.

name: HILLSIDE MONTESSORI SCHOOL, INC
detail:
Hillside Montessori School has been serving Hillside and the surrounding areas since 1997. We provide education and care for children ages six weeks to six years old. Our school consists of nine classrooms; Two Infant rooms, two toddler rooms, two 2 year old rooms and 3 three to six year old rooms. We offer a variety of programs including two or three day a week schedules and preschool programs. Our summer program is a full time summer camp orientated program which serves all ages up to age twelve. We have special events, complete studies on world issues and work with many arts and crafts.
 
Each Montessori classroom, from birth through kindergarten operates on the same principal of freedom within limits. Children can work alone or with others integrating individual choice and group activities. Through daily observation the teacher decides what activities and materials to introduce into the classroom. The goal is to encourage active, self-directed learning, and strike a balance of individual mastery. We believe in making learning fun and not a forced activity.
 
Hillside Montessori School is a beautiful environment for the children to grow and develop. We encourage you to stop by today so you can see for yourself all of the enriching programs we have to offer.

detail: Our goal is to nurture self-esteem and independence and to set the stage for future learning through a positive first experience at school. Curricular elements should be scientifically proven to be appropriate and successful for children of this age. Children’s social development is emphasized through play and the companionship of their peers. Learning should be enjoyable, and emphasize hands-on experiences, in a bright, open, well-equipped classroom. Our programs are designed to maximize your child’s learning potential, while fostering their intersocial skills and behaviors. Our curriculum is designed to meet the total needs of the child by coordinating activities and experiences at the child’s pace, allowing space, equipment and movement necessary for overall early childhood development. Our curriculum also provides a balance between quiet and active periods, between academic awareness and comfortable relaxation, always permitting the joy of self-discovery and the pleasure of social interaction.

detail:
Tiny Town Inc. offers the highest quality childcare services in the Lansing and surrounding areas. Since 1982, we have provided superior child care service to our customers and have taken good care of their children while they work. With over 35 years of experience, our commitment to excellence has earned us the reputation as the best childcare choice in the area.

Tiny Town is licensed by DCFS for children ages 3-11.

Our purpose at Tiny Town, Inc., is to provide a safe, loving and caring atmosphere for your children. Opportunities are provided for your children to experiment and create, in both active and quiet play, with experiences that develop confidence, a sense of worth and a feeling of success. In all opportunities your children will be allowed to freely create and develop their own individual personalities.

name: CHILDREN'S CARE & DEVEL. CENTER, INC.
detail: Welcome to Children's Care & Development Center, a licensed, NAEYC accredited early childhood program!       Our mission is to provide a safe, loving environment designed to engage your child and support their cognitive, physical, and social emotional growth. Our philosophy follows developmentally appropriate practices as prescribed by NAEYC (National Association for the Education of Young Children).   Research confirms that planned activities that provide hands-on learning, collaborative play and exploration provide meaningful learning experiences for young children. Our curriculum is planned by teachers degreed in Early Childhood Education.  Topics of study are implemented through project work which meet Illinois Early Learning Standards and Objectives.  Through guided exploration, children discover different ways to obtain answers to their questions.  We build a strong foundation for young children to become life-long learners. Our teachers act as facilitators, preparing the environment, modeling appropriate behavior, and helping young children learn self-control.  Our teachers praise good behavior,  acknowledge feelings, redirect and set clear limits when necessary.  Children learn how to problem solve, negotiate and share with others.   We teach children to respect themselves, others, and their surroundings. Our teachers recognize parents as their child's first teachers.  We establish strong partnerships with parents, through parent notes, newsletters, conferences, curriculum nights, and family events.  Through a combination of low child-staff ratios and close teacher interaction, optimum growth and development can take place.  Parents are welcome to stop in at any time throughout the day.

name: THE CHILDREN'S PLACE LEARNING CENTER INC
LOVE "N" LEARN DAY CARE CASTLE, INC.
COMMUNITY MENNONITE EARLY LEARNING CTR
detail:
Community Mennonite Early Learning Center (CMELC) is concerned with the development of children. We wish to aid children in growing, not just physically but also intellectually, socially, and emotionally. In working with children and their familes, we help to foster trust, autonomy, initiative, and responsibility - all parts of a healthy personality. Children will be exposed to their world through socialization, respect, and co-operation.

CMELC does not replace the home - it complements it. We provide experiences to enrich children's lives through play. Our staff is well-educated, trained in early childhood practices, and are carefully chosen to offer the best early educational experiences as well as love and support for you and your child.
business hours: 6:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.; Monday through Friday

name: KLC DBA CHAMPIONS MARYA YATES
detail:
Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not. 

A loving, safe, fun environment with trusted adults to care for and guide your child is the foundation of all our programs. What sets us apart are our highly trained educators who deliver the thorough and engaging Early Foundations curriculum for infants through 6-year-olds. While your child is feeling cared for and having fun, our professional teachers are skillfully fostering your child's cognitive, emotional, social, and physical development to its greatest potential. Our curriculum and methods also prepare students for seamless transitions into each next level of education. Once in Kindergarten, our Extension and Enrichment Program collaborates with Woodland Primary to reinforce and extend your child's learning day, thus maximizing his/her readiness for first grade. And while loving staff and rich curriculum are essential, we also commit to ongoing teacher coaching, extensive evaluations, and continual professional development that result in the highest quality education and care for your child.

detail:
The mission of St. Paul Lutheran Preschool is to provide a Christ-centered, education establishment by helping chidren and their families:

    To develop positive attitudes about themselves, their family, and friends by discovering and learning more about the many gifts, talents and abilities that God has provided.
    To increase their knowledge about and participation in the Church's liturgical seasons of Advent, Christmas, Lent and Easter.
    To increase their knowledge about God and friendship with Jesus.
    To increase their knowledge and practice of Christian actions toward others such as taking turns, listening, helping, waiting, caring, sharing, loving and thanking others.
    To prepare for Kindergarten through pre-reading, writing, rhyming, math and language development.

Step By Step has been taking care of children throughout the Midlothian, IL area for many years. We provide the most caring and attentive child care services and know that each day your child visits us, you’ll both feel completely at ease!

We specialize in assisting childhood development and truly care about the well-being and education of the children we supervise. We are always happy to show your child the attention and care he or she deserves and will always help them develop and learn new skills.

Our programs are designed to maximize your child's learning potential, while fostering their intersocial skills and behaviors. We have an extremely high return rate, with most of our first-year children returning the following year. And each one of our 7 centers has at least one teacher on staff who themselves were once a Sandbox student!

Sandbox graduates still keep in touch, so we have seen our children grow to become intelligent, confident, and productive adults, many landing successful careers. Visit us today and see what sets us apart

detail: When it comes to your kids, nothing less than the highest standards will do. Since 1962, Papoose has provided a safe environment for your child to explore his or her full potential. If you're looking for a daycare center that meets these stringent demands, look no further!

name: THE SANDBOX
detail:
The Sandbox in Oak Lawn is a collaborative effort with CHSD 218 to provide an on-site childcare for the benefit of District staff and employees.  As such, it is closed to the public.

This center has provided services for the District employees for eleven years.  It’s Director is Ms. Laura Cunningham.  Laura is an Illinois Credentialed Director with a degree in Early Childhood. Her background includes many years of working in the Early Childhood classroom.

We pride ourselves in the nurturing care we provide the children, the family friendly atmosphere, and our excellent staff.

Creative, exciting and educational activities are planned daily.   We invite all employees of District 218 to call us for quality care for their children ages six weeks to five years.

name: HEPHZIBAH-MANN DAY CARE PROGRAM
detail:
Children benefit immeasurably from high-quality day care programming - developing greater self-confidence, improved physical and social skills, increased respect for others, and enhanced cognitive and learning skills.

Since 1974, Hephzibah has provided quality day care for children whose parents are working, going to school, or completing career training. Our nationally recognized, award-winning Day Care Program offers a nurturing, enriching, and dynamic day care experience for Oak Park children from kindergarten to fifth grade. These children attend Hephzibah Day Care after school, on school holidays, and full time during the summer months.

Hephzibah currently operates eight day care programs at the Oak Park elementary schools in cooperation with the school district. Our goal is to provide a day care experience that will help children achieve their full social, emotional, and intellectual potential. Day Care activities are designed to promote the well being of children by fostering the development of a wide variety of skills, as well as social competence and a positive self-image. Children gain experience in areas such as arts and crafts, group games, sports activities such as swimming and ice skating, movement and music, camps, and field trips.

Each year, our Day Care program serves more than 600 school-aged children from diverse socioeconomic backgrounds. Our day care fees are assessed on a sliding scale and offset by financial aid when necessary to ensure that every family in our community has access to high-quality day care - regardless of income - and that children from low-income families have the same growth opportunities as their peers.

name: THE SANDBOX PRE-SCHOOL & KINDERGARTEN
detail:
Sandbox Preschool and Daycare has excelled in early childhood development, care and education in the southwest suburbs of Homer Glen, Midlothian, Palos Heights, Oak Lawn, and Orland Park for over 42 years! Our licensed and qualified staff has the patience and experience that has helped us establish our reputation for excellence.

Our programs are designed to maximize your child's learning potential, while fostering their intersocial skills and behaviors. Our curriculum is designed to meet the total needs of the child by coordinating activities and experiences at the child’s pace, allowing space and equipment and movement necessary for overall early childhood development. It is also to provide a balance between quiet and active periods, between academic awareness and comfortable relaxation, always allowing the joy of self-discovery and the pleasure of social interaction.

We have an extremely high return rate, with most of our first-year children returning the following year. And each one of our 7 centers has at least one teacher on staff who themselves were once a Sandbox student!

Sandbox graduates still keep in touch, so we have seen our children grow to become intelligent, confident, and productive adults, many landing successful careers. Visit us today and see what sets us apart.

detail:
Sandbox Early Care & Education in Orland Park offering Preschool and Daycare services for children ages 2-5 years, Half Day and Extended Day Kindergarten, Before and After School Age Care and Summer Camp for children ages 2-12 years.

Our director, Cindy Galason, focuses on creating a positive early childhood learning experience for every child at The Sandbox Learning Center, ensuring safety while encouraging creativity among the children. She has been employed with Sandbox since October of 2002 and has extensive teaching experience with prior lead teaching
positions in all age groups. She has a Bachelor’s degree in Early Childhood Education from DePaul University and attains an Illinois Directors Credential Level II, ECE Credential and an Infant/Toddler Credential.

As with all our schools, the staff at our Orland Park Sandbox located on 151st Street is committed to early Childhood Education.  Some of the teachers have been with working at this location for over 20 years.  We pride ourselves in the nurturing care we provide the children, the family friendly atmosphere, and our excellent staff.

We feel that you child’s daycare experience will be an important factor in the social, intellectual, physical and emotional development of their formative years. Therefore, we strive to offer a loving, well organized and educational environment. Many activities, both indoor and outdoor, will be utilized to achieve these goals. Many teaching medias are used. 

Each child is encouraged to grow and develop at his own speed. The child does this by exploring, manipulating, playing, finding out what and how, and discovering for themselves. Every child is unique and so are their parents.

detail:

 -a growing relationship with Jesus Christ by modeling, teaching and practicing age-appropriate components of spiritual development

 -loving, nurturing interactions between Christian educators, children and their families

-a commitment to exceeding the standards, goals and practices of Early Childhood Center Certification of the Evangelical Lutheran Education Association (ELEA) and the DCFS Licensing Regulations of the State of Illinois

The Jolly Fun House Playschool was founded in 1942 and is third generation owned.  Our belief is a child’s learning environment should be safe, creative, warm and stimulating.

At the JFH Academies, our primary goal is to provide a personal and unique experience for each child. We strive to enrich the intellectual, physical, social and personal values and skills your child is now forming.

JFH offers customized curriculum for children from early childhood through primary grades, as well as many programs for gifted students. We pride ourselves on our individualized and innovative programs for children, and our personalized approach to education made possible by small classroom sizes and the best educators in the Chicago land area.

At JFH, our past, present and future commitment is to provide the highest standard of care and education for your child.

We offer two schools to better serve you and your child.

name: SAFE HAVEN CHILD CARE ACADEMY, INC

detail:
Health Care. Child Welfare. Community-Based Services. Aunt Martha's.

Aunt Martha’s is a family of more than 1,300 staff and volunteers. We are health care providers, social workers, educators, counselors, and advocates. We are as diverse as the people and communities we serve.

We honor people’s strengths, resourcefulness and resilience. We offer compassion. We provide supportive, professional care.

We are a team – skilled and specialized. From the psychiatrist treating children in downstate Illinois, to the dental hygienist care for a homeless person in Kane County; and from the therapist helping a youth in crisis on the streets of Chicago, to the doctor delivering a baby in Kankakee. Our staff are the best and the brightest in the field.

We are all Care Coordinators – intensely dedicated to our patients and clients, connecting each person with exactly what they need, from the services our organization provides to the specialized care offered by our collaborating partners.

We are Aunt Martha’s.

name: CUDDLE CARE CHILD CARE CENTER
detail: CUDDLE CARE INC is a year-round program that offers all day care for children ages 6 weeks to 6 years. Our daily activities and program consists of a flexible schedule that has been created to provide diversity and challenge for children in all age groups.  We offer a structured program for children of all ages that includes a year round curriculum.  Our activities include school readiness skills, arts and crafts, games, music, outdoor play and story time.  We offer a Full Time contract, which is for children present at the center over 6 hours per day, and we offer a Part Time contract, which is for children present at the center for less than 6 hours per day.

detail: A stress-free solution for working parents, Before and After Care provides a safe and secure alternative to would be Ã¢â‚¬Å“latch-keyÃ¢â‚¬Â child. name: ACORN OAKS PRESCHOOL CHILD CARE
detail:
Program content is a dynamic combination of teacher-guided and child-initiated learning activities. 
Through skillful observation of each child, Academy teachers extend a child's development by providing experiences that help them make connections with what they already know and can achieve.

Teachers plan meaningful integrated activities to meet four categories of curriculum goals for each child:
• Skills - Developing large and small muscles, manners, habits, and other practices related to positive relationships and living.
• Knowledge - Developing foundations of math, science, social studies, problem solving abilities, language arts, music, and art.
• Feelings - Developing feelings of trust, adequacy, competence, acceptance and self-esteem.
• Dispositions - Developing tendencies related to literacy (focused participation, risk taking, hypothesis testing, persistence, and self-regulation) and toward creative thinking, curiosity, and learning.

The Village Children's Academy works to develop strong lines of communication between the school and parents. Formal conferences are scheduled throughout the year and the staff is available for informal meetings on an ongoing basis.  In addition, a parent board works closely with the school's management to ensure an even greater ongoing flow of communications and the development of new ideas. 

Curriculum is designed to promote learning, experience, and development in the following areas:
• Whole Language
• Phonics
• Art
• Music
• Math
• Science
• Nutrition and Health
• Social Relationships
• Spanish

Other activities include:
• Weekly Music Classes
• Community Field Trips
• Enrichment Afternoons
• Cultural Outings
• Playtime on Private Playgrounds

Separate enrichment programs are available for an additional fee: 
• Private Music Lessons
• Tumbling
• Computer Skills

name: LEARN AS YOU GROW DAY CARE, LLC
LA PETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

name: JENNIFER'S KIDS LEARNING CENTER

WE PRIDE OURSELVES IN DIVERSITY.
