name: ZION BUDS OF PROMISE CHRISTIAN ACADEMY
KIDDY KULTURE CHILD CARE & LEARNING CTR
NURTURING DEVELOPMENTAL LEARNING ACADEMY
detail: The mission of Nurturing Developmental & Learning Academy is to provide exceptional care for children in a clean, safe learning environment. We place the need of each individual child at the forefront of our program. Efforts are focused on each child’s personality as well as fostering their overall development. Our goal is to promote the physical, social, emotional, and cognitive development of each child.  We recognize and foster an active partnership between home and school; including partnerships formed with the community.

name: FAMILY LIFE CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
Family Life Christian Preschool and Daycare offers quality Christian care, guidance, and growth for children ages 15 months through 12 years old. Family Life was founded by First Reformed Church of South Holland in 1981 as a community outreach program and is now a non-profit, state-licensed center. We at Family Life take pride in our excellent, highly qualified, loving staff members who devote their time and energy to each child and our school. Together, the church board, pastor, and director, and staff work towards the following goals:

1. To provide a safe, secure environment for play and learning.
2. To foster increased self-awareness.
3. To deepen love for God and His Word, family, and others.
4. To guide social growth and provide companionship.
5. To stimulate cognitive growth, creative interest, physical activity, sensory channels, language experience, artistic expression, music appreciation, and independent success.

name: HAPPY DAYS CHILD CARE CENTER
detail:
Happy Days Child Development Center is where your child can gain the tools needed to reach their potential. We take childhood education very seriously and are committed to helping your child succeed while having fun at the same time. By maintaining small class sizes, we ensure your child gets the individualized attention they deserve.


We are passionate about education and providing your Child with the tools to be successful in life. Our philosophy is to focus on the needs of the individual child by providing a stimulating atmosphere for learning along with a secure loving environment.


We offer full or part-time care at an affordable price for children 6 weeks to 12 years of age and have 3 locations to serve you in the Chicago Land Area – Berwyn, Cicero, and South Holland. Call to Schedule a Tour Today, we want to be your partner in nurturing your child’s dreams!

We offer full-day and half-day educational child care, preschool, pre-kindergarten, kindergarten, and before-and-after school care facility.

Happy Days Child Development Center is OPEN ALL YEAR AROUND to meet the schedules of working parents. We are conveniently located in Berwyn, Cicero, and South Holland.

name: THE GINGERBREAD HOUSE C.C. CENTER, INC.
SUNNY DAYS LEARNING CENTER OF STICKNEY
detail: Our daycare was founded by Patricia Kaiser, Chief Administrative Officer, who loves children and has been actively involved with them all of her life including three wonderful children of her own.  Her experience in managing an early learning program, goes back to 1983, when she first opened Sunny Days.  Patricia has received an Early Childhood Education Certificate from Trition College, an Associate Degree from Morton College and also studied infant and toddler curriculum at Kendall College and Concordia University.

name: ST BLASE EARLY CHILDHOOD DEVELOPMENT CTR
ANTICO ACADEMY, INC.
detail:
The Antico Academy strives to provide an environment that helps children feel safe and comfortable.  The small size of the childcare center permits teachers and staff to give each child individual attention and allows for good communication with parents.  The home-like environment enables children to easily make the transition from home to school.
 
The Antico Academy was founded in 1996 and is operated by two college professors with expertise in child development.  They continue to oversee the curriculum and insure that the Academy provides a safe, nurturing, home-like environment.

name: WESTCHESTER PK DT-TOT SPOT & LATCH KEY
FIRST CONGREGATIONAL CHURCH PRESCHOOL
detail:
We Believe in the Power of  Play! 
Research on young children's learning and development proves how play strongly benefits a child's intellectual, social, emotional, physical and language development.

Children at play are actively involved in creating themes, exploring and establishing environments, solving problems, and developing shared understandings.  Through play, young children learn to see other's points of view, to use language in new ways, to interact with others, and develop their muscles and coordination.

name: KENSINGTON SCHOOL OF WESTERN SPRINGS
detail:
Kensington School, established in 1969, is a private preschool and kindergarten in the western suburbs of Chicago.  Throughout eight locations, our innovative curriculum, inspirational teaching and extraordinary classroom environments make Kensington a distinctive first school experience for each child.

In a world built just for them, you will find busy, curious and happy children who love being at Kensington. The sound of laughter, the magic of learning and the hum of activity fills every corner of our buildings.

We invite you to visit one of our schools and experience the energy and excitement that has impacted the educational foundation of thousands of children and has become recognized as a praiseworthy model of the finest traditions of early childhood education.

We look forward to the opportunity to introduce your child to Kensington School – a world built just for them.

name: L & L BRIGHT BEGINNINGS PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
Kensington School, established in 1969, is a private preschool and kindergarten in the western suburbs of Chicago.  Throughout eight locations, our innovative curriculum, inspirational teaching and extraordinary classroom environments make Kensington a distinctive first school experience for each child.

In a world built just for them, you will find busy, curious and happy children who love being at Kensington. The sound of laughter, the magic of learning and the hum of activity fills every corner of our buildings.

We invite you to visit one of our schools and experience the energy and excitement that has impacted the educational foundation of thousands of children and has become recognized as a praiseworthy model of the finest traditions of early childhood education.

We look forward to the opportunity to introduce your child to Kensington School – a world built just for them.

name: WEE CARE CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Here at Wee Care Children's Center, we know the level of trust you place in us when you put your child in our care. That's why we are committed to providing a safe, secure and comfortable environment for your little one. Our high quality Christian preschool and extended care is the ideal place to prepare your child for the life ahead.

We offer excellent facilities to children between ages 2 and 6 in Wilmette, IL and the surrounding areas.With more than 31 years of experience, our trained staff understands the specific needs of children and provides building blocks for their bright future.

Our low teacher-student ratio ensures proper supervision, while allowing your child to develop in a group setting. Rest assured your child will receive maximum individual attention. We not only focus on enhancing the academic and creative skills of our little scholars, but also inculcate in them values such as sharing, patience and kindness.

name: LUTHERAN GENERAL CHILDRENS DAY CARE WILM
TRINITY CHURCH NURSERY SCHOOL
detail: We’re reaching out to provide one of the most highly respected preschools in the northern suburbs. Trinity Church Nursery School is a non-denominational preschool dedicated to the belief that each child is a precious individual with a unique pattern of development. We feel that building a child’s self esteem is crucial to the learning process.  Self-esteem is enhanced when a child experiences pleasure in seeking, doing, and achieving.  Through carefully planned activities we encourage children to stretch their imaginations and abilities and to try the untried. We want children to enjoy themselves,  to gain a sense of independence,  and to feel secure and happy as they interact with others and develop friendships. Our teachers offer support, guidance, and a nurturing environment.  We are committed to do whatever is necessary to ensure that each child thrives and feels capable and loved. Our mission is to provide a safe and stimulating environment in which children may play,  learn, grow, and flourish in body, mind and spirit.

name: WILMETTE COMMUNITY NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
Wilmette Community Nursery School (WCNS) provides high quality, developmentally appropriate, play-based educational programs for young children and support for their families. The school provides a carefully planned, nurturing environment that facilitates the social, emotional, cognitive and physical development of children who are 2 to 6 years in age. The curriculum emphasizes play, social interaction and creativity, and encourages curiosity and the development of self-esteem by emphasizing the children’s ability to make choices for themselves.

At WCNS, your child’s needs and feelings are our primary interest. Our school offers a place for noisy, active children as well as quiet, thoughtful children—we have an activity guaranteed to fit their mood and personality on any given day. In this stimulating environment, your child will make new friends, discover new toys and talents, and build confidence across his/her developing skills.

name: BAKER DEMONSTRATION SCHOOL TODDLER PROG
detail:
Baker Demonstration School is an independent coeducational school, serving toddler through eighth grade children, dedicated to creating well-rounded students through the principles of progressive education.

Less formally, Baker is a school where children learn by doing.

Founded in 1918 by Clara Belle Baker, a leader in progressive education, the curriculum today still reflects the philosophy she shared with the likes of Francis Parker, John Dewey, and Jean Piaget. In broad strokes, the school emphasizes hands-on learning over lectures and memorization of facts. Furthermore, as the North Shore’s only demonstration school, Baker is a place where students from leading college- and graduate-level education programs come to learn from our master instructors as teachers-in-training. Consequently, the majority of the classrooms have both a teacher and an associate teacher. It is the unique combination of demonstration school and progressive curriculum which makes Baker uniquely suited to teach children to love to learn, cherish the journey and serve the world.

name: WINNETKA PUBLIC SCHOOL NURSERY
detail:
Winnetka Public School Nursery (WPSN) is a private play-based preschool with classes for ages 16 months through Junior Kindergarten. Despite our name, we are a private preschool as well as the oldest preschool in Winnetka. Nestled in the heart of Winnetka, WPSN is located at 1155 Oak Street.

WPSN offers a play-based approach to early childhood development and education. WPSN’s talented, nurturing, and experienced teachers individualize the curriculum to meet each child’s developmental needs and interests. WPSN consistently fosters cognitive development, social and emotional skills, critical thinking, and creativity, including the following:

    Lifelong interpersonal skills: How to collaborate and build relationships with peers and teachers
    Curiosity and critical thinking skills: How to ask, think and hypothesize about the world
    Respect: For their peers, teachers, community and the world around them
    Self-confidence: Knowing they are competent learners and that their voice matters
    A love of learning: Experiencing learning as fun, in an atmosphere of innovation and caring support

name: FRENCH SCHOOL
detail:
The French School, located in the heart of Chicago’s North Shore, is a total French immersion preschool/kindergarten. We welcome children when they are at the optimal age to learn French, giving them the opportunity to develop a high level of language proficiency and fluency.

The French School’s comprehensive curriculum is based on France’s internationally renowned école maternelle. Set forth by the French Ministry of Education, this program is revered as one of the world’s best and gives your child a solid academic foundation while providing a warm, nurturing environment where learning is fun and age appropriate.

name: LITTLE LEARNERS ACADEMY
detail: Little Learners Academy has a fresh approach to educating young children. We use a music base as our key teaching tool, this along with engaging puppets, games and a well structured solid curriculum make Little Learners the highest quality preschool and private Kindergarten. We work for our families to assure that we continue to offer this high quality experience ALL children deserve while still making it affordable for all families. It is our hearts work to give all our students a firm academic foundation for life long learning.

name: E.R.B.A -MATTOON HEAD START
detail: Head Start is a Child Development Program which provides comprehensive educational and health services to preschool children (3-5 years old) of primarily low-income families.  At least 10% of the children served have a disability.  The children receive nutritious meals, breakfast and snacks.  ERBA Head Start also provides a strong Parental Involvement Program to parents. Parents are involved in program planning, operating activities and are eligible to receive cash incentives for completing the GED and/or college classes.

name: FCNS CHILD DEVELOPMENT LABORATORY AT NIU
detail:
The Child Development Lab (CDL) is a teaching and research facility for child development and early childhood professionals sponsored by the School of Family, Consumer, and Nutrition Sciences.  Accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC) with a four star rating from the Quality Rating System of the Illinois Department of Human Services, the laboratory provides inclusive, full-day, mixed-age child care in a nurturing and supportive environment with low teacher-child ratios. High quality care is implemented by the full-time staff that is highly educated in child development and early childhood education.

naeyc_famThe Child Development Lab has three mixed-age classrooms. There are two mixed-age classrooms with infants (6 weeks - 14 months old), toddlers (15-23 months old) and two-year-olds, and there is one mixed age classroom for preschoolers (3-5 years old).

We are a developmental based program which uses Emergent Curriculum. Our curriculum fosters the development of the whole child including language, cognitive, emotional, social and physical domains.

name: ONCE UPON A TIME CHILD CARE
detail:
Once Upon a Time Child Care was established in September, 2006 we are licensed by Department of Children and Family Services. Our center operates year round from 6:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. We were licensed for 50 children. After expanding in 2008 and 2009 we are currently licensed for 78 children, 6wks through Kindergarten. We have 6 classrooms and 15 staff members. We provide stimulating activities that enrich children physical, cognitive, social and emotional development. Our hands-on program

    Stimulates language development,
    Promotes small and large muscle coordination
    Promotes gross motor development through exercising and music
    Develops fine motor skills by coloring, cutting, puzzles, and art projects
    Fosters social and emotional development by assisting children with problem solving
    Encourage self-help and self-control skills

 

We learn through our play. Our goal is to ensure that every child’s needs are being met by introducing a variety of materials based on the child’s age, abilities, and interests.

name: OPEN HANDS PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
Open Hands Preschool is a part of the Christian education program of the Waterman United Methodist and Waterman Presbyterian Churches. We are licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services (DCFS). Our Preschool offers:
 
* A Christian learning center.
* Loving, caring, and qualified teachers.
* A quality developmental program for children ages 3 to 6.
* An opportunity for your child to feel safe, loved, challenged,
  and important in an educational environment.
* Opportunities for parent input and participation.
* A fully equipped indoor playroom and a large outdoor fenced in play area.
business hours:
Mon. Wed. Fri.   8:30-11:00 AM      4-6 year olds
Tue. & Thu.       8:30-11:00 AM         3 year olds

name: GOD LOVES LITTLE CHILDREN DAY CARE II
TUTOR TIME CHILD CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail: Every child is different. Every child is one-of-a-kind. So at Tutor Time, every child’s unique set of skills and interests are utilized to his or her advantage in the way that they learn, grow, build self-esteem, and develop their imagination. It’s our job to bring out their best through nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: PIXI & DIXI DAY CARE CTR INC
detail:
PixieDixie Daycare Center is a modern, beautifully designed language-learning preschool and daycare facility. We offer a rich array of activities designed to stimulate and inspire children in gaining new skills and abilities. We understand the challenges involved and the care that is required in early childhood education. We enroll children from as early as 15 months old.

It is well established that the most important years of learning are begun at birth. A child's brain at this age is making connections that will last the rest of their life. Studies have shown that high quality preschools have a long term effect in improving the success of a child.

Our goal is to facilitate and foster language-learning skills from an early age that will prove invaluable in your child's future. In order to prepare our children for the global world we live in, our program integrates a multicultural approach into our curriculum. It's goal is in preparing your children to succeed and live in full harmony with people of different ideas, religions, and ethnicities.

At PixieDixie, we advocate a healthy and nutritious lifestyle. To that end, we offer home cooked meals and snacks throughout the day along with fresh juice and milk. We place the utmost importance on the physical and emotional well-being of your child. We interact with every child on an individual level, allowing us to provide them the maximum amount of care and safety.

We realize how important it is for your child to understand themselves and the world around them and be able to harmoniously function in it. In allowing your child the opportunity to explore language-learning at an early age, you will be ensuring for them a better upbringing, a better education, and a better future.

PixieDixie Daycare is filled with trained and loving professionals who are prepared to mentor and care for your children with the highest level of quality. So if you are looking for the best preschool or daycare center for your child, you've found the right place!

name: ST MARK'S CHRISTIAN MONTESSORI PRESCHOOL
detail: St. Mark Christian Montessori Preschool and Daycare provides a unique educational experience incorporating Christian values with the Montessori curriculum. Our daycare serves infants from 6 weeks to 2 1/2 years. Our Montessori classrooms serve children ages 2 1/2 - 5 years old, including a kindergarten program. We recognize this age as a critical time to instill God’s love and the thrill to learn.

Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.

name: SETON MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail: The goal of Seton Montessori School is to enable each child to grow in awareness of him or herself, of others, and of the world around. Dr. Maria Montessori recognized that the very young child goes through periods of great sensitivity in particular areas during which one learns more easily than any other time in life. A totally prepared environment awaits the absorbent mind of the child. Each material, activity, or experience is expressly designed to give the child new perspective, to develop a scientific concept, or to encourage growth as a social being. Seton fosters a sense of partnership between the children, the teachers, and the parents to work collaboratively towards the common goal of realizing each child’s fullest potential.

name: LADS AND LASSIES PRE-SCHOOL INC
detail: Our program is designed to enhance your child's self-esteem and personal development. Our goal is to help your child improve their communication skills while nurturing their, emotional, social, and intellectual development. We strongly believe in hands on learning in an academic environment to improve each child's own personal education.

name: READY, SET, GROW, INCORPORATED
detail: Ready, Set, Grow is a family owned and operated child care center. Judy Monaco began the center as a licensed home child care in 1993. Prior to this, she was the owner and director of The Little Gingerbread House in Oak Lawn. Opening another center was always a goal for Judy. In 2005, Judy's daughter Beth Orr, graduated with her BA in Early Childhood Education. It was at this point, that this mother and daughter team began actively looking for a location to open a child care center. In July of 2008, Ready, Set Grow opened its doors. It began with the enrollment of the 12 children from Judy's home child care, and quickly grew to over 70 part time and full time children enrolled in just 2 years!

name: ELMHURST ACADEMY OF EARLY LEARNING
detail:
Elmhurst Academy's philosophy towards educating young children is inspired by
the programs of Reggio Emilia, Italy. Internationally regarded as an exceptional
method for early childhood education, the basic principles of the Reggio Emilia
schools focus on the strength and capability of the children they serve. At
Elmhurst Academy, we recognize the collaboration that takes place between
children and teachers and see the work they do together as key within the learning
environment.

Where Love of Learning Begins

name: CHILDTIME CHILDRENS CENTER
detail: We help children learn to love their world. At Childtime, your child gets what he or she needs to develop their best mind, their love of learning, their personality, their bright future. We provide nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: WESTMINSTER PRESCHOOL
detail:
Mission Statement for the Preschool: The ministry of WPS strives to provide a foundation for the love of learning, nurture for a child’s body, mind & spirit with skills and confidence for the academic years ahead.

Westminster School has excelled in early childhood education for more than 50 years. In 1956, First Presbyterian Church of Glen Ellyn founded Westminster as a ministry outreach of the church and a service to the community.

name: LOUISE M. BEEM ECEC DEMONSTRATION CNTR
detail:
The Louise M. Beem Early Childhood Center is committed to providing quality care and education for young children while working in partnership with their families. The Center is a part of the Continuing Education department at College of DuPage and is licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services.

All classes are taught by lead teachers with a minimum of a bachelor's degree and teachers with a minimum of an associate degree in Early Childhood Education or Child Care and Development. College students who are pursuing their education in the Early Childhood Education field may also participate in the classrooms. College students enrolled in education, psychology, speech language pathology or other approved classes may observe the children's program from our observation pods.

name: TUTOR TIME CHILD CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail: Every child is different. Every child is one-of-a-kind. So at Tutor Time, every child’s unique set of skills and interests are utilized to his or her advantage in the way that they learn, grow, build self-esteem, and develop their imagination. It’s our job to bring out their best through nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: VLG/GLENDL HGTS PRKS & RCRTN DPT PRE-SCH
CHILDREN'S MONTESSORI LANGUAGE ACADEMY
detail: Children’s Montessori Language Academy is a community based Montessori school serving young children and their families from pre-birth to six years of age in Hinsdale, Illinois and the surrounding areas. We are committed to providing a language rich experience within a Montessori setting. We offer a birth to 3 class, a 2 year old class and a mixed age preschool class for children 3-6 years old.

name: KLC DBA CHAMPIONS @ ST CYRIL
detail:
Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not. 

A loving, safe, fun environment with trusted adults to care for and guide your child is the foundation of all our programs. What sets us apart are our highly trained educators who deliver the thorough and engaging Early Foundations curriculum for infants through 6-year-olds. While your child is feeling cared for and having fun, our professional teachers are skillfully fostering your child's cognitive, emotional, social, and physical development to its greatest potential. Our curriculum and methods also prepare students for seamless transitions into each next level of education. Once in Kindergarten, our Extension and Enrichment Program collaborates with Woodland Primary to reinforce and extend your child's learning day, thus maximizing his/her readiness for first grade. And while loving staff and rich curriculum are essential, we also commit to ongoing teacher coaching, extensive evaluations, and continual professional development that result in the highest quality education and care for your child.

name: HIS GRACE CHRISTIAN CHILD DEVEL LRNG CTR
CREATIVE DAY LEARNING CENTER
detail:
As individuals we are all unique, having different needs and personal goals, which help us establish the criteria for a happy and healthy living environment. Children too have different individual needs at various points throughout their growing stages. Our objective, at Creative Day Learning Center, is to accommodate these needs by: 1) presenting a warm and healthy atmosphere filled with many options for practical experiences, 2) providing a home away from home type surrounding comfortable to all children, 3) submitting a healthy positive attitude, creating enthusiasm which is so vital to a child’s progress as they grow.

In so doing, we focus on activities in the areas of language, social, and motor development. Our program includes: Arts and Crafts, Music, Literature, Writing, Dramatic Play and Science activities. We encourage the art of doing, as it is through experience and practice that a child progresses.

In general, we provide an informal and natural home type setting which is important in making children feel welcome and accepted by his/her teachers and peers. This also makes him/her feel secure and protected.

Finally, our overall goal is to foster a positive attitude to each and every child, giving all the encouragement and support needed to grow and carry on day to day. This is the criteria we at Creative Day Learning Center have set for ourselves as we strive to consistently build a happy and healthy second home for your child.

name: COOP NS 1ST CHURCH-LOMBARD
detail:
A child's first school experience is an important one.  Each child is different and deserves individual attention.  The Cooperative Nursery School of Lombard has been meeting the needs of children for more than 50 years.  Our staff believes that children come first!  Our program is a play based curriculum, creating an environment in which all children develop the academic, social, and emotional skills they need to be successful in school and beyond.  Research shows that "young children learn best through manipulation of materials and hands-on experiences, planned by knowledgeable teachers...It is play with purpose" (NAEYC, Early Years are Learning Years). 
We realize that all children have different needs and develop at different rates.  Some children need a familiar routine , while others are adventurous.  To meet these diverse needs, painting, block play, play dough, and familiar books and songs are part of the everyday routine, while a rotating variety of table toys, science activities, art projects, dramatic play areas, and field trips make each day different.  Our staff works in partnership with each child to find the right path to success.

name: KENSINGTON SCHOOL OF NAPERVILLE
detail:
Kensington School, established in 1969, is a private preschool and kindergarten in the western suburbs of Chicago.  Throughout eight locations, our innovative curriculum, inspirational teaching and extraordinary classroom environments make Kensington a distinctive first school experience for each child.

In a world built just for them, you will find busy, curious and happy children who love being at Kensington. The sound of laughter, the magic of learning and the hum of activity fills every corner of our buildings.

We invite you to visit one of our schools and experience the energy and excitement that has impacted the educational foundation of thousands of children and has become recognized as a praiseworthy model of the finest traditions of early childhood education.

We look forward to the opportunity to introduce your child to Kensington School – a world built just for them.

name: THE LITTLE SHEPHERD DAY SCHOOL CENTER
detail:
Peter Pan Early Learning Centers and Little Shepherd Day School are privately owned preschools with private kindergarten programs. Helen Hochstetter, our Executive Director and owner, has had the fine reputation of administering outstanding early childhood programs since 1969. Our private ownership allows us to reinvest right back into each of our schools, continually enhancing and improving our home-like, interactive learning environment. We can assure you that Peter Pan will provide your child with the absolute best care and early childhood experiences!

Our professional, dedicated, and highly trained staff is our greatest asset. You will find every Peter Pan teacher is truly dedicated and focused on providing a nurturing environment with outstanding curriculum activities. Each has a wealth of talent and professional experience to draw upon. They use a variety of teaching methods and materials to engage, support and challenge each child. It is amazing to observe these professionals in action and see all of the exciting activities each class is involved in throughout the day.

Our administrative team and long term early childhood teachers take great pride in our program and the excellent care and education we provide for our families. We know that each and every day our staff makes a conscientious and loving effort to provide the very best throughout the many facets of each child’s day. Every Peter Pan staff member works very hard to insure each child is nurtured and cared for in a kind and gentle manner. Our administrative team and teachers are all experienced and degreed early childhood professionals with a love of children and teaching.

Our Peter Pan staff appreciates the time and thought that parents put into choosing an early childhood program for their child. We realize that you want only the best for your child and know that choosing the correct early childhood program is one of the most important decisions you will ever make. While our website provides you with basic information, the quality and depth of our program is something you must see to appreciate.

name: DUPAGE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
DuPage Montessori School is a private, non-profit educational institution affiliated with the American Montessori Society and registered with the Illinois State Board of Education. Founded in 1987 by Robert and Sharon Breen, the school has grown in response to community interest in Montessori education. We offer programs for children ages 15 months through 14 years. Commitment is the most important part of our relationship with our students and their families. By focusing on each child as a unique individual, we offer learning experiences that satisfy each child's interests and needs. Workshops and other events for parents are offered throughout the year. Parents may also support or join the Parent Task Force, which works on fundraising, community projects, and school events. Parental support comes naturally as you connect with the educational process, and thus the school becomes an important part of the community.

Our mission is to help your child build the foundation for a happy and capable adolescence and adulthood.
We encourage children to exercise good judgment, cooperate with others, and use self-discipline--to develop values and skills that allow each child to become an important member of the social group. Daily discoveries and new experiences create a thirst for more knowledge, preparing your child for all that life has to offer.

name: ST. JOHN'S PRE-SCHOOL
detail: Our mission at St. John’s Preschool is to help each child reach his or her learning potential. We want our preschool children to leave each day with smiles on their faces, new ideas in their heads and love and confidence in their hearts.
business hours:
Program (M-F) 8:45-11:45 a.m.
Extended Day (T/W/Th) 11:45-2:00 p.m.

name: LA PETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

name: TRINITY CARE CENTER
detail:
We offer a caring, enriching program, where young children can learn and grow. We have developmentally appropriate programs and practices that provide an opportunity for young children to develop critical thinking skills and positive social skills.We have a variety of age-appropriate activities that are enjoyed daily in our classrooms and outdoors.We provide nutritious, hot lunches and a.m./p.m. snacks.Intergenerational programming (with Trinity’s Adult Care Center) is an integral part of our program.Concepts and skills are introduced to children in classroom interest centers and through computer exploration.Children have the opportunity to experience a wide variety of enriching activities in a warm, caring, Christian environment.Our qualified Early Childhood Staff foster a love for learning in each child.

Trinity Care Center’s goal is to provide quality care and education for children and their families in a Christian environment.
business hours: Monday to Friday from 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: VLGE OF VILLA PK-REC DEPT/E.C. PROGRAMS
AGAPE' CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Agapè Children’s Center is designed to meet the emotional, social, intellectual, physical and spiritual needs of children ages 3-5.  We are a not-for-profit, Christian preschool licensed by D.C.F.S. and have been serving the Warrenville community and surrounding area for more than 25 years.

Agapè is a Greek word for love.  It describes the type of unconditional love that God has for us.  At Agapè we strive to provide an ecumenical Christian program that demonstrates this kind of love.   Our philosophy is based on the acceptance of each child as he or she is.  Our teaching techniques are aimed at building confidence, self-respect and responsibility through play and directed experiences.   Our curriculum is based on the needs and interests of the children in each class.

name: ALL ABOUT CARING
detail: At Tots in Motion Inc., our daycare center (All About Caring) services the Warrenville, Naperville, West Chicago and Aurora IL areas. We have an amazing staff that combines learning experiences and structured play in a fun, safe and nurturing environment. Tots highly trained teachers and staff nurture kids’ natural curiosity and wonder within a safe, home style environment that allows them to explore and discover as they learn. Our childcare team will assist each individual youth during their early childhood education years to find them ways to learn that are right for them. The enthusiastic teachers genuinely care about children, and understand each child’s individual developmental needs and learning styles. We take the time to help each child discover, in his or her own way, a fascinating world of play and learning. We offer far more than just childcare at our child care centers, we offer a first introduction to a lifetime of learning and a journey that starts off on the right foot. A journey we will take together!

name: CREME DE LA CREME, INC.(WARRENVILLE)
detail:
Crème's passion for child development has spawned research to enhance the learning experience in young minds. In fact, Crème has been bringing out the greatness within children since 1980, earning awards for the best daycare and the best childcare centers throughout Colorado, Georgia, Illinois, Kansas, New Jersey, Ohio, Texas, and Virginia.

Crème's exceptional early learning programs have been featured in both national and local media such as: CBS Evening News, NBC Nightly News, Good Morning America, U.S. News & World Reports, Education Week, The Washington Post, The Chicago Tribune, The Denver Post, The Kansas City Star, The Chicago Sun Times, and Chicago Tribune.

name: KIDDYPLACE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
We structure the daily activities at Kiddyplace by observing the rapidly changing developmental levels of the child. Considering the busy schedule of the parents we provide before / after school care and transportation for the children to and from West Chicago / Carol Stream Schools. Your child will be in our caring and loving environment after his / her school day. Parents will be informed on daily basis about your child's activity at Kiddyplace.
At Kiddyplace learning center all programs and activities are carefully designed to match your child's needs. Our staff with warm and caring attitude will give more personalized importance to each child. The most critical phase for the development of your child's brain are the first 3 years. Our quality early child care outstanding programs and a warm response from our caregiver will help your child's total cognitive, physical as well as psychosocial development
business hours: Monday thru Friday from 6:00 a.m. to 6: 30 p.m.

detail: First Pres Preschool & Pre-K provides a safe, caring, Christian environment that stimulates the physical, social, emotional, and cognitive development of children. We've been serving the community since 1967.

name: WOODRIDGE UNITED METHODIST PRESCHOOL-SM
detail:
The mission of Small Miracles Preschool is to provide quality early childhood education and care. We seek to provide a safe environment in which young children feel respected, loved, and valued while nurturing their capacity to grow socially, emotionally, intellectually, and spiritually. We strive to deepen children's commitment to positive social values such as kindness, helpfulness, and respect for others.

As a ministry of Woodridge United Methodist Church, a Christian community of faith, we gladly accept and welcome children and families of all faith backgrounds. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, gender, national origin, disability, economic status, or cultural background.

name: CHRISTIAN COUNTY HEAD START
detail:
The Head Start 0-5 Program is a free federally-funded program that provides comprehensive educational services to pregnant women and children ages 0-5, including those with significant or multiple special needs, that meet the Federal Income Guidelines for enrollment.  Currently the program benefits the families of 430 preschool children and 80 infants, toddlers, and pregnant women in the seven county service area.

Head Start is operated by local non-profit organizations in almost every county in the country.  Children who attend Head Start participate in a variety of educational activities that help them grow mentally, socially, emotionally, and physically.  Children leave the Head Start program better prepared for kindergarten, excited about learning, and ready to succeed.

name: SUNNY DAYS CHILD CARE & LEARNING CENTER
VANDALIA 1ST UNITED METHODIST PRESCHOOL
detail: The First United Methodist Preschool was established in 1980 by the First United Methodist Church in Vandalia. It is a Christian-based preschool that is licensed by the state and is inspected every year. All staff meet requirements of the State of Illinois and receive additional training each year. The First United Methodist Preschool is governed by a Board of Directors consisting of members from the First United Methodist Church. The Staff at the First United Methodist Preschool is dedicated to providing a well balanced curriculum along with a warm and nurturing environment for all children.

name: GIBSON CITY COMM. AFTER SCH. PROG.(CAPS)
PAXTON DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
The Paxton Day Care Center and Preschool is a full serviced day care center with preschool curriculum.The Center offers quality care for children 2 years thru 12 years of age. The Center's purpose is to be a supplement to the home through a planned curriculum appropriate to the childs age.
The Center is a not-for-profit corporation, governed by a Board of Directors. This Board is comprised of parents of enrolled children and other members of the Paxton Community. The State of Illinois Department of Children and Family Services have licensed the Center and monitor the program on a regular basis.

name: THE BUSY BEE EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: We opened The Busy Bee Early Learning Center in 2006 to provide our son along with the Christopher Community a high quality child care setting. We pride ourselves on our love and care for children with an emphasis on learning through play.

name: ROOTS & WINGS EARLY EDUCATION CENTER
detail: The mission of Roots and Wings Early Education Center is to provide a developmentally appropriate, research based curriculum designed specifically to meet the individual needs of children ages 6 weeks to 12 years old and their families. Our focus is to provide a stimulating education experience that promotes each child’s social/emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our goal is to support children’s desire to be lifelong learners.

name: LITTLE FARMERS EARLY LEARNING CENTER INC
detail: Little Farmers Early Learning Center serves children 6 weeks through 6 years of age. We believe that the early years of a child's life are extremely important in their cognitive, social, and physical growth.

name: ST JOHN THE EVANGELIST CHURCH DAYCARE
EARLY BEGINNINGS INC
detail: E.B.I. is a daycare and private Preschool, owned and operated by Allison (Early) Tepen of White Hall. We serve children ages 6 weeks -12 years. This is my 10th year of business.

name: KIDS KORNER
detail:
We provide residents of Coal City, IL with fun, friendly and educational child day care. We provide a safe and loving environment that adheres to the intellectual, emotional and active side of every child’s upbringing. We encourage curiosity, modern learning and respect for classical ideals. As a family owned business, we understand the importance of a fun and intellectually stimulating environment for both toddlers and elementary age children.

We offer preschool programs, before school programs, after school care, transportation to and from school and more. We are fully licensed in the state of Illinois to care for children from 2 to 12. We look forward to meeting your family and working with you to create a long lasting relationship with meaningful ties to the community.

name: STEP BY STEP CHILD CARE CENTER INC
detail: We believe that the teacher in an early childhood classroom should teach process vs. product. This Step-by-Step process teaches children valuable problem-solving skills that will help them learn throughout their lives. There should be many avenues of learning through experience and repetition. Learning should be made fun so children will want to learn throughout their life. Step by Step reinforces these learning experiences by using a variety of learning centers. After all, children are not taught, they are exposed to opportunities and experiences and encouraged by the teacher. It is up to us to provide a safe, nurturing environment that children find comfortable so they can explore……

name: GODLEY PARK DISTRICT CHILD CARE
detail: The Godley Park District Child Care Center offers a safe and educational environment to care for your children, while you work or attend classes. Our secure facility operates from 6:00 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday.
business hours: 6:00 am to 6:00 pm, Monday through Friday.

name: ROYAL CHILD CARE AND LEARNING CENTER
detail:
We at Royal Child Care and learning Center are dedicated to providing your child a quality learning experience. We at Royal Childcare and Learning Center are dedicated to create a setting in which children will find warmth, comfort, and gentleness as well as an abundance of opportunities for movement, exploration, and self-discovery according to individual needs, interests, and abilities.

We strive to assist each child to grow to their fullest potential by recognizing each stage of development and fashioning an environment (I.e. curriculum, facilities, staff) designed to nurture and facilitate growth during each stage.

We are also dedicated to help children achieve independence, self-discipline, social competence, self-knowledge, enthusiasm for learning positive attitudes, intellectual growth, and an organized approach to problem solving.

name: GALVA KIDS FIRST
detail: We are committed to affordable, accessible, high quality early care and education services and to increase public awareness of the importance of early childhood and thier impact on children's success throughout life. Kids First is dedicated to providing our children and families the best, highest qulaity services. We eagerly pursue current research on best practices and continually incorporate what we learn into our programs. We do everything we can to build partnerships within the community and with our families and to ensure our children grow up healthy, nutured, safe and well educated.

name: NEW HORIZONS LEARNING CENTER AND DAYCARE
detail:
The mission of New Horizon’s Learning Center and Day Care in Kewanee, Illinois is to provide high quality, accessible and affordable child care services to families who are employed and/or in training. We are a service-oriented company that offers developmentally appropriate programs for children ages 15 months through 12 years.

We believe that our staff and parents provide a partnership to benefit children and families from many areas in the Kewanee Illinois community and beyond. The services that we provide enhance the physical, social-emotional,  ommunication/language, and cognitive development of children while contributing to the economic vitality of our community.

name: THAWVILLE COMMUNITY NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
We receive no state funding of any kind even though we fall under the governing rules of the Department of Children and Family Services. We are not affiliated with any school district. We go by the Iroquois West calendar because the nursery school is located in that district and thought it would be easier for parents to listen for school closings for Iroquois West when there is bad weather. However, the Board of Directors has the option to change the schedule to meet the needs of the nursery school.

We appreciate your support and we hope you and your child will enjoy a great experience with Thawville Community Nursery School.

name: THE LEARNING TREE DAY CARE CENTER
detail: For day care services you can trust, contact the professionals at The Learning Tree Day Care Center. We are a day care center in Watseka, IL that has been in business since 1983. We accept children ages 4 weeks to 6 years old, and provide 2 daily snacks and hot lunches. Our friendly, knowledgeable staff is dedicated to providing a warm and caring environment for your child.

name: PRESBYTERIAN CHILD DEV. CENTER PRESCHOOL
detail:
The Presbyterian Child Development Center Day Care is a non-profit program sponsored and supported by the First Presbyterian Church of Carbondale, Illinois as a service to the community. It was created in response to the need for quality childcare in the hope that the resources of the Church could help provide that care at a more affordable cost to parents. We have been meeting this need since 1972 when we were first issued our license.

The staff of the Presbyterian Child Development Center Day Care (PCDC) or (Center) is pleased that your child will be attending the Center. We hope the time your child spends with us will hold many worthwhile and enjoyable experiences as children, parents, and teachers all learn together. The Center communicates with families in their primary language or utilizes resources as needed to communicate with families.

Parents are an important part of the children’s experiences at the Center. We look forward to getting to know you better through daily sharing, special parent visits to the Center and parent conferences. All family members are welcome to come and visit children enrolled at our center. We ask that you let the Director or the class room teacher know the day before so you can receive a visitor pass. We hope that both you and your child will find the time spent in the Center exciting and rewarding. Parents will be given an annual evaluation, this evaluation will help met the needs of the center plus the needs of he staff. This evaluation is given out every January with the newsletter. After the evaluations are reviewed the parents will receive the results in the next newsletter.

name: PUKA SCHOOL, INC.
detail:
PUKA is a Hawaiian word that refers to a small hole or hollow such as a nest that a mother foxes hollows out for her babies. In our school, the word PUKA refers specifically to the areas (child-sized and child-centered) where activities enhancing the growth and development of our children take place. In a larger sense, PUKA refers to the spirit of the whole school – that of providing a safe, healthy environment where children can grow with support and love.

PUKA School was founded in May 1973. It was incorporated as a not-for-profit educational corporation in 1974 and received tax-deductible status from the Internal Revenue Service in 1978. PUKA is classified as a 501©3.

name: CHILD DEVELOPMENT LABORATORI
detail:
The primary goal of the Child Development Laboratory (CDL) is to provide quality education and training experiences for students majoring in Early Childhood, while enhancing the field of child development through research. In that context, the CDL offers high quality child care for children from six weeks to six years of age.

Quality care is delivered through a curriculum designed to provide sound emotional, social, physical and intellectual development. Teachers assess each child’s growth and development, and plan a curriculum to facilitate these processes as a child progresses toward maturity. Both the indoor and outdoor learning environments feature a wide variety of developmentally appropriate activities. By working in conjunction with parents, the CDL staff is able to supplement home experiences and provide a continuity of care.

name: S.I.U.C. HEAD START - CARBOND
detail:
SIU Head Start is a program operated by Southern Illinois University Carbondale on a federal grant. The program is designed to serve children three to five years of age from families qualifying for Head Start throughout Jackson and Williamson Counties.

Head Start helps all children succeed by providing a comprehensive program that provides children with activities that help them grow mentally, socially, emotionally and physically.

Head Start recognizes that, as parents, you are the first and most important teachers of your children. We encourage you to participate in our program. We offer opportunities for you to become involved in classroom activities, in developing center programs, and direct involvement in the decision making of program planning and operation. We are hopeful that your experiences in Head Start will enhance your parenting skills and ability to make decisions.

Summer and Full Day Hours are 7:30AM-6:00PM

name: MURRY'S CHILD DEV. CTR.
detail:
The purpose of MCDC is to provide QUALITY care and early education for the children who are enrolled.

MCDC serves as a supplement and compliment to each child’s home and family life.  The individual needs of each child and family are considered.  Areas are provided so that each child can flourish and grow: physically, socially, intellectually, and emotionally under the guidance of qualifed teachers and staff.

name: KID'S KINGDOM PRESCHOOL, INC. NEWTON CTR
REND LAKE COLLEGE FOUND. CHILDREN'S CTR
detail:
This is the smart choice for child care.
Recently reaccredited for five more years by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), the Rend Lake College Foundation Children’s Center offers care to children 6 weeks to 5 years old throughout the school year. Summer care is available to children up to 12 years old.
business hours:
Mon - Thu: 8:00 am - 4:30 pm
Fri: 8:00 am - 4:00 pm

name: LOGAN STREET DAY CARE AND PRES
detail: The Logan Street Day Care exists to love families in our community by providing quality, loving care for children who must be separated from their parents everyday.  We express this care in a warm, understanding, and safe environment where each child will be challenged to develop spiritually, emotionally, socially, mentally, and physically.  Our dedicated and well-trained staff is committed to partnering with parents in training children in the way they should go so that when they are old, they will not depart from it.  Therefore, we are committed to serving parents and families in any manner to help them develop healthy families that are a blessing to God and others.

name: BUMBLEBEE CHILD CARE CENTER
detail: The Bumblebee Child Care Center & Pre-K believe that it is our privilege and obligation to provide educational, social, and emotional experiences everyday to all children enrolled in our child care facility. It is our goal to enrich the lives of children, parents, and all family members by providing community focuses outreach experiences through literacy and quarterly family fun nights. Here at Bumblebee Child Care Center & Pre-K, we are fulfilling our mission by being an active leader in our region's development of child care programs. Our children's and families' success is our success!

name: SONSHINE KIDS DAY CARE AND LEARNING CTR
detail:
Welcome to Sonshine Kids Daycare and Learning Center!  Sonshine Kids offers a variety of programs, depending your need. 
(Child care 6 weeks-5 years, preschool sessions, Before and After School Care & Summer Camps.)

About Sonshine Kids
    Sonshine Kids is owned and operated by the Jerseyville Methodist Church and has been in operation since August 2000.
    It is a Non-Profit Christian Based Program. 
    We are licensed for children 6 weeks-12 years of age.  
    Sonshine Kids is open year round from 6:00am-6:00pm.  
         (We are only closed for 7 major holidays.)
    We offer a wide variety of programs;  
         Preschool Sessions Full or Half days (8:30-11:30), 
         Full day care (infants, toddlers, & two year old), 
         Summer Camps (Preschool & School Age children)
    Sonshine Kids offer Before & After School Care at East, West & Grafton Elementary. 
    When schools are closed for holidays and snow days, School Age children attend Sonshine Kids at our main site.
    Healthy meals, snacks and naps are included in full day programs.
    Call to schedule a tour.

name: GALENA ART AND RECREATION CENTER
detail: The Galena ARC Preschool is an educational, socialization and enrichment program. We prepare children for kindergarten by developing self-esteem, teach number and letter recognition, respect for others as well as an opportunity to learn the social skills of sharing, listening, speaking and group participation. We offer a nurturing environment for children to discover his or her interests in a curriculum of science, nature studies, creative art projects, music, exciting field trips and guest speakers.

name: LITTLE EXPLORERS LEARNING CENTER, INC.
detail: Little Explorers Learning Center's goal is to offer high quality childcare services in Aurora, with the committment to helping children reach their full potential through the use of innovative programming and curriculum. Our programs are planned to stimulate the balanced growth of the child: physically, socially, emotionally and intellectually. Each child has a unique rate of development, which will not be hurried or forced, but based on the individual child's readiness. This uniqueness will be expected valued and accepted. Children learn by doing, imitating, exploring and questioning.

name: TWO RIVERS HEAD START
detail:
Two Rivers Head Start Agency is a community action agency which provides Head Start, Early Head Start, and CSBG services for eligible children and families. Our Agency strives to be an effective advocate for children and families affected by poverty.

Head Start & Early Head Start are federally funded child development programs designed to help break the cycle of poverty by providing children of low-income families with comprehensive programs to meet their emotional, social, health, nutritional and mental health needs. The approach is that the parent is the child's primary educator and that the entire family, as well as the community, must be involved.

name: WESLEY METHODIST CHURCH NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
We are located in Wesley United Methodist Church located on the near west side of Aurora at the corner of West Galena Blvd. and May St. which is one block east of Highland Ave.  Please call or send email to set up a tour of our school.   We welcome you and hope you will come to visit soon.

First Day of School for children is Monday, September 8th!

All Registered families and children should attend the Preview Night on Thursday, September 4th  from 5:00 – 6:00 p.m.

We are excited to welcome you and your child to preschool this fall!  At least one parent should attend preview night with the preschool child.  During this time the children will stay in their classrooms to play, meet their new friends and get to know the teachers.  Parents will attend an informational session with the Director.  All paperwork and fees should be turned in by this evening, but to make the night even better you can return everything to the preschool ahead of time.  Parents will also have time to meet and visit with the teachers.  School bags and school t-shirts will be distributed too.

name: NEW ENGLAND PRESCHOOL
detail:
We believe that children learn best through play and hands-on developmentally appropriate activities.  A balance of child-initiated and teacher-initiated activities is provided.

Our program is concerned with the development of the whole child and his/her physical, social, emotional and intellectual development.

name: ST MARKS CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
At St. Mark's Child Development Center, we provide a loving and stable place for children. Our programs are designed to help each child grow psychically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. We offer Christian child care services for children starting at 6 weeks, pre-school care, before and after school care, summer camps for school age children, and much more.

We treat each and every child as if they were our own. Our loving, dedicated teachers will encourage your child to explore their strengths and interests. Our child care center fosters a safe, nurturing environment -- your child will grow in all aspects of their life. We promote Christian values at our child care center, because we want to help all our children become responsible, thoughtful, and spiritual people.

At St. Mark's Child Development Center, we have proudly served the community in Aurora, IL and surrounding areas for over 25 years. We offer child care, infant care, after-school programs, summer camps, and much more.

name: PEOPLE FOR CHILD CARE - GATES SCHOOL
BATAVIA NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
Batavia Nursery School is sponsored by the Congregational Church of Batavia. It is a non-profit organization with enrollment open to all children, regardless of religious affiliation.

Our emphasis is on basic building blocks for reading readiness, which includes a strong phonetic approach including lots of hand-on experiences in math, science, and literature as well as art and music. Lots of opportunities are provided for gross motor activities, including free play!

name: TOM THUMB COMMUNITY CHILD CARE CTR
TUTOR TIME LEARNING CENTERS, LLC
detail: Every child is different. Every child is one-of-a-kind. So at Tutor Time, every child’s unique set of skills and interests are utilized to his or her advantage in the way that they learn, grow, build self-esteem, and develop their imagination. It’s our job to bring out their best through nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: BETHLEHEM LUTHERAN CHILD DEV. CENTER
detail:
Our Philosophy & Goals:

    Each child is gift from God with his (her) own pattern for development.
    Each child has an individual personality, separate learning style, and family background.
    Spontaneous play and child-initiated activities are an important part of learning and cognitive development.
    Our goal  is to help children develop the skills they will need to succeed in school and throughout life.

name: YWCA CHILD CARE CENTER
detail: YWCA Elgin Commitment Statement: The YWCA Elgin ensures that all children have equal access to comprehensive, high-quality educational programs, including continuous development support. The YWCA Elgin feels early education plays an important role in reducing poverty and inequality by giving all children the opportunity to reach their full potential. When children get off to a strong start, they are more likely to grow up to be contributing members of their communities, helping to create a stronger economy.

name: ELGIN DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
The Elgin Child & Family Resource Center, accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC), has 13 classrooms, a large indoor gym and three separate outdoor play spaces. The center offers Preschool for All along with three dual-language classrooms, bilingual staff and a full-day kindergarten program.

Our Healthy Lifestyles curriculum emphasizes classroom discussions about healthy eating, cooking projects that introduce nutritious snacks, activities that encourage movement and environmental awareness through gardening and recycling.

Elgin Child & Family Resource Center supports family involvement in the center with parent meetings, conferences and parent-child events. The site has an open-door policy, which welcomes families to visit and interact with their child throughout the day.

name: ELGIN COMM COLLEGE-EARLY CHDHOOD LAB SCH
KING OF GLORY LUTHERAN PRESCHOOL
detail: The early childhood years are an important time of development for children. It is our desire to stimulate the "Whole Child"... physically, mentally, emotionally, socially, and spiritually. We will stimulate this growth through hands on activities. This will help foster each child's individual growth so that they may become self-reliant, self-confident, respectful, responsible and able to solve problems. Along with nurturing a love for Jesus and a life long love for learning, the Preschool provides the strong emotional support children need. Each child is treated with love and respect and as a very special child of God.

name: NEW CREATIONS PRE-SCHOOL
detail: At New Creations, every day your child will have the chance to explore, discover, learn, and grow. Through a developmental approach, we help your child prepare for kindergarten. Through a Christian lens, our teaching gives your child the opportunity to learn, socialize, and grow emotionally and spiritually.

name: THE LEARNING TREE CHILD DEVELOPMENT CTR.
detail:
At The Learning Tree, your child is afforded the opportunity to grow intellectually, socially, physically and emotionally.
Activities are varied between quiet and active, structured and non-structured, variety and flexibility being the key to the daily programs.

The Learning Tree has been state licensed since its opening in 1975. Our teachers are college educated in child development and experienced. Your child's first experience with education and school is very important and we are dedicated to providing the best programs available.

name: THE GROWING PLACE OF FOX VALLEY PRESBYTE
detail: The Growing Place Preschool at Fox Valley Presbyterian Church seeks to serve three, four and five year old children and their families by providing a warm, nurturing early childhood education experience.  The atmosphere of our preschool is designed to support your child’s growth and development. The curriculum is carefully planned to stimulate your child’s curiosity and creativity.  Age appropriate activities are used to support all areas of learning including literacy, math, science and social skills.  Experiences, both indoors and out, promote problem solving and questioning and will encourage further investigation in your child's areas of interest.  Our school embodies the values of our faith, but is open to and respectful of all faith traditions

name: HAND IN HAND CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
detail:
Hand in Hand Preschool has been in existence since 1997. A caring, Christian environment is created at the preschool where children develop emotionally, intellectually, physically, spiritually and socially.

Our goal is to enhance each child’s emotional well-being and self-esteem, while stimulating mental growth. Our balanced program provides exploration and discovery in group and individual settings. The teaching staff strives to teach the values of Christian faith to the children through guided conversations, spontaneous teachable moments, Bible stories, and songs. The teachers pray with the children and model Christian attitudes and outlooks through their daily classroom activities.

name: KENSINGTON SCHOOL OF GENEVA
detail:
Kensington School, established in 1969, is a private preschool and kindergarten in the western suburbs of Chicago.  Throughout eight locations, our innovative curriculum, inspirational teaching and extraordinary classroom environments make Kensington a distinctive first school experience for each child.

In a world built just for them, you will find busy, curious and happy children who love being at Kensington. The sound of laughter, the magic of learning and the hum of activity fills every corner of our buildings.

We invite you to visit one of our schools and experience the energy and excitement that has impacted the educational foundation of thousands of children and has become recognized as a praiseworthy model of the finest traditions of early childhood education.

We look forward to the opportunity to introduce your child to Kensington School – a world built just for them.

name: POLKA DOT DRAGON PRESCHOOL/DAYCARE
detail:
Are you looking for a way to prepare your child for primary school? Are you apprehensive about sending your child to just any preschool? Look no further than the professional educators at Polka Dot Dragon Preschool in North Aurora, IL for a superb jumpstart to your child’s elementary school education. Our campus offers many different programs that prepare children for Kindergarten, Preschool, and Pre-K.

Our educational curriculum comprises classes regarding computers, math, and pre-reading skills to ensure that your child excels in elementary school. For your convenience, we have classes available in the morning and afternoon.

At Polka Dot Dragon Preschool in North Aurora, IL, we provide Kindergarten and Preschool for Children ages 3 to 5. If you would like more information about our school, please peruse our Services page.

name: SEE SAW DAY CARE CENTER EAST
ST. MARK'S PRESCHOOL
detail: St Mark's Preschool is a mission of St Mark's Lutheran Church. Our preschool assists families in building a strong Christian foundation for their children, and in cultivating the love of learning about the world in which they live. This is achieved by employing staff that brings the love of Jesus Christ and His teachings into the classrooms each day and by celebrating the inquisitiveness of the young mind.

name: KIDS CONNECTION, INC.
detail: Kids Connection Inc. provides the highest quality preschool and activity programs for participants of  all agesto develop socially, cognitively, emotionally, and physically through play, art, music and other modes of creative activity. Both individual and group programming encourages development of the whole child.
business hours:
Mon - Thu: 8:45 am - 3:30 pm

name: SONSHINE PRESCHOOL
detail: The philosophy of Sonshine Christian Preschool is to provide children with a developmentally appropriate and positive learning environment that is Christian based. Your child will experience a peaceful, respectful, and caring classroom where they can develop socially, emotionally, cognitively, and physically; through exploration activities and open ended questions. Your child will acquire the foundation needed for successful social interaction and future school experiences.

name: Y'S KIDS SCHOOL AGE CENTER-KANKAKEE YMCA
CHILDREN'S CORNER
detail:
Here at Children's Corner, we have been providing a rewarding preschool learning experience for children for the past 35 years. Our intentions are to strengthen every child's developmental skills to the best of their potential. 
    Our programs offer a whole language unit approach to learning and we focus on a unit for two to three weeks. We center our units around various interests and themes.
    All our students will tell you that our number one rule is... HAVE FUN!

name: MBS CHILDCARE CENTER
detail: MBS Childcare Center Inc in Kankakee, IL is a preschool house bringing personalized care with enjoyable activities and our seasoned teachers. We are committed to providing your child an environment that is dedicated to continuous learning and practical training at reasonable costs. We bring students the necessary tools to ensure that they grow and develop to the best of their abilities.

name: DEL VALLE MIGRANT HEAD START, INC.
BOULDER HILL ELEMENTARY/KIDS CONNECTION
detail: Kid’s Connection is a recreational before and after school program offered in cooperation with Oswego Community School District 308. It is implemented by the Park District and held in the cafeterias of District 308 elementary schools with additional use of the gym and playground. The program is available daily from 6:15am until the beginning of class and from the end of class until 6:15pm, Monday through Friday. One to five day options are available for before school, after school, or both!  Kids play games, make crafts, enjoy playground, gym, and computer time, cook, go on field trips, or choose to do homework. After school Out and About trips to different locations in our area will also be offered. Children will have the opportunity to travel to various places including local parks, other Kid's Connection sites, the library, and more during these Out and About trips. Our caring staff will provide plenty of fun in a safe, nurturing environment. Breakfast and afternoon snacks are included.

name: SOUTHBURY ELEMENTARY
detail: Kid’s Connection is a recreational before and after school program offered in cooperation with Oswego Community School District 308. It is implemented by the Park District and held in the cafeterias of District 308 elementary schools with additional use of the gym and playground. The program is available daily from 6:15am until the beginning of class and from the end of class until 6:15pm, Monday through Friday. One to five day options are available for before school, after school, or both!  Kids play games, make crafts, enjoy playground, gym, and computer time, cook, go on field trips, or choose to do homework. After school Out and About trips to different locations in our area will also be offered. Children will have the opportunity to travel to various places including local parks, other Kid's Connection sites, the library, and more during these Out and About trips. Our caring staff will provide plenty of fun in a safe, nurturing environment. Breakfast and afternoon snacks are included.

name: LA PETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.
