name: LOVING ARMS CHILDCARE CENTER
detail:
Loving Arms is a non-profit, Christian childcare facility that offers care for children 6 weeks to 12 years old. Our facility is situated on 25 acres in the Yorkville/Oswego area.

We offer services that include:
    full-day childcare
    full-day preschool
    before and after-school programs
    summer camp
    transportation to several school districts in the area

name: FOX VALLEY FAMILY YMCA
detail:
The human brain develops most between birth to age five, making the preschool years a crucial part of a child's education. Our Early Learning Academy focuses on nurturing your child's development by providing a safe place to learn foundational skills, develop healthy, trusting relationships and build self-reliance.

We use Creative Curriculum and Teaching Strategies Gold Assessment Tool in both our child care and preschool, giving parents the option for full day, full year care OR half day preschool. Our curriculum is research based and focuses on science, social studies and “first hand” experiences as a segue to learning. Children develop confidence, creativity, and critical thinking skills necessary for Kindergarten.

name: COMMUNITY NURSERY SCHOOL ASSOCIATION
detail: Community Preschool is a private preschool in Galesburg, Illinois that was established in 1971.  We are dedicated to giving our students the best education to prepare them for kindergarten.  Our teachers facilitate learning through a variety of hands on experiences.  Children will begin their educational journey in a nurturing environment with a play-based curriculum, while gaining experiences and opportunities to enrich their emotional and social skills.  We offer developmentally appropriate programs focused on each child's unique skills and abilities.  Classes are available Monday through Friday for 3, 4, and 5 year olds.  Community Preschool is a Knox County DCFS licensed facility.  Community Preschool accepts students of all religions, race, ethnicity, and gender.

name: YMCA KID CARE STATION
detail: The Knox County YMCA understands the sensitive needs of your child. We offer a developmentally and age appropriate child care center that ensures your child gets the most out of his/her YMCA experience. CARING and RESPONSIBLE staff are there to provide an enriching experience for your child.

name: KNOXVL 1ST UNTD. METH. CHR. NURSERY SCH.
ANTIOCH'S LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Antioch's Learning Center offers day care, preschool and school age programs in a safe, nurturing environment where your child will get the attention and care that he or she needs. Our ratio of children to teachers is always within state guidelines - and often even lower - to make certain each child receives top-quality care.
We are also state licensed as a daycare center and have met or exceeded all health and safety guidelines.
At Antioch's Learning Center, your child will participate in developmentally-appropriate activities throughout the day, such as:

    Story Time                       
    Show and Tell
    Puzzles and Games
    Computer Time
    Arts and Crafts
    Music
    Pre-Reading Activities
    And much more

You can rest assured that your child will be cared for with the utmost kindness, love and respect. We believe all children are precious gifts and we treat them as though they are our own.
Full-time, part-time and after-school schedules are available.

name: KLC SP DBA CHAMPIONS @ OAKLAND PX
detail: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.
business hours:
Hours of Operation:
Before School: 6:30 am-8:30 am
After School: M, T, TH, F: 3:15 pm-6:00 pm, W 2:30 pm-6:00 pm

name: YACHAD KIDS ACADEMY INCORPORATED
detail:
Our Center is not only a child care center offering quality care and education to children, it is a community within itself. Parents and teachers work together to foster growth and development in our children. We partner with parents through special events, community service and volunteer opportunities, book fairs, picnics, celebrations of staff milestones and achievements, parades, preschool graduations, camp-outs, and everyday communication. Often our alumni come back and volunteer when they are old enough, and sometimes come back years later to teach or enroll their own children in our program.

Our commitment to our families and children includes:
- Quality care and education by knowledgeable staff
- A safe, nurturing environment built on trust and respect
- Growth through observation, assessment and support
- Encouraging individuality, independence and tolerance
- Staff-Parent partnerships
- Individualized attention through primary care-giving
- Assistance for children with special needs
- A diverse Center community that serves all economic levels, ethnic origins and family units

name: MONTESSORI CHILDREN'S HOUSE
detail:
Founded in 1966, the first Deerfield Montessori School was established as a not-for-profit corporation in response to the needs of the community. It is a private, nonsectarian school which has been nationally accredited by the American Montessori Society.

The Riverwoods Montessori School was founded in 1986.  It was followed by a second Deerfield location, the Deerfield Montessori Children's House, and, in 1991 by the Glenview Montessori School.  The four schools together are known as the Deerfield/North Shore Montessori Schools and are professionally managed by the same team.  Each school is staffed with Montessori trained teachers certified by the American Montessori Society and/or the Association Montessori Internationale.  In securing the services of professional and volunteer personnel, the Board strives to secure the person most qualified for the position.  See for yourself what other Montessori parents have found: Montessori educational preparation provides the best start for life.

name: PEPPERMINT STICK PRESCHOOL
detail: We provide an environment conducive to discovering joy in learning and developing a positive self-image. We offer a wide range of enriching and recreational activities in an affortable, nurturing, safe and supportive environment.

name: PRIME TIME 2 CHILDRENS CENTER
detail: Prime Time Children’s Center where we believe children should grow and develop in a friendly caring environment. With a family oriented atmosphere rather than one of a major corporation. Prime Time has been family owned and operated for more than 20 years. We strive to provide a nurturing, safe, friendly arena to begin your child’s education. By choosing Prime Time as your child’s provider you are guaranteeing your child the best possible care.

name: MARY'S PEPPERMINT STICK PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
It?s that sweet and simple. When you give a child the basic tools to love and live, the world becomes a happier place.

Mary's Peppermint Stick Pre-School Mary?s Peppermint Stick is a developmentally appropriate preschool program for three though six year old children. We promote the idea of kindness and peaceful conflict resolution in our school. Since children tend to learn what they live, our teachers are sweet models of such behavior. We believe when seeds of kindness and peace are planted confidence grows. When confidence grows learning expands!

Our program provides the opportunity to play and socialize in a safe environment filled with art, music, movement (both fine and gross motor), and cognitive activities. We are environmentally conscious and love to spend time outside, whether playing on our playground or taking walks in the neighborhood finding the gifts that nature gives us!

name: KLCSP DBA CHAMPIONS @ WOODLAND EL PX
COUNTRY MEADOWS MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
The Montessori philosophy is based upon mutual respect and belief in the child. The basic aim of the Montessori approach is to cultivate the natural curiosity and delight in discovery that is present in all children.

Within each carefully prepared classroom environment, children are able to explore and learn as they acquire the confidence and motivation they need to fulfill their greatest potential. Specially trained Montessori teachers present hands-on educational materials that are specifically designed to support children’s development, build on their interests and nurture their enthusiasm.

name: MONTESSORI CONNECTION EAST
detail: The Highland Park Montessori Schools consist of 4 school campuses located on the beautiful North Shore. Highland Park Montessori, located at 1301 Clavey Road, opened its doors in 1987 and is directed by Carol Ann Lee. Montessori Connection West, located at 1731 Deerfield Road, opened its doors in 1993 and is directed by Norma Morley. Montessori Connection East, located at 330 Laurel Avenue, opened its doors in 1996 and is directed by Patricia Parker. All three of these schools are located in Highland Park. Expanding to the Glencoe community in 2013, Glencoe Montessori located at 556 Vernon Avenue is directed by Carol Ann Lee. The Highland Park Montessori Schools are dedicated to creating an environment where children feel comfortable and are able to learn in a respectful, caring community. To realize this goal we have created Montessori schools where children can be themselves in an atmosphere of freedom and responsibility. They are places where little ones will come joyfully and become absorbed and interested in their learning. We will help the children become creative, competent human beings who are fully aware of themselves, of others and of the world around them. Our goal is to create a love of learning, self-motivation, increased self-esteem, persistence, concentration and habits of inner discipline and order.

name: HIGHLAND PK COMM NURSERY SCHOOL & DCC
detail:
Highland Park Community Nursery School and Day Care Center, affectionately known as “Community” was founded in 1951 by Martha Struve Freeman to provide high-quality, licensed, early childhood education and care to children 2 1/2 to 5 and before school care for elementary school aged children to age 10. We are committed to providing a safe, educational and nurturing environment where children feel safe, cared for and respected.

At “Community”, we believe every child deserves to thrive. Our mission is to provide a safe, caring and enriching environment where:
    Children and families are nurtured and supported and diversity is celebrated.
    Each child’s individual emotional, social, cognitive and physical development is fostered by a skilled and loving staff.
    Play is valued and natural curiosity is encouraged.
    Interpersonal relationships and collaboration are emphasized and seen as avenues for growth and trust.

name: KIDSUCCESS
detail:
We provide quality care for children six weeks through twelve years old. Located in Fox Lake/Ingleside, we have developed specialized curricula to foster positive growth in your child in a caring, secure environment.

Our intention is to encourage children to develop confidence, curiosity, enthusiasm, intellect, and healthy lifestyles. We offer integrated, innovative theme-based programs that incorporate language, academic, social, and gross motor skills that enhance your child's development as an individual.

Please explore our site to discover what KIDSUCCESS has to offer you and your child. You can email us by clicking the envelope icon at the bottom of this page, or give us a call.

name: LAKE BARRINGTON ACADEMY OF STARS, LTD.
EPISCOPAL PRE-SCHOOL OF THE CHURCH OF HS
detail:
One step inside our school will tell you that this is a special place – a place known for its nurturing environment and broad, enriching curriculum. A place where our caring staff strives to foster in students a sense of wonder and curiosity, of joy, empathy, responsibility and service, all while developing an excitement to learn.

Located in the Lake Forest, IL community for nearly 50 years, The Episcopal Preschool (EPS) has become a leader in local early learning programs. We offer a strong curriculum, and a safe and nurturing environment, as well as a lunch option, morning class times and enrichment programs, such as Spanish language.

The Episcopal Preschool is located at The Church of the Holy Spirit. Our mission is to develop each child to his or her fullest potential – intellectually, socially and spiritually.

Start your child on the right path, beginning with The Twos program (age 2.5) and rounding out with our Pre-K program. Check us out, we’re the right choice for early success.

name: THE LEARNING TREE
detail: A child's work is play. Through play children develop coordination, verbalization, thoughts and expressions, establish friendships, become creative and feel a sense of self esteem. Our program hopes to encourage discovery, exploration, and the love of learning in children. The individuality of each child is important to us. We hope to provide an enriching environment where children grow in a caring, safe, stimualting and fun atmosphere. The child care center has been exploring the Reggio Emilia Approach where we respect the child and feel he/she is capable and ready to learn and socialize.

name: TUTOR TIME CHILD CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail: Every child is different. Every child is one-of-a-kind. So at Tutor Time, every child’s unique set of skills and interests are utilized to his or her advantage in the way that they learn, grow, build self-esteem, and develop their imagination. It’s our job to bring out their best through nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: CONDELL DAY CTR - INTERGENERATIONAL CARE
detail: The nationally prominent Condell Day Center for Intergenerational Care provides all-day care for children ages 6 weeks to 6 years old, through our Child Day Care program, as well as all-day care for adults in need of supervised recreation, social, and exercise activities through our Adult Day Services program.  Along with the advantage of high-quality care, this unique center also offers the unequaled benefits of interaction between adults and children, creating an environment in which children and adults can form relationships by learning and sharing together on a daily basis.

name: POKO LOKO EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: Welcome to Poko Loko Early Learning Center, a child care facility located at 1601 Northwind Boulevard in Libertyville, IL. We specialize in infant and toddler daycare, preschool through kindergarten education, and have full-day and half-day programs available. Our certified staff is trained in quality, individualized child care and education for all children. Our curriculum is theme based and includes a variety of topics, thus helping to ensure a well-rounded child ready to enter grade school. We have been family owned and operated since 1965 and serve local Lake-Cook communities such as Libertyville, Mundelein, Grayslake, Round Lake, Gurnee, and Vernon Hills.

name: LIBERTYVILLE COOP NURSERY SCHOOL
detail:
For more than 65 years, LCNS has been recognized as an innovator in preschool education and a pillar in the greater Libertyville area community.  
This level of excellence can only come about when there is a continuing commitment that spans generations and welcomes newcomers.  Our dynamic curriculum is based on fundamentals that have proven to be effective.  Our well-credentialed staff of professional educators make learning personal and fun.
At LCNS, we firmly believe that one of the greatest gifts we can give our children is the passion for curiosity.  The early love of learning develops and serves them throughout their lives.  Our play-based approach capitalizes on the normal curiosity and interests of children.
LCNS is wholly dedicated to providing the encouragement and age-appropriate, child-centered curriculum that provides learning experiences to develop a child’s skills, confidence and overall aptitude.  Learning through active participation brings meaning and interest to a child’s world.
Today, this dedication to innovation and excellence is more important than ever.  As the Illinois elementary education system adopts the new Common Core curriculum standards, our students will need to apply sound learning methods while having confidence in their skills.  In basic terms, Common core is about covering fewer subjects in more depth, so the focus is on repeatable learning skills and the ability to interact and communicate, rather than remembering details from a broad range of topics.
At LCNS, that dovetails with the educational philosophy we’ve advocated for years.  Play-based learning is not only child-centered, but also child-initiated, where teachers act as facilitators within an active, collaborative environment.  Children are guided through developmentally appropriate activities that encourage creative and purposeful investigation.  Play-based learning promotes all areas of development, including language, self-regulation, fine/gross motor skills and cognitive functioning.  In an effort to support all types of learners, we recognize that play is the work of the child.

name: PATTIE CAKE CHILD CARE
detail:
Patti-Cake Child Care Centers emphasize providing a safe and secure learning and development environment for your child. For infants we offer a low child to provider ratio with professionals skilled in early child development and certified in infant CPR. Our child care providers work in teams to ensure adequate monitoring, supervision and nurturing of your child.

Our toddler and preschool programs are for children 15 months to six years old. Our Greenwood, Gurnee, Washington & Libertyville locations serve children up to age 12.

We allow children to explore with age appropriate thematic and planned activities. Preschool programming emphasizes success in kindergarten and beyond. We provide training for our child care givers in nutrition, safety and communicating your child’s progress. We focus on cognitive development skills as well as social, physical and language development.

name: WEE ARE THE FUTURE INC
detail: The Child Care program operates year-around from 6:30 A.M. to 6:00 P.M., Monday through Friday. All children are provided for in safe, well-equipped, cheerful classrooms and a secure stimulating playground. Classrooms are air conditioned and have computers. There are three, specific, individual developmentally appropriate programs. Children who begin at LECC at age three, may continue with the same classmates, through Primary Child Care, Pre-Kindergarten Child Care, Full Day Kindergarten classes and beyond. Children who then attend public school may participate in the Before and After School program. In the Summer, our Full Day program turns into a cultural experience as the children "visit" different global locations each week. The weekly Moon Walk, Field Trip, Guest Visitor, Sign Language Class, and Food Tasting seminar will give your child a something to look forward to every day! The continuity of the LECC program provides peace of mind for parents and comfort for the children who attend. A well balanced hot lunch is served in addition to 2 healthy snacks. Daily lesson plans and comments concerning what your child ate and his or her general conduct are sent home daily.
business hours: 6:30 A.M. to 6:00 P.M., Monday through Friday

name: PITTER-PATTER CHILD CARE TOO
detail: Pitter-Patter Child Care Inc. is a privately owned and family operated child care provider that has been in business since 1994.  Pitter-Patter’s mission is to provide the highest quality, developmentally appropriate care and education for children and their families in a loving and safe environment.  With locations in both Lake Villa and Lindenhurst, we provide care for families throughout Lake County. Aside from basic care, Pitter-Patter also provides a structured environment for children ranging in age from 6 weeks to ten years.  We are a bright and colorful center with a bright and colorful staff that is here to care for, educate, and most importantly, love your children!

name: MATIGIAN PRESCHOOL
detail:
Matigian PreSchool has been involved in shaping the lives of children for more than 40
years. We are proud of this milestone and have been thrilled to teach so many children
within Lake County, Illinois. We attribute much of our success as a preschool to our amazing team of teachers.

We also believe that our teaching philosophy provides children with the important tools they need to thrive and develop intellectually, socially and physically. Matigian PreSchool programs are divided into centers that allow children to learn by exploring dramatic play, language arts, math, science, social studies, music, blocks, transportation, arts and crafts, and outdoor play.

Our foremost objective is for your child to have fun working and playing with his or her classmates. In our opinion, the greatest carry-over value we can leave with your child is that he or she associates learning with pleasure.

name: BD JEWISH ED/EARLY CHILDHD CTR BETHJUDEA
THE GROVE MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
The main objectives of Lincolnshire and The Grove Montessori schools are to provide a carefully planned, stimulating environment which will help children develop within themselves the  foundational habits, attitudes, skills, and ideas which are essential for a lifetime of creative thinking and learning. When engaged in well-structured tasks, the students experience a deep inner satisfaction which leaves them with an overall positive attitude toward learning.

An important aspect of the Montessori experience is the natural, outdoor environment.  Dr. Montessori noted that throughout the different planes of development ages and stages, the child's connection to the natural world helped him better know himself, to understand his place in the world, and ultimately, to find personal fulfillment as he made a positive contribution to the world.

name: BIG & LITTLE CHILD DEV. CENTER II
MUNDELEIN MONTESSORI SCHOOL
detail:
We warmly welcome you and your child to Montessori World of Discovery as we celebrate our 20th anniversary! We understand the great amount of trust you place in us when you enroll your child and strive to create an environment in which your child will thrive.

It is the goal of the school to meet the developmental needs of each child - social, emotional, physical, and intellectual within the context of the "prepared environment" essential to a Montessori education. We commit ourselves daily to meet and exceed these goals.

name: MONTESSORI CHILDRENS HS OF N BARRINGTON
detail:
Built in 1970 with a unique design to serve the needs of today’s children, Montessori Children’s House of North Barrington (MCHNB) is nestled among the rolling hills of the northwest suburbs, where children enjoy a park-like 3-acre campus with educational programs serving children from birth through age six.

At MCHNB, our experienced and dedicated staff helps the child develop an awareness of himself and the world around him. MCHNB students enjoy learning about nature, exploring music, developing their dexterity and coordination through physical activity and exercising their creativity through experiences in art. The child works and learns in an atmosphere of balanced independence and structure within a mixed-age group setting.

Additionally, MCHNB is a lab school of the Seton Montessori Institute, one of the largest Montessori teacher education programs in North America. As a result, the children are exposed to the most current and progressive teaching methods in an authentic Montessori classroom.

name: ALICE'S DISCOVERY CENTER
detail:
ALICE'S DISCOVERY CENTER is the only facility in Lake County open from 6:30 am to 12:00 midnight. Over 1400 children have cared for by Alice and Ron Finch since opening in 1995. Alice's provides a safe and nurturing enviorment that promotes physical, emotional, social cognitive needs for each child. The facility is open to children 6 weeks old to 12 years old for the after school program. Over 160 children currently receive stimulating and enriching experiences at the facility.

Entrepreneurs Alice and Ron employ over 20 people, but also enable and empower countless parents in Lake County to work, live a life of self sufficiency and be a role model for their children.

Ronald and Alice Finch are the recipients of the 2011 Most Influential African Americans of Lake County Entrepreneurship Award. They are recognized for their leadership in business startup. Alice's Discovery Center received the 2010 Child Care Center of the year and the 2009 Small Business of the year Award.

The Finch’s are very active in the community. They are members of the North Chicago Chamber of Commerce and the North Chicago Exchange Club.

name: PAUL K. KENNEDY CHILD CARE CENTER
detail:
The child care center opened its doors on August 15, 1977 and became the first child care center at a VA facility.  The center has grown over the years thanks to the wonderful families which we serve. These include FHCC employees, dependents of the staff and students of the Rosalind Franklin University, military families, and community members. 

The teachers work hard to ensure that the classrooms are organized with developmentally appropriate materials to engage the children in fun and exciting learning activities according to the Illinois Early Learning Standards. Portfolios are kept in each classroom to document the learning that takes place for each child within the classroom.

PKKCCC has a long running, successful history thanks to the dedicated teachers. The teachers incorporate into their day all of the necessary elements to help children learn while having fun at the same time.  Sample activities include art, music, science, dress up, outdoor play, reading, telling stories and block building for all age groups. Through lesson planning, the teachers are able to really individualize the learning each child needs to succeed and grow.  Nutritious hot lunches and healthy snacks are served daily.

Crème's exceptional early learning programs have been featured in both national and local media such as: CBS Evening News, NBC Nightly News, Good Morning America, U.S. News & World Reports, Education Week, The Washington Post, The Chicago Tribune, The Denver Post, The Kansas City Star, The Chicago Sun Times, and Chicago Tribune.

name: DELIA'S DAY CARE
detail:
There's a place waiting for you and your child at Delia's Day Care. At Delia's, they're busy preparing the group rosters so that children will be spending time with other youngsters their own age. This will enhance your child's social skills and enable them to interact well with others.

At Delia's Day Care, they're busy designing the various activities that will provide cultural enrichment, physical exercise, musical education, and world environment awareness. This will broaden your child's intelligence and versatility. 

Delia's is preparing nutritious meals that will nourish and energize your child for the day. This will sustain your child's good health. Delia's is also designing the group sizes so that each caregiver will have the chance to provide one to one care for each child. This will make your child's daycare more effective.

Delia's Day Care is especially busy checking the backgrounds of potential caregivers so that they're sure their staff is well accredited and certified and without police records. This will put smiles on the faces of parents and children alike.

Most of all, Delia's Day Care is waiting for you to call and enroll your child in the loving and caring atmosphere that Delia's is so well known for. Come visit Delia's today and walk away knowing that you've found your child's home away from home.

name: PICKUS INFANT/TODDLER CENTER
detail:
One Hope United is a nonprofit human services agency offering a comprehensive array of prevention, counseling and intervention programs for at-risk children and families in Illinois, Wisconsin, Missouri and Florida.

The agency’s 12 licensed child development centers offer top-quality accessible education to communities throughout Chicago and its suburbs.

One Hope United is committed to excellence in education and results. Our centers served more than 2,100 children in 2012 and met all goals for social/emotional, cognitive, language and physical development.

All of our eligible centers are accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC)–putting them in the top 10 percent of early childhood education programs nationally–and our new Aurora center is in the accreditation process. 

Our dedicated staff believes in collaboration and works with families to create the best outcome for each child. One Hope United educators bring leadership, passion and expertise into the classroom.

THE KID'S PLACE

name: CARING HANDS DAY CARE CENTER
detail: Caring Hands Day Care Center still has some openings for children ages 6 weeks through 5 years old and in our school age High Flyers program serving children before and after school . Caring Hands is the oldest day care center in the area providing a great atmosphere for your children to learn and be nurtured while you are at work. Our curriculum begins at age 2 years and emphasizes building good learning skills and character. We are open from 6:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Call 815/224-4077, ext. 103 to enroll or for more information. DCFS licensed. If you need financial assistance for child care we will help you find the resources you need.

name: STEP BY STEP OTTAWA
detail: We believe that the teacher in an early childhood classroom should teach process vs. product. This Step-by-Step process teaches children valuable problem-solving skills that will help them learn throughout their lives. There should be many avenues of learning through experience and repetition. Learning should be made fun so children will want to learn throughout their life. Step by Step reinforces these learning experiences by using a variety of learning centers. After all, children are not taught, they are exposed to opportunities and experiences and encouraged by the teacher. It is up to us to provide a safe, nurturing environment that children find comfortable so they can explore……

name: JENNINGS-LYON DAY HOME
detail:
The JLDH Board of Directors and staff feel that a developmentally appropriate program of high quality should be available to all children and their families. Such a program should provide activities for each child, based on his or her age and developmental level and should be tailored to meet the needs of the child rather than expecting the child to adjust to the demands of a specific program. It is important that knowledge of growth and development be applied to program practices and that staff be responsive to individual differences. Children’s play is important to intellectual, physical, emotional and social growth. Therefore, child-initiated teacher-supported play is an essential part of our program.
We recognize the importance of adults as role models of acceptable behavior. Children begin to pattern their own ways of acting and reacting after that of the adults they are with each day. We believe the program staff should explore values that promote a sense of self-worth and respect for the child’s own rights as well as the rights of others. We feel this can best be done by providing an atmosphere of acceptance, warmth, and understanding in a safe, nurturing environment. We feel that it is important to develop a program which is sensitive to the needs of children and responsive to the concerns of their family.

name: HOLY TRINITY LUTHERAN PRE-SCHOOL
detail: Holy Trinity Lutheran Preschool opened its doors in 1982.  We are the oldest and largest preschool in the surrounding area, averaging 70 students annually.  We are recognized by the National Lutheran School Accreditation, through a successful 2009 accreditation process.

name: MORNING STAR PRE-SCHOOL
detail:
At MorningStar we invite children to master new skills at their own pace to promote a positive self identity, personal independence, and emotional sense of well being in a warm, loving home like environment.

It is our goal to support children in realizing their highest potential by striving to educate and nurture the whole child -- the physical, the social, the emotional, the creative, the intellectual, and the intuitional self.

We feel it is important to nurture kind and loving feelings as the child's emotional sensitivity develops in acts of simple service from tending the plants and animals to keeping the classroom clean and helping each other physically and emotionally - children learn the highest joy is to care for one another in the spirit of kindness and sharing. Our focus is not only on intellectual education, but also the education of the heart.

Unlike traditional education that only directs the child's attention outward, children are taught to know themselves. All activities are designed to expand the child's sense of oneness and sympathy with all life. Through the study and exploration of nature, they learn to appreciate the many lessons and diversity of life.

At MorningStar we utilize an integrated curriculum approach. Each academic lesson is coordinated with a diverse variety of artistic activities. Students are encouraged to think, reason, question and discover as well as appreciate opportunities for creative expression. To more greatly enhance intuitional advancement, simple meditations, and yoga are practiced daily.

name: BRIGHT BEGINNINGS CHRISTIAN DAY CARE
detail: Bright Beginnings believes in the development of the ‘whole child’. Therefore, the individuality and uniqueness of each family and child is considered in the creation of each aspect of our program. Our program strives to provide experiences for your child that promote and enhance autonomy and individuality.

name: FAITHFUL FRIENDS CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL
detail: Childcare and Preschool for Children aged 6 weeks through 12 years of age. We provide a loving, caring, developmentally appropriate environment in which ALL children can learn and grow. It is the goal of this center to provide the same loving, nurturing care environment children receive at home while also providing individual opportunities for social, emotional, physical, and cognitive growth. We recognize that raising a child takes great effort on everyone's part...it is the responsibility of us ALL!

name: LITTLE LAMBS DAY CARE
detail:
We want your child to know the unconditional love of God through a kind and caring environment centered on love.  Learning is so much easier and productive when a child knows they are safe and loved.  This is our heart.  This is our mission, to help your child grown and learn in a Christ centered classroom.  “Let the little children come to me” - Jesus.  

Little Lambs Day Care was founded in 1982 and is a vital part of the ministries of iWorshipCenter.org.  Our team of Directors led by Gretchen Jones has over 40 years of combined Child-care service.  Little Lambs Day Care is fully licensed through the Illinois DCFS.

Little Lambs Day Care is for children from as young as 6 weeks old through 5 years of age. We use a value based & researched based curriculum and a host preschool program which includes a variety of experiences and activities that will help your child utilize their strengths, develop and grow into their destiny and perhaps most important to them, HAVE FUN!

name: COMMUNITY ACTION HEAD START - DEWITT
detail:
Head Start is our oldest program, serving preschool children and their families from the low-income community in six counties: Piatt, DeWitt, Logan, Menard, Mason, and Fulton.  Head Start centers provide a wide range of services in the following communities: Cisco, Clinton, Lincoln, Petersburg, Manito, Havana, Lewistown and Canton.

Head Start provides opportunity for children to develop socially, cognitively and emotionally with age-appropriate activities and materials.  To meet the physical needs of the growing children, all medical information is reviewed and nutritious meals are served daily.   Screening assessments are completed regarding medical, dental, hearing, vision and speech.  Required referrals are made when deemed necessary.  Educational assessments are conducted to develop individualized programs for the enrolled children.

Parent and community volunteers are always welcome in the classroom.  Volunteers participate in many activities that may include reading stories, playing games, art, music, and cooking activities.

All Head Start sessions operate on a school year calendar similar to public school.  A variety of session options are available ranging in length of class to a home-based option in Menard County.

Early Head Start Early Head Start provides the same educational and health opportunities as our Head Start program but begins with the pregnant mother through 3 years of age. Early Head Start services are available in DeWitt, Fulton, Logan, Mason and Menard Counties! The program is home based which means a Family Educator will visit the participant families in their home once each week for 90 minutes. There is no cost to participate.

detail:

name: ANNA WATERS HEAD START PROGRAM
detail:
Anna Waters Head Start Program is a comprehensive child development program that provides service to the entire family. The program is sponsored by Decatur-Macon County Opportunities Corporation and is in its 46th year of service to children and their families in the Decatur-Macon County area. Head Start is a federally funded program through the Department of Health and Human Services.

Over 378 children attend the program annually. The children attend class 4 days per week (Monday-Thursday). Morning classes are from 8:30 AM-12:00 PM. Afternoon classes are from 12:00 PM-3:30 PM. Fridays are set aside for planning for the upcoming week, parent & staff training, Parent/Teacher conferences, or Home Visits.

There are several components of the program, which include: Education, Disability/Mental Health, Transportation, Health/Nutrition, Social Services, and Parent Involvement.

Head Start classrooms are located at the Effie Oliver Child and Family Center and the New Horizon Family and Child Development Center.

Anna Waters Head Start enrolls children who will be 3 or 4 years of age on or before September 1st of the enrollment year.

name: KID'S CASTLE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Kids Castle Learning Center currently has three locations, two centers in the Decatur area and one in Springfield, Illinois.  Our goal is to provide child care for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years of age, in a safe and educational environment.  We will provide care to all children regardless of race, gender, and economical background.  We strive to be the best Child Care Center in the area.  We take pride in the education aspect of our organization.  

Kids Castleâ€™s hours of operation are 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.  We provide breakfast, morning snack, lunch and afternoon snack to all of the children on a daily basis.  All meals and snack are in accordance with the Illinois State Board of Education regulations through the state food program.  Our menus are posted in each classroom for the convenience of our parents and staff.  Our cooks have their sanitation license and are expected to keep it current.  They also have training in First Aid and CPR.  

As part of our promise to provide the kind of care and education the parents want for their children, we feel that the parents should be involved every step of the way.  We encourage all parents to visit anytime, call as much as they would like and join us for field trips or special family events at the center.  We are here for the children and our parents.  We work together as a team to ensure your childâ€™s safety and education.

With that said, we feel the first five years of childhood are the most important years in development and learning.  We provide a creative educational curriculum that will help children to reach their fullest potential.  The lessons will be developmentally appropriate and will develop the child physically, intellectually, emotionally as well as socially.  We encourage the children to explore and develop at his or her own pace.  

Kids Castle Learning Center takes certain measures to ensure the safety of the children.  Each morning, upon arrival at the center, we require all parents to sign in their children into the Pro Care computer system.  Each individual will be able to choose two four to eight digit codes that will allow them to clock their children in and out each day.  After signing the children into the computer system, we encourage our parents to take their children to their appropriate teacher/classroom.  At the end of the day, upon departure we ask our parents to sign their children out of the computer system before retrieving them from their classroom.  Each individual who is on the pick-up list is required to provide a photo ID before being able to pick up children.  Along with our computer system we also have all of our doors locked at all times.  Parents as well as guests have to check in at the office before proceeding to the classroom where their children maybe.  At this current time our Maynor location has security cameras in the hallways as well as on the outside of our premises.  We take all of these measures to protect the children in our care as well as our staff.

Kids N Fitness students continuously rank at the top of the list in kindergarten readiness. There will be no doubt that your student will leave us with all the skills they need to be successful at the next level.  There are few decisions more contemplated by parents of young children than which day care option to choose – and where to leave their child when they cannot be with him or her. Rest assured that we will welcome you and your child into our family – knowing you expect nothing less than the best. Kids-N-Fitness is committed to providing unparalleled care.

name: SIUE EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail:
The Early Childhood Center (ECC), located on the beautiful campus of Southern Illinois University Edwardsville (SIUE), provides full-day, year round early childhood care and education for the children of students, faculty, staff, and others in the University community, ages two through five.

The Early Childhood Center recognizes the potential of each child and the vital contributions parents make to the Center community. Our philosophy is strongly influenced by the Reggio Emilia Approach. Our work with children and families is grounded in our commitments to nurturing trusting relationships. We are devoted to growing a deeply connected community that allows intellectual and emotional risk-taking. We emphasize a joyful, playful climate with a culture of intellectual inquiry and critical thinking.

Our program is licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services (DCFS), has a 4 star rating from the Illinois Quality Rating System (QRS), and is accredited through the National Association for the Education of Young Children (NAEYC).  We are also proud to be a certified Nature Explore Classroom.

name: LAPETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

name: BARLINA HOUSE PRESCHOOL
detail: The Crystal Lake Park District Preschool program is licensed by the Department of Children and Family Services. Our main goal is to provide children opportunities to participate in activities, which help them develop socially, emotionally, and intellectually into a self-assured child. A semi-structured daily schedule includes art, literacy, music, and play activities, encouraging independence and a desire to learn.   The Crystal Lake Park District Preschool opened in September of 1986, at Veteran Acres Park.Classes began at Barlina House in the fall of 1997. It offers a well-rounded curriculum and ongoing academics. The children in the program meet two or three times a week. Children must be toilet trained and at least three years of age prior to September 1 to participate. Our preschool is open to participants, regardless of cultural, religious, or ability differences. Barlina House complies with the rules of the McHenry County Health Department regarding preschool centers and is licensed through the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services.

name: MY FATHER'S WORLD PRESCHOOL
detail:
Our Mission at My Father's World Preschool is to extend an atmosphere of unconditional love as children begin their first learning experience outside of the home. Our goal is to provide an environment that balances child-initiated & teacher-directed learning opportunities. Each child will be encouraged to gain a concept of him/herself as a unique child of God and gain a basic understanding of the love of God for mankind. We support the family unit and encourage a positive self-image to help stimulate the self-confidence needed to meet all of life's new challenges.

Learning takes place through child initiated free choice activities, group activities and skill-focused learning (fine motor, gross motor, perceptual, memory, problem solving and literacy). Our preschool program is designed to be informal and flexible, but the curriculum and environment are a result of careful planning by the staff. The curriculum is designed to help each child develop socially, emotionally, physically, intellectually and spiritually. At My Father's World Preschool the children have activities, read stories and sing songs about God and Jesus. Christian love and caring is the basis for our program throughout the year.

name: CHESTERBROOK ACADEMY
detail:
What makes our school so special? Imagine children having so much fun in school that they can’t wait to arrive each morning. The excitement of our preschoolers is the result of a team effort. Our teachers are enthusiastic about developing lifelong learners. They genuinely care about children, and have the sensitivity and knowledge to understand a child’s individual developmental needs and learning styles.

Our learning environment is built around children and their needs. It’s a place where children feel safe and ready to absorb what the world has to offer. Our classrooms feature well-equipped learning centers to allow hands-on practice of new skills in smaller groups.  Outdoor time on our playground is built into every day’s schedule, weather permitting.

Nothing is more important than your child’s safety. We maintain records of those authorized to pick up each child. No child is released without proper authorization. All visitors to our school are greeted, asked to sign the Visitor Log and state the purpose of their visit. Picture identification is required from all unfamiliar visitors.

We know that parents play a critical role in their child's educational success and positive attitude toward learning. So, building and maintaining strong parent-teacher relationships is crucial to everything we do here. For children to get the best possible education, everyone needs to be involved. We’re proud that at our school, effective communication among parents, teachers and staff is a way of life.

After you've had the opportunity to review our website, please feel free to contact us to schedule a private tour. We look forward to meeting with you to gain an understanding of your child’s educational needs, and discussing how our school can meet them.

detail: Welcome to New Salem Children’s Center! NSCC was designed and developed in order to provide working families with a reputable child care center. New Salem Children’s Center is dedicated to providing professional, high quality care and preschool education programs, which is designed to facilitate the development and growth of all the children in our care. detail: The purpose and goals of the Hillsboro Community Child Development Center: Our center is a community effort to engage in successfully operating a child care center that focuses on the child’s mental, physical and emotional needs. Our daily activities encourage language, fine and gross motor skills, sensory, cognition, socialization, and positive self-concept. We have developed an educational, social, warm and loving environment for our children.

detail: We offer child care services Monday through Friday from 6:00 AM to 6:00 PM. We have been under the same ownership and established in Litchfield for years. Currently, there are openings at our facility. If you would like more information or would like to schedule a time to come by and check us out, please call (217)324-6237. name: PETER RABBIT DAYCARE OF KICKAPOO, INC
LITTLE TYKES LEARNING ADVENTURES
detail:
Little Tykes Learning Adventures has qualified teachers with their Associates degree in Education or higher and an assistant with at least one year’s experience in each room. We have been trained in CPR and First aid. We also work with Illinois Valley High School in their co-op program. We have been doing this going on 3 years and it has been an excellent experience for the students and preschool.

Little Tykes Learning Adventures is also involved with Mossville School, which is part of IVC school district. Adventures in Aftercare provide a safe and unique Before & Aftercare learning environment. Our number one goal is to keep your student in a fun, motivated, and stimulated atmosphere. After a long day of sitting in a school desk, we realize that your child won’t be interested in another “school session”. Adventures in Aftercare offers a variety of activities such as: arts, crafts, social interaction, games, teamwork and fitness.

Little Tykes belongs to the Illinois State Board of Education Child Care Food Program. This helps us to provide healthy lunches and snacks. Earlier this year we started a Wellness Program. The Wellness policy is for creating a healthy nutrition and physical activity environment for children enrolled in our center.

name: THE SALVATION ARMY CHILD CARE CENTER
detail:
The Salvation Army Child Care Center, located at 210 Spalding Ave., is licensed by the Department of Children and Family Services to provide services to children ages 6 weeks to 5 years of age. 
The comprehensive care offered by the staff of the Child Care Center includes developmentally appropriate activities addressing the social, emotional, intellectual, nutritional, physical and spiritual needs of the children in care.
The Salvation Army Child Care Center also serves as an observation and practicum site for students enrolled in early childhood education courses at Bradley University and Illinois Central College.
A sliding fee scale is provided to insure low-income family participation in the program. The Salvation Army ChildCare Center is accredited by the NAEYC.

name: PALS PRESCHOOL & KINDERGARTEN, INC.
detail: PALS is more than a childcare or daycare center. It's an experience that engages your child in creative play and learning – all with the goal of helping him or her develop into a happy, successful adult. Everything we do at PALS is designed to instill confidence and let children discover and expand on their own individual talents. From the way we uniquely greet each child in the morning to the carefully selected program content and curriculum, PALS maps out a system that encourages your child's maximum development. Plus, our staff is hand-picked and trained in early childhood education – focusing on cultivating strong values, building self-esteem and encouraging individuality – to prepare children for the more structured learning environments of preschool, kindergarten and beyond. We know that everything great must start small, so enroll today and give your child an extraordinary beginning... or request a tour of our safe environment, where creativity and fun run wild.

name: UNIVERSITY UNITED METH CHURCH NUR SCH
detail:
It is our primary goal to help your child develop intellectually, mentally, socially and physically.  The  Nursery School staff has planned a developmentally appropriate curriculum to meet the different
needs, interest, and development level of each child.  Your child will participate in a variety of activities to make this growth possible.   We offer enrichment activities in all classes.

name: SOUTHSIDE CATHOLIC CHILD CARE CENTER,INC
detail:
Our mission is to provide a pathway to learning for all young children. We aid them in developing a positive self-image, and through our child-focused programming, we foster a joy of learning. The opportunity to learn is introduced through developmentally appropriate activities designed to develop skills in the areas of social, physical, and cognitive growth. This opportunity, available to all children and their families, is presented in a warm and accepting environment that encourages a sense of security and trust.

We believe all children deserve an equal opportunity to learn and develop to their greatest potential. Children learn in a positive, nurturing, stimulating environment where they’re encouraged to solve problems, be independent, satisfy their natural curiosities, make choices, and understand the impact their actions have on others. “Thoughtful play” is productive play that develops self-esteem and cognitive skills. We believe that an eclectic approach to education provides the opportunity for a balance between adult- and child-initiated activities.

Parent involvement is an important part of our well-balanced, family-oriented program. We have an open-door policy in which you are welcome to visit at any time and encouraged to participate in any or all activities. Our goal is to become a partner with your family in our common goal of providing quality education and care for your child. We want you to feel comfortable with our staff and free to make suggestions regarding your child’s education and daily routine during his or her membership in our program.

name: FUN N FIT ACADEMY
detail: The mission of Fun N Fit is to provide safe, affordable, high quality child care for the Clubs at River City members and the community. The Fun N Fit Care Center provides a cognitively based program for children ranging from birth to twelve years. We provide a home like environment where children are encouraged to develop at their own pace. Our goal is to instill self-confidence, a desire for learning, and fitness in every child we educate.  The compassionate staff at Fun N Fit is committed to the families we serve, providing support and encouragement.

name: THE EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: The Early Learning Childcare Center exists to provide a safe, developmentally appropriate environment for preschool and school age children. Our focus is to provide a stimulating early care and education experience which promotes each child's social/emotional, physical and cognitive development. Our goal is to support children's desire to be life-long learners.

PINCKNEYVILLE HEAD START
detail: Western Egyptian E.O.C. Head Start is a comprehensive federally funded child development program serving three and four year old children from low income families. name: KAIROS SCHOOL
detail:
The word "Kairos" is derived from a Greek expression meaning "a time filled with God-given possibilities." Kairos School gives youngsters who are two and a half to five years old an opportunity for these meaningful experiences. Our goal is to guide each child in developing their own creative and learning skills, and to foster positive Christian attitudes about themselves and the people around them.

Why a church sponsored school? We believe that as children become aware of their place in the Community of Faith, they become just as conscious of their place in the church family as they are of the family in their home. We stress church doctrine and theology only as we express them through everyday Christian living.

The Kairos School program is planned to create an atmosphere in which each child feels secure in beginning to explore the world outside their home. We encourage each child to grow at their own rate - emotionally, mentally, and scholarly. We believe that each child's self image is underlined by the quality of teaching they receive. This, in turn, determines what they will care and dare to learn.

name: S7HD/HEAD START Cairo Head Start Center
detail:
The Southern Seven Head Start Program is federally funded for children ages 0-5.  The Traditional Head Start Program is for children 3-5 years of age.  Currently we serve 520 children.  An Education Program is provided to help prepare children for transition into Kindergarten.  Health Screenings are provided as well as 2/3 of the nutrients a child needs each day.  Transportation is provided at most locations. 

The Early Head Start Program is specially designed to meet the unique developmental needs of children between the ages of birth to 36 months.  Early Head Start currently serves 70 children and is offered at Cairo Head Start, Mounds Head Start, and Rustic Head Start.  

The Home Based Option is also available which provides an educational experience to the children and families during weekly visits.  Twice per month a special day will be held at the center for all parents and children.

name: CHILD DEV. PARTNERS, LLC DBA KID ZONE
detail:
KidZone Has a Star Three Level Rating through the Illinois Quality Rating System.

The Quality Rating System (QRS) was introduced in July of 2007 by the Illinois Department of Human Services to support child care providers offering high quality care and education to the children of Illinois.

QRS certification is a detailed process. Independent evaluators, using a set of nationally recognized standards, observe in the classrooms and evaluate how the teachers work with the children, how the rooms are set up and what learning materials are available. Director and teacher education and overall administration practices of the center are also reviewed.

name: LITTLE FRIENDS DAY CARE CENTER II
UIS COX CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
The Cox Center is dedicated to reflecting state-of-the-art practices in working with children, families, and other adults. As theorist suggest (Dewey, Piaget, Vygotsky, and Erikson), children learn through their individual experiences with the world.

When children build upon experiences they “construct” knowledge by building new experiences and connecting them to prior knowledge. Young children are active and curious participants in the construction of their knowledge.

Teachers challenge children to make predictions, to explore, to discover, to challenge, to represent and to reorganize their ways of thinking.

Positive development of self-image is important and is a priority in all aspects of program planning. Teachers provide opportunities for learning in an environment of respect and trust between and among all participants, young and old.

In building upon trusting, respectful relationships, teachers learn the needs of individual children and plan for the successful fulfillment of those needs.

The unique qualities of each child and adult are valued and differences are respected. We create an environment of cooperation and collaboration to enhance the process of learning to work together.

Understanding that the child is a member of his/her family, it is our goal to collaborate with family members in creating the best environment for each child. Building an equal relationship between family, child and teacher is an integral part of our philosophy.

name: CARE-O-SEL
detail:
Care-O-sel Child Care and Education sprang literally from a field of dreams. Janice Lowder wanted to create a space where children could learn and discover through play. She purchased the land on the north edge of Virden in the1986.

The center was built that Summer and opened it's doors on October 6, 1986. There were 12 students with 1 teacher and her aid.

A collaboration was formed in 1989 when the Care-O-sel subcontracted the Prekindergarten-At-Risk Program from the local school district. Two teachers and two aides were hired to provide forty-five children with preschool classes. Room for the program at the center was created by moving the school age portion of the program to the Virden elementary school.

All special needs children - three, four and five - moved to the center with their teacher and aid in 1992. This inclusion was supported by the State Board of Education. A teaching team was formed from the child care workers, the prekindergarten staff and the special education teachers.

Accreditation from the National Association for the Education of Young Children was achieved in 1994. The program was one of the 300 in the the State of Illinois to be accredited. This honor attests to the high quality of care and education children and their families receive through the program.

name: JACK & JILL DAY CARE & CHLD DEV CTN. INC
LA PETITE ACADEMY-BELLEVILLE
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

detail:
Welcome to Smart Start Learning Centers!  We offer parents caring,

in their choice of Smart Start Learning Center as a care and education partner 
for their children entrusted to us..

Originally started in Belleville, IL in 2000, we now have a second location in New 
Baden, IL.  Each center provides quality services and both centers are licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services.  We participate in the child care subsidy program sponsored by the Illinois Department of Human Services and administered through the Child Care Resource and Referral program of Childrens Home and Aid Society.  We also participate in the Federal Food Program and 
provide nutritious breakfast, lunch and snacks daily for our program participants.

The Belleville facility provides Preschool For All services through the sponsorship of the Illinois State Board of Education.  Serious budgetary issues of the State of Illinois have prevented us from expanding the service to the New Baden site but we will continue to request support for that service at our newest facilities.

name: ST. HENRY CREATIVE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
OUR MISSION STATEMENT
To provide a home away from home, a loving family atmosphere to help each child grow physically, mentally, spiritually and emotionally.

Established in 1980 the St. Henry Creative Learning Center is a full service Child Care Facility operated in accordance with the provisions of the Child Care Act of Illinois.  The staff is DCFS certified and CPR certified.

The St. Henry Creative Learning Center program is designed to prepare children for Kindergarten by providing them with the necessary skills required for success.  This is accomplished by providing the experiences which develop those skills through such subjects as language, mathematics, art and music, as well as socialization.

We have a well balanced pre school program that is incorporated with the child's care.  We take field trips to many interesting places such as the Zoo, Apple Picking and Pumpkin Picking to name a few.  We host many visitors for entertainment, safety and educational benefits of the whole child.  Among those visitors are, Magicians, Policeman, Dentists and many more.

 Among our many programs available to the children is a Computer Tots Program.  This program introduces the child to the use of the computer.  For a slight up charge, the Lil Tumblers Program identifies the child's need to strengthen and develop their muscles through the use of the “gym on wheels”.  The child is able to climb, exercise and walk on balance beams.

 Special events include a Thanksgiving Dinner prepared with the assistance of the children, a Christmas Program, an Easter Egg Hunt, along with activities to include parents.  Birthday's are celebrated each month with cake, ice cream and all the trimmings.

  In addition to our pre school program we also conduct a Summer Camp for children 6 to 12 years of age.  All of our programs are intended to make the children 's day at the center a pleasant one.

name: DEEDEE'S LRNG ACAD, INC AFTERSCHOOL PROG
BELLEVILLE HEAD START CE
detail:
The SIUE Head Start/Early Head Start Program is a nationally recognized quality early childhood education program that promotes school readiness for children and self-sufficiency for families. Services are available to St. Clair County expectant parents and families of children ages six weeks to five years old.  The Head Start Program currently provides services to 1,314 children and families and the Early Head Start Program serves 188 children and families. Both programs include children with specialized needs and English as Second Language Learners (ESL).

Program options for both programs include part-day (3.5 hours) and (5.5 hours), full-day (7.5 hours) and home-based.

The SIUE Head Start/Early Head Start Program is funded through a $10.7 million grant from the Department of Health and Human Services, the Office of Head Start. 

    The SIUE Head Start /Early Head Start Program is the winner of six National Head Start Association Awards
    The SIUE Head Start/Early Head Start mission is to provide quality individualized comprehensive services that empower children, families, and staff from diverse backgrounds in order to achieve success.

name: SIUE E. ST. LOUIS PROJECT SUCCESS
detail:
Project Success
    The Project Success Program is a comprehensive after-school tutorial enrichment child care program which services children 6-12 years of age. The program is funded by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services. It is designed to serve children who are in protective custody and are referred by the Department of Children and Family Services.
    The program operates after school during the academic school year and all day during summer months. A complete balanced meal is provided for after school program participants. During the summer months, the program provides breakfast, lunch and an afternoon snack.

name: MAGIC BUILDING BLOCK,INC.(FAIRVIEW HGTS)
detail:
At Magic Building Block we appreciate the fact that each child is a unique individual. We expect and accept different temperaments and learning styles of the young children in our care. We believe the children learn through play and that the early childhood years should be happy ones filled with a variety of meaningful hands-on experiences.

We know that an integrated, well-planned program is essential to the social, physical, emotional, cognitive, and creative development of a child. We believe that the teacher of young children is a facilitator for learning. We believe that open communication must exist between home and school to maximize learning possibilities.

It is the responsibility of the educators at Magic Building Block to set up the environment for learning and be active facilitators in the learning process.
business hours: 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. Monday through Friday

name: LIGHTHOUSE LEARNING CENTER OF FREEBURG
detail: Children learn best in loving, nurturing relationships and through everyday experience. At Lighthouse Learning Center, we respect children as individuals. Age-appropriate programs and a staff of dedicated teachers ensure that children get the positive learning experiences they need to grow up happy and confident.

name: H.E.L.P. FOR MOM (CH.DEV-CNTR PRSCHL PRG
detail:
At our preschool we emphasis a readiness program which helps the children develop self-reliance and a positive attitude toward future school work.  We strive to:

Learn to listen, follow directions, have responsibilities, be courteous, orderly and willing to share.

Familiarize the children with the alphabet to know letters by sight and sound, using games, names, flannel board activities, etc.

Know primary colors, shapes and numbers.

Strengthen and improve large motor skills and coordination (skipping, hopping, rhythm, balancing, bouncing balls, etc.).

Strengthen and improve small motor skills (cutting, coloring, writing, drawing – both free hand and directed).

Teach a concept of the world around them through plants, animals, walks, the weather, and other aspects of nature.

Encourage good health and eating habits.

All of the goals of our program will be implemented through a planned program of activities, finger plays, songs, games, and the child’s natural curiosity.  Some repetitive activities are planned because the young child loves to repeat the familiar.  The director will be happy to discuss any questions regarding the program at any time.

name: LEARN WITH US CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
O'FALLON CHILDCARE AND LEARNING CENTER
detail:
We are a not-for profit child care service licensed with the State of Illinois, and a member of the Illinois State Board of Education Food Program. Our commitment to our community includes participation with state supplement agencies including Children's Home & Aid (CHASI), grandparent and foster children support care.

Established in 2002, we have striven to offer the highest quality programs possible. Here you will find a safe, intimate environment that promotes healthy development and growth for your child. We serve children 6 weeks to 12 years of age.

Our qualified Early Childhood Teachers are committed to excellence and age appropriate care for your child. We welcome your telephone calls and your visits to our facility.

Putting your child’s future first!

name: JUST US KIDS CHILD CARE CENTER, INC.
TOGETHER WEE GROW
detail: Together Wee Grow Child Development Center provides affordable daycare in Swansea, IL. Our dedicated team of teachers and aids work closely with parents to ensure the children in our daycare center are kept safe and sound. Other child care facilities will babysit your kids while you are at work but our day care is also a well rounded preschool. Our teachers provide a nurturing environment filled with educational activities that will keep your children motivated and willing to learn. We are happy to provide affordable and low income child care to the hard working parents of Swansea, Shiloh, O'Fallon, and Fairview Heights.

name: DAKOTA LEARN AND PLAY CHILD CARE CENTER
CREATIVE LEARNING CTR. FOR PRE-SCHOOL ED
detail: Prince of Peace Lutheran Church offers one of the longest running preschools in Freeport – the Prince of Peace Creative Learning Center. Morning weekday classes for preschool children are offered throughout the school year. It is a structured early childhood program for ages 3-5. The preschool offers age appropriate developmental activities and hands-on learning experiences in a loving, Christian atmosphere.

name: NICAA HEAD START - ST MARY'S SCHOOL
detail: NICAA HEAD START will enhance the lives of preschool children and their families by providing a high quality program, which includes academics, health, nutrition, parent involvement, and social-emotional related services. We will partner with families as they work to set and attain their goals.

name: AMITY DAY CARE CENTER
detail: Amity is a partnership of volunteers, professional staff and families; working together to ensure that quality early childhood education, school age programs, and parent support services are available to all families on an equitable basis.

name: YMCA CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Serving children ages 6 weeks to 10 years.
A great place for your child to grow.

All enrolled children in our Day Care will be eligible to receive a complimentary YMCA Membership.

All our YCC lead teachers have college degrees. All YMCA staff are trained in CPR, First Aid and bloodborne pathogen procedures to assure the safety of your children!

Our program strives to nurture and encourage the natural curiosity and creativeness of your children. The curriculum is based on the values of the YMCA and the Illinois Early Learning Standards. Our goal is to promote the overall development of children by helping them acquire the proper skills and attitudes to succeed in their education.

name: THE CHILDREN'S CTR OF TAZEWELL CO, INC
HANSEL AND GRETEL DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
At Hansel & Gretel Child Care, our main focus is the well-being of your child.  In other words, we want him/her to thrive in all areas.  We have been providing high quality child care services in East Peoria, IL for children in the surrounding areas for many years.  Our center is noted for its developmentally appropriate program which supports children in their Christian and educational growth.  We utilize a Christian curriculum which outlines weekly theme units that incorporate daily Bible stories and activity ideas to stimulate a young child’s growth physically, emotionally, socially and intellectually.

Our experienced, fully qualified teachers plan their daily classroom activities to include the following program components: language, math/science, art, music, dramatic play, and both fine and gross motor skills.

name: FANTASYLAND NURSERY SCHOOL 3
detail:
The mission of Fantasyland Preschool 3 is to provide young children with a quality environment that is nurturing and stable and where the children are valued and respected. An environment where children learn by doing and are given opportunities and the time to discover, create, and challenge themselves. This evironment will encourage the children to appreciate themselves, others, and their world.
Goal: -To provide the child with a foundation for living including self help skills and develop independence, responsibility, resourcefulness, and self- reliance.
- Build a strong sense of self- worth
- Develop the "whole child" (physical, cognitive, emotional, nutritional, and social)
- To function sucessfully in a structured setting
- To develop trust and respect
- To develop the joy of learning
Our goals are accomplished through children's play

name: FAITHFUL HEART CHILDCARE & DEV CENTER
detail: We are a Christian based childcare in Morton. We have quality teachers and low teacher to student ratios.

name: HEAD START PEKIN CENTER
detail: Head Start is a federally funded preschool and family development program for low income children age three to five and their families. Head Start’s educational program is designed to meet the individual needs of each child. Children attend the program three hours a day Monday through Friday. The curriculum follows both the Head Start Child Outcomes Framework as well as the Illinois Learning Standards. Families are encouraged to participate in a variety of program activities throughout the year.

name: ST. MARK'S LUTHERAN CHURCH CHILD CARE/NS
SUNRISE PRESCHOOL AND CHILD CARE
detail: Sunrise Preschool & Child Care has been caring for children in communities from Anna, IL since 1974. We accept kids from age 6 weeks to 12 years with classrooms that are arranged by chronological age.  We understand just how busy your schedule can be, which is why we've designed our services and scheduling around you! Our caring and experienced staff is here for you and your children Monday through Friday from 6 AM to 6 PM.

name: SU CASA MIGRANT HEADSTART DAY CARE CNTR
LAURA LEE FELLOWSHIP HOUSE HEAD START
COMMUNITY ACTION AGENCY FAMILY CENTER
detail:
More than 10,000 preschoolers have participated in our Agency's early childhood education services in the past thirty-five years. Not only do we provide classroom based education and socialization activities, we also provide comprehensive medical, dental, nutrition, and developmental screenings and interventions for all children. The child's family also receives services in the form of a comprehensive ten-area self-sufficiency scale, from which the family develops goals for their future. Agency staff then works with the family towards accomplishing their goals.

We have classrooms in Danville, Westville, Hoopeston, Watseka, Gilman, and Paxton, and currently serve more than 500 children each year. Our experienced faculty individualizes services for each child to maximize the learning experience. If you know a child who might benefit from our services, or if you would like to volunteer in one of our classrooms, please let us know.
