name: MEMORY LANE PRESCHOOL
detail:
Welcome to our web site! Memory Lane Preschool is an exciting, fun place for your child to come and experience many things. We provide an environment where each child can have a safe place to build their self esteem through encouraging their creativity, curiosity, and social and emotional capabilities.  We appreciate the fresh outlook these children have as we help them discover their world. 

We provide a variety of activities to foster early learning skills such as free play time with friends, carpet time for discussion and songs, and group times for games, science activities, and engaging stories.  Your child will have an opportunity to gain math and reading readiness skills, learn counting and number recognition, and practice sequencing.  Your child will also learn letters and sounds of the alphabet, shapes and colors.  They will participate in craft and art activities, outdoor play and make new friends.

We offer a Monday-Wednesday- Friday class and a Tuesday-Thursday class. You may choose to have your child enrolled all five days. Our preschool time is from 9:00 a.m. to 12:00 noon. For more information about our daily activities, please see the "Schedule" page of this site.

We're happy to provide you with the information you need about Memory Lane Preschool here at the web site. If there are questions you have that are not addressed here, please visit the "Information" page of this site for information on how to contact us.
business hours:
Day Care:  8:30 a.m. - 9:00 a.m
Preschool:  9:00 a.m. - 12:00 p.m.

name: ABC PREK DAY CARE CENTER, INC.
ABINGDON HEAD START
detail:
The Head Start program is a national program that promotes school readiness of low-income children by enhancing their cognitive, social, and emotional development through the provision of health, educational, nutritional, social, family, parent involvement and other services that are determined, based on family needs assessments, to be necessary.
Head Start provides comprehensive child development services to economically disadvantaged children and families, with a special focus on helping preschoolers develop the skills they need to be successful in school. 10% of our families may be from over-income status. Head Start serves at least 10% children with disabilities.

NASHVILLE HEAD START - BCMW COMMUNITY SV

name: IMMANUEL LUTHERAN WEE CARE
detail: We are a non-profit, community-oriented daycare center, caring for children in a loving, Christian atmosphere. Children at Immanuel Lutheran Daycare are lovingly taught and reinforced through demonstration of basic Christian values of respect, compassion and the knowledge of the love of Christ for the children and their families. Child care is available for children aged 15 months through 12 years. Before- and After-School care is also offered; bus transportation is provided to and from Okawville schools. Immanuel Lutheran Daycare aims to provide a comfortable, nurturing environment with age-appropriate curricula that is enjoyable for its children.

name: STAIR STEP LEARNING AND DAY CARE CENTER
WABASH AREA DEVELOPMENT - HEAD START
detail:
Wabash Area Development, Inc. (WADI) Head Start/Early Head Start is a high quality Early Childhood program serving seven counties: Edwards, Gallatin, Hamilton, Saline, Wabash, Wayne and White. Our staff is family-focused—parents and teachers or home visitors work together to plan activities that support each child’s growth and well-being. Services are offered to meet the special needs of children with disabilities. Eligible families have children between the ages of birth and 5 years of age. Pregnant women are also encouraged to apply. Our focus is to serve families with limited income based on federal guidelines. All interested families are encouraged to apply. Staff will work with each family to determine eligibility.

Children participate in a variety of educational activities that encourage a love of learning and lifelong healthy habits. Children receive medical and dental care, have healthy meals and snacks, and enjoy creative play in safe settings, both at home or in the classroom. Head Start helps all children succeed. As a result, children get along with others, solve problems, and are more confident. The children also improve their listening and speaking skills. Children leave Head Start more prepared for kindergarten, excited about learning and ready to succeed.

detail: Morrison Community Day Care was established in 1972 with the intent to provide a high quality of supervised care for children whose parents or guardians are away from home during the working day. name: DIXON HEAD START
detail:
The Tri-County Opportunities Council (TCOC), Community Action Agency, was organized and incorporated in 1965 by a group of interested citizens from Lee, Ogle, and Whiteside Counties for the purposes of investigating the frequency, location, character and cause of poverty; and coordinating efforts to prevent, alleviate and eliminate poverty through the cooperation of public agencies, private organizations, business, industry and interested individuals.

    To strengthen and enable low-income people to become self-sufficient through the attaining of necessary skills, knowledge, motivations and opportunities.
    To better organize a wide range of services related to the needs of low-income people in Bureau, Carroll, LaSalle, Lee, Marshall, Ogle, Putnam, Stark and Whiteside Counties by utilization of innovative approaches and new types of services in attacking the causes of poverty including the support of self-help groups and cooperative efforts of low-income people.
    To encourage participation of low-income people in the planning, development and implementation of programs and projects and in the decision making processes of governmental entities affecting their lives.
    To strenghthen the capabilities of the CAA's community for planning and coordinating federal, state, local and private assistance related to the elimination of poverty by broadening the resource base of programs to include public officials, private organizations, individuals, business and industry.

    To better organize a wide range of services related to the needs of low-income people in Bureau, Carroll, LaSalle, Lee, Marshall, Ogle, Putnam, Stark and Whiteside Counties by utilization of innovative approaches and new types of services in attacking the causes of poverty including the support of self-help groups and cooperative efforts of low-income people.
    To encourage participation of low-income people in the planning, development and implementation of programs and projects and in the decision making processes of governmental entities affecting their lives.
    To strenghthen the capabilities of the CAA's community for planning and coordinating federal, state, local and private assistance related to the elimination of poverty by broadening the resource base of programs to include public officials, private organizations, individuals, business and industry.

name: ROCK FALLS DAY CARE CENTER, INC.
Y.W.C.A. OF THE SAUK VALLEY
detail:
The YWCA of the Sauk Valley's 80 year history is proud and our achievements are countless.  The Sauk Valley area can always count on this YWCA to help make our communities stronger and our future look brighter.

Established in 1924, the YWCA of the Sauk Valley is the women's center in the counties of Lee and Whiteside in northern Illinois.  Our high-quality services do more than just meet the needs of the Sauk Valley area.  They make our communities a better place to live.

Our YWCA is one of more than 200 YWCAs across the USA and many more worldwide that are dedicated to eliminating racism and empowering women.  We all fight for peace, justice, freedom and dignity for all people. 

It's simple.  We make a difference every day.  Come and connect with us and connect with a brighter, stronger future.
business hours:
M - Th: 8 am - 8 pm
Fri: 8 am - 5 pm

name: LITTLE SAINTS OF GOD ACADEMY CORPORATION
DIVINE SHEPHERD LITTLE LAMBS PRESCHOOL
detail: We are a Lutheran Missouri Synod preschool, serving the early childhood needs of the Bolingbrook area for over 20 years.  Our curriculum is thematic in nature following the Illinois Early Learning  and Development Standards, as well as a Christian curriculum to help give your child a good start. Our mixed-age class structure is flexible, allowing for several options to fit your schedule.  A longer 3 1/2 hour day gives your child more time to work on those important pre-kindergarten skills.

name: CREATIVE CHILDREN'S DAY CARE CENTER INC
KIDDIE KAMPUS LEARNING CENTER INC
detail: Thank you for your interest in Kiddie Kampus Learning Center. We know that entrusting your child to outside care can be very scary and stressful. However, making the right choice for your childcare needs just got easier. Kiddie Kampus Learning Center is thrilled to bring both quality childcare and early learning education to your neighborhood. Once you walk through our doors you will immediately see and feel the difference. You will notice that we have created a warm, inviting and fun learning environment. We want your child to feel like Kiddie Kampus is their home away from home. We look forward to the journey of getting to know you and your family.

name: HOUR PLAYHOUSE LLC
detail: At Hour Playhouse our philosophy is modeled after the theories of Piaget, Vygotsky and the HighScope Research Foundation. Often it is said that play is the work of childhood, the primary method for them to learn about themselves, others and their world. Following components of HighScope our teachers are as active and involved as the children are. Supporting learning through active participation teachers and students are partners in shaping the learning experience. Active learning and play is the best way for young children to learn the concepts, skills, and tasks needed to set a solid foundation for later school and life success. Within our program we provide children with a safe secure, active learning environment where they can learn through play.
business hours:
Monday-Thursday 6:30 am-10:00 pm
Friday 6:30-midnight  Saturday-Reservations Only  
Sunday-Reserved for Parties

name: TINI TOTS DAY CARE CENTER INC
detail: If you’re looking for high quality child care, contact Tini Tots Day Care Center of Crest Hill, IL. They strive to provide a nurturing and caring environment where children can grow, develop and learn in a supportive Christian environment.

name: THE LEARNING EXPERIENCE
detail: The Learning Experience enhances the lives of children ages 6 weeks to 5 years. In each contemporary, colorful building children learn in a fun fashion starting with sign language for infants through preschool, technology, early literacy, math, sciences, music, theater, creative arts, dance, physical fitness, nutrition, etiquette and much more. Graduates of TLE are more than prepared to enter Kindergarten and first grade. All the curriculum is proprietary and has been designed, written and published especially for TLE children. At The Learning Experience early learning is an art. We believe that knowledge is like the sky, never ending. Parents dream of the best for their children and at TLE their dreams become reality making those important first years creative, productive, happy and most importantly filled with lots of love.

name: PEACE COMMUNITY PRESCHOOL
detail:
Peace Community Preschool is a non-profit outreach ministry of Peace Community Church. It is our mission to share the love of Christ with young children and their families. We operate as a parent cooperative and all children 3 to 5 years old are welcome. We are state licensed by DCFS and have been operating since 1991. Peace Community Preschool strives to provide a Christian environment where children have
fun, learn about God, and progress in their
academic, social-emotional, communication and motor skills. We provide excellent, age-appropriate curricula that are hands-on and designed to prepare the children for future success in kindergarten.

name: CHILDREN'S COUNTRY CLUB TOO
detail: Welcome to the The Children's Country Club Too Preschool and Daycare The CCC  has been providing high quality child care in the community since 1978.  Thank you for inquiring about our center. We are excited to share all the wonderful features our center has to offer. We invite you to take an interactive tour of the the Children's Country Club Too school. We at Children's Country Club too! are excited about our ADVENTURES IN LEARNING! We hope the information  will be helpful in furthering your knowledge of some of  what we have to offer.

name: SANDBOX PRESCHOOL AND CHILD
detail:
Sandbox Preschool and Daycare has excelled in early childhood development, care and education in the southwest suburbs of Homer Glen, Midlothian, Palos Heights, Oak Lawn, and Orland Park for over 42 years! Our licensed and qualified staff has the patience and experience that has helped us establish our reputation for excellence.

Our programs are designed to maximize your child's learning potential, while fostering their intersocial skills and behaviors. Our curriculum is designed to meet the total needs of the child by coordinating activities and experiences at the child’s pace, allowing space and equipment and movement necessary for overall early childhood development. It is also to provide a balance between quiet and active periods, between academic awareness and comfortable relaxation, always allowing the joy of self-discovery and the pleasure of social interaction.

We have an extremely high return rate, with most of our first-year children returning the following year. And each one of our 7 centers has at least one teacher on staff who themselves were once a Sandbox student!

Sandbox graduates still keep in touch, so we have seen our children grow to become intelligent, confident, and productive adults, many landing successful careers. Visit us today and see what sets us apart.

name: LA PETITE ACADEMY
detail:
La Petite Academy, Inc., is one of the nation’s largest educational daycare companies. We are headquartered in Novi, MI, with more than 450 schools across the country.

Each of our schools is licensed by the state where it operates. In addition, each adheres to the highest standards of safety, security, cleanliness, teaching, and loving care. Every Academy operates the way any good neighborhood business does. We know our community and we understand how best to serve the parents and children who live there.

Along the way, we have become widely recognized for our innovation, leadership, and reputation for excellence in early education. As a pioneer in education-based care, La Petite Academy is matched by very few organizations for the perspective and insight we’ve achieved.

In 2007, we became part of the Learning Care Group, one of the largest providers of early childhood care and educational services in the United States. La Petite Academy is an equal opportunity provider.

We hope you and your child become part of our story, today.

name: BUTTERFLY GARDEN LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Our purpose is to create an inviting, stimulating, cozy environment where learning will be fun; where each child will be treated with the utmost respect all of the time. We will provide an opportunity for each child to have free choice of activities and free choice of playmates. Our purpose is to teach and interact in a manner that will build the child’s self-esteem, cultivate his natural curiosity, develop a love for learning and a positive attitude about school. Butterfly Garden Learning Center will provide a varied, “hands-on” program designed to nurture each child’s social, emotional, physical, and intellectual growth as the child readiness dictates.

Our goal is to give 100% to each and every child, each and every day.

name: JOLIET TOWNSHIP INFANT CHILD CARE CENTER
VILASECA JOSEPHINE CENTER
detail:
Our Mission is to educate the children in an integral formation and create an environment where their spiritual, academic, and moral gifts can grow within themselves and become good Christians and citizens of tomorrow.

The educational community of the Josephine Sisters at the Vilaseca Day Care Center believe in the importance of the human and spiritual formation from infancy, therefore, they are conscious of the special need and attention that each particular child requires in accordance to his/her age, development, sensibility, culture and traditions.

name: GOOD SHEPARD HEAD START
detail: Early Childhood Services is comprised of a variety of services for children under the age of five years and their low-income families. Programs include traditional Head Start and Early Head Start programs as well as childcare. Through these programs children participate in education and social activities, receive help accessing medical and dental care, and have healthy meals and snacks all within a safe and developmentally appropriate setting. Parents play a key role in their child's development and as such become active participants in various aspects of the programs.

name: ABC ALL ABOUT CHILDREN DAY CARE CENTER
MARY SEARS CHILDRENS ACADEMY
detail: Our goal is to meet the total needs of young children with high quality child care, education and guidance. It is extremely important that we create a warm, loving environment so we can instill in our young children a Love for Learning that will last a lifetime. The purpose of Mary Sears Children’s Academy is to meet the total needs of your child, emotionally, physically, socially and intellectually with love and understanding.

name: CATHOLIC CHARITIES ST. JOHN'S HEAD START
detail: These programs include Head Start, Early Head Start, home-based, expectant mothers, and daycare programs for children up to five years-old and their low-income families.  Children participate in developmentally and educationally appropriate activities; receive medical and dental care; have healthy meals and snacks; and enjoy playing indoors and outdoors in a safe setting.  Parental involvement is encouraged.  Family Service Workers are also available to provide support services and assist in securing needed community resources.

name: LITTLE RED SCHOOL HOUSE INC
detail: The Little Red Shoolhouse, Inc. is a professional licensed childcare center. Since 1968, the center has provided responsible childcare for thousands of Joliet and Will County families. Daily programming provides each child the opportunity to explore and develop individually through an appealling blend of active and quiet play indoors, in addition to, the well-equiped fenced outdoor play area. Creative play, crafts, art, science, math, and music, come together throughout the morning preschool program producing an environment where positive social and emotional skills develop.

name: LIVING WATERS CHILDREN'S CENTER
detail:
Living Waters Children's Center
is a ministry of Christ's Mission Church. Open in 2003, it was started to serve the needs of the community by sharing God's love and helping to meet the needs of children and their families by providing the social, educational, and recreational resources they need in a safe, Christian, environment. 

A professional staff utilizes classrooms, homework clubs, games, nutritional meals and snacks, interaction, large indoor and outdoor play spaces, computer lab, sports, crafts, gym, and game room. Children are able to rotate with their teachers through the various learning and recreation areas in a way that allows them to unwind from a busy day, while continuing to expand their learning horizons and relationships.

name: LE BUNNIES CHILD CARE/LEARNING C., INC.
detail:
Welcome to "Le Bunnies" Child Care / Learning Center. The center was established in August of 1996. "Le Bunnies" primary focus is caring and educating children ages six weeks through twelve years of age. We are dedicated to the development of each child and to making a difference in their lives. The center is licensed by Illinois Department of Children and Family Services, governed by the Village of Lansing officials, inspected by the Cook County Health Department and State Fire Marshall bi-annually.

"Le Bunnies" is a home away from home and a place where children can come to have fun, learn, explore, and grow. Parents can trust that their child is safe in a secure, warm, and friendly environment. Security is present throughout the facility by video surveillance in and out of the center, locked doors to the classrooms, lighted outdoor parking facility, authorization cards for parents to select various individuals to pick up their child. Picture identification will be needed to pick up children until staff get to know the parents and families of the child. We request parents and guests to call the center to schedule a tour to learn more about the "Le Bunnies" difference before hopping in. This is for the safety and security of all the children and adults at the center. We have an open door policy for the parents after enrollment of your child.

name: CHILDTIME LEARNING CENTER
detail: We help children learn to love their world. At Childtime, your child gets what he or she needs to develop their best mind, their love of learning, their personality, their bright future. We provide nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: MS. NICKI'S CHILDCARE INC.
detail: It is the philosophy of this center, Ms. Nicki's Childcare, that learning should be a time for fun, security, exploring, and discovery. We strive to nurture and encourage creativity in each child. Ms. Nicki's Childcare's purpose is to provide an atmosphere that encourages social, emotional, physical and intellectual growth and development of each child.

name: GRACE'S PLACE SOUTH
detail: The mission of Grace's Place is to provide a stimulating environment where children have fun while they grow physically, emotionally, and intellectually. We are a resource for our families and our community, working together for the good of our children. Our employees are chosen and recognized for the affection and undivided attention they give each child. Our employees are treated with respect and rewarded for their contributions. Grace's Place is a family where each child is loved and nurtured.

name: GOOD SHEPHERD PRESCHOOL
detail:
Mission:

To nurture children in Christian growth
To maintain a safe environment for children to develop healthy social relationships
To provide the opportunity to become a whole person as intended by God
Good Shepherd PreschoolWe are dedicated to providing a warm, accepting environment that supports the development of the whole child. 
We strive to stimulate each child toward their potential in the areas of spiritual, emotional, social, physical and intellectual development.
We encourage and promote learning in these areas with hands-on learning experiences.

name: THE SHOREWOOD EARLY LEARNING DCC, INC.
detail:
Shorewood Early Learning Daycare Center is a privately owned full-time daycare center owned by Sandra Seemann. The center is open Monday - Friday 6:15am to 6:00pm. There is a full day kindergarten from September through May with school age class during the summer months.

Sandra Seemann began the business as a home daycare in 1985. In 1990 she moved the daycare into a rented facility in Shorewood with the capacity of 50 children ranging from 6 weeks old through 12 years old. In September of 1995 the daycare was moved into a building designed and built for Sandra Seemann. The capacity of the is 114 children ranging from the age of 6 weeks though 8 years old.

Presently, our staff consists of a full time director, seven teachers, eight aides, a cook and a maintenance man. Four of our teachers are director qualified and fill in as needed. The director has an Associates Degree in Early Childhood and is currently working on getting her IDC (Illinois Directors Credential). The kindergarten teacher has a BA in Education, and is state certified. The other teachers have 60 hours of college credit with at least 6 hours in early childhood. The teachers who are director qualified have at least 18 hours in early childhood. All the staff are required to attend 15 hours of service classes each year.

The staff ratios are: Infants 4-1, Toddlers 5-1, 2 year olds 8-1, 3-4-5 year olds 10-1, and kindergarten 20-1.

Currently, all of our rooms (except infants and kindergarten) have double these numbers with an aide assisting the teacher. These are state-regulated ratios. Shorewood Early Learning Daycare is licensed by the State of Illinois.

The Shorewood Early Learning Daycare center considers its program to be of high quality. Each teacher designs their lesson plans to fit the childrens developmental needs. There is a tremendous amount if care and concern to meet the child's needs no matter what the age level. This organization also strives to communicate with parents to make sure that their concerns and needs are being meet.

Balanced, nutritious meals are prepared and served on site. The facility also includes a large area for indoor and outdoor play. Stop by and check us out at 651 Deerwood Drive in Shorewood, Illinois.

name: TUTOR TIME CHILD CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail: Every child is different. Every child is one-of-a-kind. So at Tutor Time, every child’s unique set of skills and interests are utilized to his or her advantage in the way that they learn, grow, build self-esteem, and develop their imagination. It’s our job to bring out their best through nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: MALONES EARLY LEARNING CENTER INC II
detail:
The mission of Malones Early Learning Centers, Inc. is to provide high quality, accessible, affordable, and educational child care services to families. We are a private, service oriented program that offers developmentally appropriate programs for children ages 6 weeks to 13 years, including Pre-kindergarten and Head Start.

We believe that we provide a valuable partnership to benefit children and their families. The services that we provide enhance the physical, social-emotional, and cognitive development of children. The families that we serve and our staff contribute significantly to the economic vitality of our community.

name: ARGYLE PRESBYTERIAN PRESCHOOL
detail: We are pleased to offer a child-centered curriculum which strives to balance social and academic. By providing a fun and nurturing environment, your child is sure to enjoy their first school experience with us. The purpose of Argyle Preschool is to provide an enriched environment, which will encourage children to work out their problems, take a chance, try new things, become involved, and experiment with new ideas. We strive to offer the highest standard of quality instruction that is both educationally and developmentally appropriate for each child. We hope you’ll join us!

name: GRACE LUTHERAN PRE-SCHOOL AND NURSERY
detail:
Purpose
    Provide Christian training
    Provide for the development of perceptual and motor skills
    Stimulate socialization and develop a sense of responsibility
    Discover, encourage, and evaluate a child’s learning ability
    Foster creativity
    Encourage sensitivity to, and understanding of one’s own feelings, as well as those of others

Goals
A variety of developmentally appropriate activities and materials shall be provided to help children achieve the following goals:
Positive self-concept, sense of independence, and wise use of leisure time
    Social skills, ‘including an awareness of community
    Cognitive skills
    Physical development and skills
    Sound health, safety and nutritional practice
    Creative expression
    Respect for diversity
    Develop an appreciation for God’s world and to know what it means to be a child of God

name: ANTZY PANTS PRESCHOOL
detail:
Antzy Pants has themed based play dates for children ages 3- 6 years old.  We believe children learn through play!
Themed play dates include a snack, story time, music and a craft along with hands on activities in our science, math, dramatic play, block and puzzle centers.
Each play date has a limited number of children.  You must reserve your child's spot before the scheduled play date.  Play dates are scheduled ahead of time so it is important to register a week to two weeks in advance.  

Antzy Pants is owned and operated by Mary Rademaker.  Mary has many years of experience working with young children.  She has two of her own, ages 18 and 21.  She was a licensed home daycare provider for 8 years.  Once her children were in school full time she decided to work outside of her home and became a teachers assistant at a local preschool.  Mary has enjoyed working so much at the local preschool for the past three years, she returned to school herself and became Director/Teacher qualified.  She is so excited to be doing something she enjoys and loves!

name: ST. ELIZABETH EARLY CHILDHOOD DEV PROG
CIRCLES OF LEARNING
detail:
Circles of Learning is a not-for-profit, non-sectarian social service agency licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services.

Building on roots of tradition that trace back more than a quarter century, Circles of Learning is recognized as a not-for-profit, state-licensed child care facility with a long and distinguished record of support to local families. Among the services we offer are:

    Pre-school educational services
    Infant/toddler care
    Before and after-school child care
    School-age summer and holiday care
    Nutritional services
    A comprehensive family support system
business hours: 6:00 am to 5:30 pm Monday through Friday

FAIRGROUNDS HEAD START
detail: Head Start has the overall objective of breaking the cycle of poverty by preparing children to be effective learners and by assisting families to achieve greater economic, social and personal self sufficiency in support of their children.

name: HILAND HILL PRE-SCHOOL
detail: We at Hiland Hill Preschool strive to enrich and support the development of young children during the most formative years of their lives. Through hands on learning and exploration your child will have the opportunity to participate in activities which will enhance and build on the experiences they have at home with you, their family.

name: RYAN JURY CHILD DEVELOPMENT LEARNING CTR
ROCKFORD DAY NURSERY EARLY LEARNING CTR
detail:
Organized by a group of Rockford women in 1916, the Rockford Day Nursery had been at its previous location since 1921.  The original object, according to the State Charter of November 26, 1921, was “to maintain a day nursery to assist women in the care of their children and to use its influence in procuring employment for women.”

     Although a new building replaced the original facility in 1951, the purpose had remained basically the same: “to provide day care for young children between the ages of two years and six years, whose parents are employed or in training.”

     In August of 1989, we added a new wing and expanded our services to care for children through 12 years of age.  Our Before and After School and Summer Day Camp Program is designed to fill the needs of children in Kindergarten through 6th grade. 

     In February of 2005 we relocated to 2323 South 6th Street and were able to further expand our mission to care for children 6 weeks to 12 years of age.  The addition of our infant/toddler program fulfills a dream that has been shared by the founders of this organization and those who followed.  To provide quality care for children ages 6 weeks through 12 years of age, whose parents are employed or in training.

name: MT OLIVE EARLY CHILDHOOD CTR
detail:
The mission of the Mt. Olive Preschool is to offer Christ-centered programs which will provide a ministry of love and support to young children and their parents.
 
We are licensed by the Illinois Department of Child and Family Services. We provide opportunities for Christian nurturing so children can grow:
  * spiritually
 * physically
 * socially
 * emotionally
 * intellectually

name: STEPPING STONES CHILD'S CENTER ROSCOE
detail: Stepping Stones is an Illinois state licensed, curriculum based childcare facility focused on providing quality care to the families of the Roscoe, Rockton and South Beloit communities.  In fact, we've set the standard for quality in our area since 1991. We serve children from the ages of 6 weeks to 8 years, with transportation available to and from the Kinnikinnick school district.  We pride ourselves on offering a year round, hands-on, enriched preschool program, to enhance the early learning years as children and families grow and develop towards kindergarten.

name: WINNEBAGO PRESCHOOL INC.
detail: Winnebago Preschool first came into existence in the mid 1970's as a privately owned business, licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family services. In 1987, the preschool was sold to a group of parents who formed a corporation deeming the preschool a non-for-profit business. In 1989, the school moved from a Winnebago church basement to the present building on Benton Street, in order to meet state guidelines. The school is run by a governing Board of Directors made up of parents and/or members of the community. The Board of Directors holds meetings once a month. Parents of the school children comprise the voting membership when choosing the Board of Directors. Elections for the positions are held in October. Parents are encouraged to attend and/or get involved.

name: LITTLE OAKS EDUCATION CENTER
detail:
Pumpkin Place Ltd. opened its Little Oaks facility in 2004 with the dream of filling a community need for a child care center.

Conveniently located off Route 116 in Germantown Hills on a large two acre area. Little Oaks compliments the local public kindergarten program by filling your child’s day with education, enrichment, and fun. Working alongside local educators, Little Oaks has developed a curriculum that perfectly compliments your child’s classroom experience, reinforcing federal common core standards that guide public education nationwide.

Little Oaks is proud to offer you a child care center where the number one priority is your child and you. The staff strives to provide a happy, healthy environment for your child while you are away from them. Open lines of communication are encouraged between the parents and staff to communicate to us your concerns, suggestions, and support.

Among other enriching child care programs, our summer School-Age program means your child will have a fun filled place to meet new friends, and know old friends. Included in our pricing are all field trips, food and art activities.
business hours:
6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m
Infant hours are 7:00 a.m. to 5:30 p.m.

name: ROCKING ROBIN DAY CARE CENTER, INC.
detail:
We are happy that you are interested in information about our school. Every day at Rocking Robin Daycare, we give children many rewarding experiences and the opportunity to grow in a program that has been established for many years and is known for providing a nurturing learning environment.

Our goal is to provide a nurturing atmosphere that is conducive to learning and will provide your child with many different learning experiences. As a daycare center, our curriculum focuses on the importance of play. Play provides your child with the ability to problem solve, get along with others, and discover new things.

name: STATE OF ILLINOIS CHILD DEVELOPMENT CTR
address: 160 N LA SALLE ST STE N200
detail: Our mission statement is to provide nurturing and educational care to children while also supporting families. We focus on developmentally appropriate practices and ensuring that each child’s individuality is embraced to fortify their love of coming to our center to be life-long learners.

name: BRIGHT HORIZONS CHICAGO EAST LOOP
detail:
Bright Horizons is the world's leading provider of employer-sponsored child care, back-up care, education and work/life solutions with more than 700 child care and early education programs and schools for employers and working families across the US, UK, Ireland and Canada. Committed to creating great work environments for its 18,000 employees, the company has been named 12 times as one of FORTUNE magazine's "Best Companies to Work for in America."

Bright Horizons provides work/life solutions for more than 800 leading employers to help them address challenges across key life stages. Programs include child care, back-up care, college counseling, elder care, and work/life consulting.

The first few years of life are an extraordinary time that sets the stage for all the years that follow. Our program for learning creates educational environments that empower children to be confident, successful, lifelong learners and socially responsible citizens. Bright Horizons' innovative programs help children, families, and employers work together to be their very best.

name: CORPORATE CHILDCARE CONSULTANTS LEARNING
detail: Child Care Consultants, Inc. (CCC) is a non-profit child care resource and referral agency serving parents, providers, employers, and the community in central Pennsylvania. Founded in 1987, CCC helps parents find and evaluate child care options and offers financial assistance through the Subsidized Child Day Care Program in York County. For child care providers, CCC offers training and technical assistance. Additionally, CCC works with employers interested in promoting work/life balance, provides leadership to community-supported child care initiatives and advocates on behalf of child care issues at the local, state, and national level.

name: A CHILD'S SPACE EARLY LITERACY & LC, INC
detail:
We believe that PLAY is the WORK of the child!
We honor that work each day by providing children with thematic hands on experiences that encourage discovery learning.
Not a cookie cutter approach in any way! We pride ourselves on being very flexible and accommodating to meet the needs of parents and most importantly, children!
Each classroom and daily learning experiences are crafted to meet each child's needs and designed to encourage learning through centers, which include, dramatic play, art, blocks, sensory learning, literacy and music and movement. Content area lessons  in Science, Math, Early Reading and Social Studies complete the curriculum learning circle while  keeping the activities developmentally appropriate and fun!

Monthly newsletters with home and school connections, biannual child developmental assessments and conferences equip parents and teachers to monitor and support each child’s development and growth.

Regular school events, family gatherings and parent participation opportunities, solidify our belief that educating young children is a partnership effort between parents and the school community.

name: MONTESSORI ACADEMY OF CHICAGO
detail:
At the Montessori Academy of Chicago, we believe that learning is a journey. Our goal is to develop engaged and independent thinkers who embrace community responsibility and leadership. Our teachers strive to inspire a joy of learning, academic success, intellectual excitement, emotional well-being, and creativity in every student. It is with confidence, joy, compassion and leadership that Academy students venture forth on their unique journeys to make a difference in the world.

Our school is a proud member of the American Montessori Society and the Association of Illinois Montessori Schools. We welcome the opportunity to share more about our mission and background. Please also visit us during our informational coffees to learn more.

name: THE SALVATION ARMY TEMPLE HEAD START
detail: The Salvation Army Head Start programs give your child the same advantages every child deserves - a chance to learn in a creative, exciting, educational environment. Your child can begin to learn early and enjoy a healthy start in life by enrolling in one of our child care programs. Services include individually planned pre-school programming, and nutritional, medical and dental care.

name: LITTLE GREEN TREE HOUSE
detail: We are a unique early childhood education center that offers an eco-friendly environment (the first in the Chicagoloand area). We promote a message of positive worldly consciousness and modern learning. Our professional teachers coupled with an eco-friendly environment facilitate the optimal growth and development of the whole child.  Each child's potential will be nurtured through our vibrant learning environment which combines play, carefully designed lesson plans, and thoughtful interactions. Children will build a strong foundation for their future and the future of our world during their time with us.

name: CORDI MARIAN CENTER
detail:
Catholic Charities fulfills the Church’s role in the mission of charity to anyone in need by providing compassionate, competent and professional services that strengthen and support individuals, families and communities based on the value and dignity of human life. In order to remain faithful to our mission, Catholic Charities is guided by these core values: Respect, Compassion, Competence and Stewardship.

Our mission and values are based on the firm foundation of Catholic Social Teaching, a collection of themes developed in papal and other writings over the course of the Church’s history. These themes include the belief that human life is sacred; that all humans have inherent dignity, rights and responsibilities; that social structures like marriage and the family must be supported; that the needs of the poor and vulnerable must be met; and that we must be responsible stewards of God’s creation.

Far from limiting our focus, our Catholic identity and values enable us to truly be “universal,” which is what “catholic” really means. The tenets of Catholic Social Teaching call us to serve everyone, regardless of their belief or background, and to employ anyone, not just Catholics, who commits to our mission. Christ reached out to people of all faiths, and Catholic Charities does the same, with the goal of transforming lives for the better.

name: IT TAKES A VILLAGE AT RIVER CITY, LLC
detail:
At It Takes A Village, our mission is to uncover the gifts and talents of students so that they can reach their fullest potential. We strive to foster a love of learning in each student that comes through our Educational Community. We recognize that each child has unique talents, learning styles and personalities. Our curriculum skillfully weaves artistic and practical disciplines into everyday academics. Students learn to follow their curiosity, to think creatively, and to work both independently and cooperatively with others.

At It Takes A Village we celebrate diversity and strive to instill integrity, compassion and confidence in each child. We provide students with an environment that is safe, supports risk-taking, invites the sharing of ideas, and incorporates the family, culture, and beliefs of each student.

The low staff to student ratio allows each child’s natural curiosity to direct his or her learning and t shape our curriculum. Out highly qualified teachers (Masters and Bachelor Degrees) and staff are committed to working within each child’s comfort zone to ensure optimal social, emotional and educational results. All staff have received satisfactory background checks, drug screenings, and are certified in Pediatric CPR and First Aid.

You can rest assured that your child will be cared for with the utmost kindness, love and respect. We believe each child is a precious gift and we treat them as though they were our own.

name: THE NORTHERN TRUST CHILD CARE CENTER
EASTER SEALS GILCHRIST-MARCHMAN CENTER
detail:
Our Mission Statement:
Easter Seals Metropolitan Chicago maximizes independence and creates opportunities for people with disabilities and other special needs to live, learn, work and play in their communities by providing a lifespan of premier services.

Our Vision Statement:
Easter Seals Metropolitan Chicago will be the recognized leader providing innovative services, creating solutions and changing lives of people with disabilities and other special needs.

name: GADS HILL CHILD CARE CENTER
detail: Gads Hill serves low-income working families who want to make a better life for their children. The Center provides families with a comprehensive support system, facilitating long-term, positive change to the community. Offerings encompass learning support and enrichment, and out-of-school care for children from birth to college. The Center serves families in Chicago’s Pilsen, Brighton Park, North Lawndale, Little Village, and other communities throughout the southwest side of Chicago that often lack educational and childcare resources.

name: FIRMAN COMMUNITY SERVICES DAY CARE
detail:
Founded in 1872 Firman Community Services is a multifaceted human service agency. We offer an array of supportive human services for “at-risk” children and families.

Our dedicated professional staff and volunteers strive to provide holistic human services that are community based and designed to further the development of “at-risk” children and families that we serve toward a more positive lifestyle.

Firman's motto is "The Children Today, Our World Tomorrow."

Therefore, we invite you to review our website and join Firman Community Services’ efforts to enlighten, educate and empower.

We need your help therefore; we hope that after reviewing our website you are inspired to join us in our steadfast efforts, to change the lives of “at-risk” children and families.

We are privileged to be an organization with a history of helping children and families to realize their long term goals via innovative programs and services throughout the greater Chicagoland and Cook county suburban communities.

name: ST JOHN OF GOD CHILD CARE CENTER
LINCOLN PARK PREPARATORY
detail: Our primary consideration is the growth and well-being of each child. We believe in providing an environment where our Toddler, Preschool and Kindergarten children are respected and valued for their contributions to the learning process. Our educated, caring and enthusiastic teachers are valued for their knowledge and commitment to working with young children. Our teachers take into account the individuality of each child and are attentive to specific strengths and needs of the children in their class. Each day, children are invited to participate in a wide variety of discovery and play based activities that are developmentally appropriate. We believe that through play, children experience the joy of discovery and learning for themselves. When a child’s journey at LPP is complete, we feel confident that they will take with them a strong foundation, which includes a positive concept of self and school, along with a love for learning.

name: CORNERSTONE CHILDREN'S LEARNING CTR
detail: We help children learn to love their world. At Childtime, your child gets what he or she needs to develop their best mind, their love of learning, their personality, their bright future. We provide nurturing care and creative learning in a safe environment for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years.

name: FOURTH CHURCH DAY SCHOOL & CHILDREN'S CT
detail:
The Day School strives to engage children in a variety of self-selected and teacher-directed activities. An observer may expect to see children painting and drawing, building and riding, working puzzles and creating peg patterns, hammering nails, pounding clay, sliding and climbing, co-operating and arguing, dancing and singing—real children learning and growing through their play.

The environment encourages wondering, problem-solving, questioning and all areas of cognitive development through play and planned activities. Social development goals include recognizing one’s own needs, feelings, and rights and making these known to others; recognizing and respecting the rights, feelings, and needs of others; and moving through the stages of play to the level of cooperation.

name: BERNICE E. LAVIN CHILDREN'S CARE CENTER
detail: At Bright Horizons®, we’re right there with your child – providing an engaging, flexible curriculum that’s designed to inspire children at every age and stage. Built around extensive research, 21st-century technology, and developmentally- appropriate instruction, our carefully planned curriculum introduces and reinforces concepts of math, science, language, social awareness, environment, art, and health. We look forward to sharing this experience with your family and partnering with you on your child’s educational journey.

name: KINDER CARE LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Welcome to University Children’s Center located in the heart of downtown Chicago! We are very excited to meet with you and your family.
UCC uses an educational program which provides unlimited opportunities for the development of the whole child. We offer a unique curriculum for every age level, centered around developmentally appropriate and fun activities that encourage children to develop physically, intellectually, emotionally, and socially. The center provides priority care for children of Northwestern University faculty, staff and students, Northwestern Medical Faculty Foundation employees, The Rehabilitation Institute of Chicago, and The American Association of Advertising Agencies. University Children's Center is also proud to accept families from the surrounding community.

name: ONWARD NEIGHBORHOOD HOUSE
detail: The mission of Onward Neighborhood House is to empower families and individuals in need to achieve their full potential in a community-based setting through participant-driven educational, recreational and social service programs.

detail: The mission of the Malcolm X College Child Development Program is to prepare students of diverse backgrounds and abilities with the knowledge and practical experience necessary to foster developmentally appropriate experiences for young children.

name: UIC CHILDREN'S CENTER-II
detail: UIC Children's Center is a full-day early childhood program for children of current UIC students, faculty and staff. Children must be between the age of 2 years and 9 months up to 6 years. The program is accredited by the National Association for the Education of Young Children and licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services. All children must be toilet-trained.

name: CHILDREN'S CREATIVE CENTER
detail: The mission of Children's Creative Center is to provide a learning environment to equip each child with the knowledge skills and values to be a successful learner. We are committed to provide a highly comprehensive program that supports the optimal development of the whole child. Our belief is that children learn through play.

name: KC'S ACADEMY & EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION
detail: KC’s Academy of Early Childhood Education is a unique child care facility located on the north side of Chicago in the Lakeview/Wrigleyville area. Our mission is to guide your children through various stages of socio-emotional development, and build a strong foundation for their educational future. Our private ownership allows us to keep competitive classroom ratios, offer organic catering options, and continually reinvest in our facility.

name: PARK VIEW MONTESSORI SCHOOL,III, INC.
detail:
Park View Montessori School, located in Mt. Prospect in Chicago's Northwest Suburbs, strives to create an enriched environment so children are inspired to reach their highest potential using the Montessori philosophy of education. This fosters a strong sense of community and respect for self, others, and the environment, which builds a strong academic foundation for a lifetime of learning.

A Montessori environment is a community in miniature.  The children are expected to follow the rules established in that community.  This is not always an easy task for a pre-schooler. At this age, children believe that they are the center of the universe and everything revolves around their wishes and whims.  When they enter the Montessori environment, they quickly discover that they have to sublimate their wants and desires to those of the larger group.  In this way, they begin learning the important lessons of self-control, sharing, and good citizenship.

name: JEWISH CNCIL FOR YTH SERV-LAKEVIEW
detail: At the Michael R. Lutz Family Center in Lakeview, we provide children with the tools and resources they need to explore and discover the world around them.  Through Preschool and After School Programs to Summer Day Camp, our early childhood education programs are individually tailored to nurture and grow alongside your child.  Using a variety of curricula and activities from arts and imaginative play to science, music and nature, JCYS establishes a love of learning in each child.  Our active Parent Organization also allows you to get involved in our center’s community through parent-only happy hours, Shabbat Family Dinners and afternoon classroom programs.

name: CREME DE LA CREME
detail:
Crème's passion for child development has spawned research to enhance the learning experience in young minds. In fact, Crème has been bringing out the greatness within children since 1980, earning awards for the best daycare and the best childcare centers throughout Colorado, Georgia, Illinois, Kansas, New Jersey, Ohio, Texas, and Virginia.

Crème's exceptional early learning programs have been featured in both national and local media such as: CBS Evening News, NBC Nightly News, Good Morning America, U.S. News & World Reports, Education Week, The Washington Post, The Chicago Tribune, The Denver Post, The Kansas City Star, The Chicago Sun Times, and Chicago Tribune.

name: BRITE NEW MIND DAY CARE CENTER, INC
OUNCE OF PREVENTION FUND-EDUCARE CENTER
detail:
Educare Chicago is a state-of-the-art school that serves approximately 150 at-risk infants, toddlers and preschoolers in Chicago's Grand Boulevard neighborhood.

Launched by the Ounce of Prevention Fund in 2000, Educare works to narrow the achievement gap between at-risk children and their more advantaged peers by giving students the skills they need to succeed in school.

The Educare model the Ounce developed at this Chicago school has inspired the creation of other Educare Schools in the Educare Learning Network.

name: HYDE PARK LEARNING RESOURCE CENTER
detail: At CUDDLE CARE, INC. every child is important. Our program is academically rich and designed to promote your child’s growth and development. Thank you for visiting our website. Activities are planned each day to help children solve problems, express their ideas, and learn about the real world; all crucial skills in preparing for school and life. Our activities include school readiness skills, arts and crafts, games, music, outdoor play and story time.  We offer a Full Time contract, which is for children present at the center over 6 hours per day, and we offer a Part Time contract, which is for children present at the center for less than 6 hours per day.

name: IVY GARDEN AFTER SCHOOL CENTER, LLC
detail: Ivy Garden Learning Center is a revolutionary education provider offering preschool and after-school learning. Unlike traditional daycare centers (which offer zero or minimal academic prep) and Supplemental Education Services (which specialize in helping struggling students), we focus squarely on academic prep and enhancement. We prepare preschoolers (2 to 5 years old) on every dimension for kindergarten in Chicago Public Schools (CPS). We build carefully on school-age children’s academic foundation to ensure they are ready to make the most of their high school years and beyond.

name: HENRY BOOTH HOUSE/NEAR SOUTH HEAD START
detail:
Henry Booth House affectionately known as HBH, is a 501c3, Greater Chicago nonprofit community-based social services agency.  Founded in 1898 by the Chicago Ethical Humanist Society, HBH primarily focused on the development of ethical principles, education and quality of life.  It is named after Judge Henry Booth, the organization's first President.
 
From then until now, we drive this mission via 2 distinct and complementary core competencies anchoring both of these efforts in the education of the family.

First, in Head Start, our overarching goal is to "prepare at-risk children, 3-5 years of age for kindergarten and families for self-sufficiency".  We are the 2nd largest provider of Head Start services in Chicago, educating children at over 43 sites, our impact can be felt throughout 18 aldermanic wards in which we prepare over 1000 children for kindergarten each year.

Second, our Family Health effort, although not clinical in focus, targets the health education of the family from "birth to three":  HBH impacts the lives of over 3000 families each year.

Our goal is to promote the development of the whole child by way of service to the child and their family. We believe that parents/guardians have the most influence in a child’s life therefore we view parents as our partners in the education of their child. Our focus is providing an excellent education through a stimulating early care and education experience which promotes each child’s language, cognitive, physical and social emotional development in order to assist them with the initial steps on their road to becoming productive and influential members of our global society.

name: EZZARD CHARLES NURSERY CENTER
detail: The Ezzard Charles School has a long history of providing families in the community. The school was founded October 1970 by the late Rev. Clyde M. Allison, then pastor of the Emerald Avenue Presbyterian Church, located 6701 S. Emerald Ave., in the Englewood community. The founder selected to name the school after former heavyweight boxing champion Ezzard Charles, because he was a role model in the community and a member of the Emerald Avenue Church. The goal was to instill in the children the courage and confidence that made the man Ezzard Charles a champion. Ezzard Charles School is governed by a volunteer Board of Directors who are responsible for making policy. On August 17th, 1979, the Ezzard Charles School became incorporated as a non-for-profit organization in the State of Illinois. In 1987, the board of Directors purchased the property at 7944-46 S. Ashland Ave. in the Auburn Gresham community which allowed the center to expand its services. In 1994, the Board of Directors opened a Nursery program at 7949 S. Ashland Ave. to service infants and toddlers.

detail:
Welcome to Building Blocks Learning Academy. Choosing a daycare facility to entrust the education and development of your child is the first of many precious decisions parents will make. The fact you have weighed these factors and chosen to enroll your child here is perceived as your vote of confidence in our staff. Rest assured that the staff would not take your trust in us for granted. Each day we promise to allow your child(ren) the freedom to explore their environment. Each day we promise to give them our very best energy and effort. Each day we promise to do everything within our professional power to make your child look forward to returning the next day.

Our goal is to form a partnership with you for a successful experience for both you and your child. Please feel free at anytime to express any comments, questions or concerns regarding our program. Your input is greatly appreciated, as your child's needs are the most important to us. We look forward to a long and loving relationship with your family!

name: OUR LADY OF LOURDES HEAD START
detail:
Catholic Charities fulfills the Church’s role in the mission of charity to anyone in need by providing compassionate, competent and professional services that strengthen and support individuals, families and communities based on the value and dignity of human life. In order to remain faithful to our mission, Catholic Charities is guided by these core values: Respect, Compassion, Competence and Stewardship.

Our mission and values are based on the firm foundation of Catholic Social Teaching, a collection of themes developed in papal and other writings over the course of the Church’s history. These themes include the belief that human life is sacred; that all humans have inherent dignity, rights and responsibilities; that social structures like marriage and the family must be supported; that the needs of the poor and vulnerable must be met; and that we must be responsible stewards of God’s creation.

Far from limiting our focus, our Catholic identity and values enable us to truly be “universal,” which is what “catholic” really means. The tenets of Catholic Social Teaching call us to serve everyone, regardless of their belief or background, and to employ anyone, not just Catholics, who commits to our mission. Christ reached out to people of all faiths, and Catholic Charities does the same, with the goal of transforming lives for the better.

name: LES FINCH LEARNING TREE DAY NURS SCHOOL
detail: Our Mission is to develop children with creative and active minds, educate and support  them in a safe and challenging learning environment as they develop into life-long learners with personal growth.

name: FIFTH CITY CHILD DEVEL INSTITUTE INCORP.
detail: Our mission is to ensure adequate childcare for working parents and area residents in need of preschool for ages two to six years old and after school ages six to twelve. We are dedicated to creating curriculum that builds, “Self Reliance – I Am,” “Self Confidence – I Can,” and “Self Respect – I’m Great,” that encourages each child to explore, make choices and develop age appropriate skills.

name: MCCORMICK CHILD CARE CENTER/SWEDISH COV.
detail:
Welcome to the McCormick Montessori Child Care Center. I am honored to be the program director of this vibrant and dedicated staff at MMCC.  For the past sixteen years I have worked with children from three years old to high school students as a certified Montessori educator, Spanish teacher, Master teacher, Principal, and parent.  It is both rewarding and humbling to observe and guide the child on his/her path as they emerge through each continual stage of development.
  
MMCC is unique; we have a long history of over 27 years of providing an excellent educational environment for our Swedish Covenant Hospital employee’s children of all backgrounds. Our experienced, well qualified staff and our beautiful grounds and classrooms facilitate the development of the whole child; while focusing on their intellectual, physical, social, and global awareness and building up a solid foundation of essential 21st century skills.  We foster self-independence, problem-solving skills, concentration, and joy of learning through the Montessori curriculum.

name: EYES ON THE FUTURE CHILD CARE
LOYOLA UNIVERSITY CHICAGO PRESCHOOL/DC
detail:
The Loyola University Chicago Preschool is dedicated to providing a warm, nurturing environment where children can learn and grow. Our skilled teachers will help your child learn and develop through both group play and adult interaction.

We respect and value the differences in each child as to her or his interests, developmental needs and personality. We appreciate and value different family, cultural, racial and ethnic backgrounds.

Our curriculum is based on the premise that children are naturally curious about their environment and that play is the essential ingredient of our preschool program. Through play in a well arranged and regularly enriched environment, children learn about themselves and their capabilities and develop their cognitive, social and emotional capacities. Teachers create a challenging environment in which information is available through a variety of materials.

In the art area, children may have experiences with color, texture, shape, line and the expressive, creative quality of the materials. Building with blocks introduces the child to spatial, pre-math relationships such as balance and symmetry as well as promoting team effort and using a material to represent an idea. We provide many experiences that foster a love of reading and writing. Through exposure to good literature, "writing" activities, songs and finger plays we set the stage for later reading and writing. The dramatic play area offers opportunities to play adult roles and explore the magical world of fantasy and imagination. We have access to indoor gyms and a beautiful outdoor space that provide opportunities for large motor play.

We provide experiences that foster a sense of self as a competent individual, an internalization of self-control, and a positive pattern of interaction with others. While nurturing and supporting each individual child, teachers also strive to encourage a sense of community and a sense of the importance of each child as a participating member of a group.

We work to ensure a childhood experience filled with adventure, play, investigation and friendship. We care very much about the children and families of Loyola University Preschool.

name: TRINITY UCC DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
Welcome to Trinity United Church of Christ Child Care Centers, Incorporated (Trinity Child Care), where we believe in educating the whole child!  Welcome to Trinity Child Care where we know that educating the whole child means embracing their family!  Welcome to Trinity Child Care, where we value culturally connected curriculum and the principles it embodies! 

At Trinity Child Care, we realize that it is vital for children to know who they are, that they come from greatness and that they as well as their families are to be respected!  We strive to teach our children with love, respect and excellence.  It is our mission to reach each family that enters our doors in a positive and lasting way!

At Trinity Child Care, we recognize that African-centered education should be incorporated into the curriculum to ensure that the curriculum is culturally connected.  It is significant that our children know who they are and where they come from in an effort to develop brilliant scholars who realize they “come from greatness!”

We understand that families may have different schedules and budgets.  Therefore you can choose from our morning and afternoon programs to best fit your needs.
Registration for the new school years begins the first week of February.  To save a place for your child, make sure to register!

detail:

We offer programs for children aged 6 weeks to 12 years including Kindergarten, Pre-kindergarten, Head Start and our Little Bear infant and toddler care and Big Bear Day Camp camp programs. name: TEDDY BEAR DAY CARE CENTER
detail:
Your children deserve the very best in child care. Bring them to a warm, inviting environment that will stimulate their minds and provide a place to grow, learn and play.

Teddy Bear Day Care has six day care centers serving Chicago’s Southwest neigborhoods. We offer programs for children aged 6 weeks to 12 years including Kindergarten, Pre-kindergarten, Head Start and our Little Bear infant and toddler care and Big Bear Day Camp camp programs. Our staff is qualified and dedicated and we care for over five hundred children annually. We provide computers in every classroom, quality nourishing meals including hot lunches and nutritious snacks and have outdoor play areas.

We are proud to be members of the PSO-Illinois’ Child Care Association, ensuring the quality of our facility and caregivers. Our Pre-K and Kindergarten programs are accredited by the state of Illinois. Teddy Bear Day Care Centers are proud partners with Head Start.

name: HENRY BOOTH HOUSE HEGEWISCH HEADSTART CT
detail:
Henry Booth House affectionately known as HBH, is a 501c3, Greater Chicago nonprofit community-based social services agency.  Founded in 1898 by the Chicago Ethical Humanist Society, HBH primarily focused on the development of ethical principles, education and quality of life.  It is named after Judge Henry Booth, the organization's first President.
 
From then until now, we drive this mission via 2 distinct and complementary core competencies anchoring both of these efforts in the education of the family.

First, in Head Start, our overarching goal is to "prepare at-risk children, 3-5 years of age for kindergarten and families for self-sufficiency".  We are the 2nd largest provider of Head Start services in Chicago, educating children at over 43 sites, our impact can be felt throughout 18 aldermanic wards in which we prepare over 1000 children for kindergarten each year.

Second, our Family Health effort, although not clinical in focus, targets the health education of the family from "birth to three":  HBH impacts the lives of over 3000 families each year.

name: HAPPY KIDS PRESCHOOL&DAYCARE CENTER LLC
detail:
We not only take care of your children here. We give them love, warmth, respect and everything they need for best
development.
We want them to be a successful people in the future, so we teach them a lot. Our European style bilingual teaching is based on Jean Piaget's
Theory of cognitive development and epistemological view which are called "genetic epistemology". It means that our children learn by playing.
Our activities are constructed the way children don't even know they learn.
To generalize our philosophy is to:
- help your children fully develop emotionally, physically, socially, intellectually
-  to open your child's creative capability, and help to accomplish full development of your child
- to teach them how to be independent and liable people
- to prepare them for school education
- to help and assist parent's in parenting
In the education process we use Piaget's Theory, so "learning by playing and having fun".
Our preschool classes are adequately prepared for children's age. We teach showing children what's around them so our
curriculum is based on seasons, weather,  holidays and more...
In our curriculum there's everyday time for:
- learning letters, sounds and words (in Polish and English)
- math (numbers, sizes, comparisons, time etc.)
- music - moving and grooving- (singing, dancing...)
- science
- art and a lot more.....
Our three golden rules are:
- to give children respect, warmth and love, so they feel like home
- to make the environment healthy and safe
- To help develop wonderful people
We enroll children 2-6 years old. We are open from 6.30 am to 6.00 pm.
We serve healthy and YUMMY Polish food. We offer 3 full meals a day plus a lot veggies, fruits and milk, for which we
received a State Grant - so you can be sure your child is always full and healthy eating.
We teach Polish and English and show our children the beautiful cultures and traditions of Poland and USA, but also try
to show them the differences and similarities in cultures of people all over the world. We want our children to be the
Citizens of the World.
If your child is not potty trained that's OK - we can help.  With your assistance at home we do our best to let them seat
where they should :-) Just bring the diapers and wipes until your child need it.
We would also like to introduce our teachers who were educated in Poland. They are The Best of The Best. They not
only are teachers - they are friends of yours and your children. They are warm, understanding and patient... and a lot of FUN. 
If you are unable to pay for daycare by yourself, we can help to get you the financial help from DHS.

name: TOTS LAND
detail:
At Tots Land we perceive each child as precious treasure entrusted into our care. Because every child is different, we have an individual approach to each child in our care. Small classes and low student-teacher ratios ensure each child receives individual and caring attention. We offer a safe and stimulating educational environment that promotes children’s development, logical thinking and continual growth of abilities. The school is devoted to help children learn social skills, build their self-confidence and teach them the preliminary skills to explore and experience the world independently from their parents.

Tots Land provides an educational program to meet children needs with concern to their interests, special needs, and talents.

Tots Land ensures opportunities for children to grow and develop through exploration and experimentation with various learning materials and activities.

We provide a wide range of activities that help children enhance physical, emotional, intellectual and social development. Each one engage children’s interest and stimulates their minds and bodies, while providing the foundation that will let them begin their school education successfully.

The focus of Little Learners  Educational Center is to develop a nurturing environment and challenging curriculum that promotes development and focuses on early childhood learning. Many studies suggest that high-quality early learning programs improve the likelihood of
success throughout a person’s life. Here at Little Learners children will receive an excellent educational foundation that will serve as a stepping-stone for their formal education.

name: TODDLER TOWN DAYCARE TOO
detail:
What if all those swipes, taps, and clicks could help your preschooler build the skills necessary for success in school?
We have the way! Through our exclusive partnership with ABCmouse.com, we can offer your family access to award-winning content, online books and interactive activities that are both entertaining AND educational. We encourage all parents to get actively involved in your child’s education. Though children learn many of the key foundational literacy skills in school, repetition and practice at home reinforces those skills. Remember, you can become your child’s most influential teacher. The actions, conversations and connections you have at home are vitally important to their success. Read to your child. Teach him/her about responsible and safe screen time as they navigate online. Help them build confidence, and encourage their curiosity and desire to discover more. When you are excited about learning, they will be too!

detail: Our mission is to educate every child to be an academically successful student, a socially responsible citizen, and a life-long learner.  In order to understand this idea we begin by teaching the necessary knowledge and skills to achieve these goals.  With the appreciation of cultural diversity, within daycares that foster excellence, mutual respect, creativity, and the joy of learning our objective is to aim high.  With our effective, caring, certified and innovative staff, in partnership with our surrounding communities we are here to give quality care.

name: SOUTH-EAST ASIA CENTER
detail:
The South-East Asia Center (SEAC) is a community-based, educational and social service organization building bridges of understanding and cooperation between peoples of Old and New World cultures.

SEAC serves some of the most culturally diverse immigrant neighborhoods in the United States, with over one hundred different languages spoken by residents within its borders. SEAC's Uptown-Edgewater home base is also one of the poorest neighborhoods in Chicago, with some forty-three percent of Uptown children and twenty-six percent of Edgewater children living under the poverty line. Many of the immigrants and refugees served at SEAC come from rural societies where education and literacy are scarce commodities.

SEAC’s more than 30 staff and over 100 volunteers provide cultural, emotional, and educational aid and social services to over 8,000 of the needy each year.

name: ABCD ACADEMY FOR CHILDREN INC
detail:

By applying modern early childhood education methods we provide a developmentally appropriate environment in which our preschoolers learn to speak both Polish and English, acquire the skills of solving problems, making friends, and overcoming difficulties through fun and play activities.

name: CREATIVE SCHOLARS PRESCHOOL
detail:
The owners of Creative Scholars Preschool, Mark and Della Allen, envisioned opening a variety of educationally based facilities in Chicago for families during the early developmental years of one’s life. Being the lucky parents of boy/girl twins, Mark and Della’s initial creation "Fantasy Kingdom" opened fall of 2004 and closed summer of 2012. Fantasy Kingdom was the first of its kind – a "learning through play" facility in Chicago which gave families the flexibility to pop in and play during the week without having to sign up for scheduled classes.

Their next dream came true when Creative Scholars Preschool opened in April of 2009. The environment within is warm and nurturing. With a more structured focus on building the early academics necessary before entering elementary school, Mark and Della and their Director, Mary Ann Fogg created a preschool community for children and their families to be part of a life-long love for learning as well as life-long friendships. Creative Scholars Preschool is a safe, engaging, collaborative place for children to learn. With a focus on early literacy development, fine arts, and foreign language, Mary has developed an appropriate curriculum that enables her teachers to discover the unique gifts each child possesses.

name: LITTLE HANDS AND FEET LEARNING CENTER
SERENDIPITY CHILD CARE INC.
detail:
Serendipity Family Center offers a unique learning experience that all parents want for their children during those crucial developmental years. We take great pride in our family environment, where everyone is treated with respect. We partner with parents and other caregivers to create a personalized academic plan for each child. As parents, we understand the importance of trusting a provider to care for your child. We have researched schools all around the world to design the best educational experience possible and assembled a high quality staff with over 40 years of combined experience that truly care about children.

We recognize environment is crucial for children.  We provide a stimulating environment for children to explore every day. Surrounding children with beautiful classrooms that are safe, fun, and educational is a priority for me as an owner and as a mother.
