Our concentration is to provide a stimulating early child care and an elementary education experience which promotes each child's social, emotional, physical and intellectual development. Our goal is to support and provide the tools to meet a child's desire to be life long learners.

name: MAE'S EARLY CHILD DEV & THERAPEUTIC DCC
LITTLE HANDS LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Thank you for considering Little Hands Learning Center as a preschool for your child. Our mission is to provide superior childcare service in conjunction with an educational and developmentally appropriate program designed to nurture the "whole child" - intellectually, physically, imaginatively, emotionally and socially.  Little Hands Learning Center has developed a curriculum that is designed to challenge and stimulate each child on a daily basis and ultimately instill a lifelong love of learning.  Little Hands Learning Center promotes an environment that fosters critical thinking, problem solving skills, and social development through structured activities and active engaged learning. Our center's commitment to excellence is critical in these formative years for your child's overall growth and development.

The quality of our program will be seen in the professionalism of the staff, classroom environment and the schedule.  We have carefully designed an age appropriate curriculum based on the principle that children need to engage in "hands on" learning activities in addition to classroom teachings to maximize their learning potential. We emphasize “hands-on” learning for children ages two through five with a curriculum focus in reading, math, science, logic, foreign language, music & movement, cultural appreciation and fine arts. The curriculum and program is structured at a pace to accommodate each and every child.

Our dedicated staff consists of passionate, caring, professional and experienced teachers and teaching assistants who have exceeded the necessary criteria in early childhood development. We require that all members of our staff are certified in CPR and First Aid.  We also require that our staff participate in various continuing education workshops to ensure that they are knowledgeable of new teaching techniques which may be incorporated into their teaching practices.

Our program activities are geared toward developing a fun and creative learning environment that is enjoyable for children. Some of our featured activities include Educational Field Trips, Foreign Languages, Global Enrichment Program, Multicultural Activities, Dance, Movement & Music, Math, Science Projects, Computer Lab, Special Guest Speakers, Self Esteem and Social Activities.

We also have a variety of ways in which parents can become involved in the school.  We offer Parent Workshops, Field Trips (parent chaperones are encouraged), Event Planning Meetings, an annual October Funfest, Pretty In Pink Tea Social (for mothers and student), a Father’s Fall Feast (for Dads and student), a Spring Production and a Preschool Graduation. In addition, LHLC offers a Newsletter (A Little Handout - The Official Newsletter of LHLC),  a Parent Bulletin Board which posts all correspondence items sent home for the week, and annual Parent/Teacher Conferences, progress reports & assessments of each child. Little Hands Learning Center practices an open door communication policy and we encourage a healthy dialogue between parents and staff.

We encourage you to set up a private tour or attend an orientation to view the school and learn more about our program, facility and curriculum. If you have any additional questions, please do not hesitate to call us at 773-445-9000 (the Beverly facility) or at 773-324-6500 (the South Shore/Hyde Park facility).

name: THE LEARNING PLACE DAY CARE CENTER

Each child has a unique rate of development, which will not be hurried or forced, but based on the individual child's readiness. This uniqueness will be expected, valued and accepted.

name: WEST AUSTIN DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
The West Austin Development Centers (a not-for-profit organization) is a twenty six thousand square feet, three story, state-of-the-art preschool university. Throughout the twelve spacious classrooms in the facility, children ranging in ages from six weeks to twelve years old can be viewed interacting in a learning, laughing, loving environment. Each classroom suite is equipped with private restrooms for the children.


Our dedicated, experienced and caring staff are committed to building a solid foundation upon which children can stand firmly as they grow into life-long learners. The inpetus to learning begins at the preschool level. It is therefore our mission to make the preschool experience at West Austin a remarkable one. Students steer their way through the learning process with both self selected activities and direct teaching tools and are assisted by instructors. Preschoolers are well prepared for the academic and social challenges they are faced with as they transition from preschool to grammar school once they leave West Austin.

Monthly field trips along with varied monthly academic and cultural themes broaden our student's learning horizons. In a ten month period, students are exposed to ten different cultures and the differences which make those cultures unique. 

Our dietician prepares delicious home style meals that are both nutritionally enriched and lovingly prepared. Students practice family style eating while instructors impart proper manners and nutritional education during meal time. 

The West Austin Development Center is distinctively committed to ensuring that the programs and practices are on the cutting edge of early childhood development. Our programming professionals work diligently and are constantly seeking new ways to promote the best learning experience and outcomes for each of the students.

name: HOME OF LIFE JUST FOR YOU CHILD DEV. CTR

detail: Our educational philosophy is strongly based on the theories and methods of Maria Montessori.  We believe that children construct knowledge based on experiences and that learning is an internal process.  Children learn best from hands-on opportunities.  We encourage children to explore, problem solve, and make sense of the world by using Montessori as well as non-Montessori materials.  Our classrooms contain a variety of manipulative, verbal, mathematical, linguistic, and play based areas.  Activities at Panda Montessori coincide with each child’s developmental needs: cognitive, physical, social, and emotional.  As children move to new levels of ability, there will always be more experiences they can choose in order to develop their skills.

Our programs are purpsely flexible so each child works and plays at his/her own pace. He/she has many choices of activities within the environment planned for his/her age group. Each phase of our program is planned with an objective in mind.

Our objectives are:
    to provide quality developmental care for each child in our program by aiding the child in discovering a sense of his/her own self-worth and knowing that his/her ideas and feelings are important.
     
    to surround the child with staff members of integrity and imagination. Each have a genuine concern for and sensitivity towards all children.
     
    to provide a learning environment for every age group, thus encouraging maximum growth of the whole child. We offer a planned education program for children aged 3–6, using a thematic approach. Art, Music, Dramatics, Science, Literature, Language, Math Concepts, Spanish, Yoga, Motor Development and laughter play a major role in our daily program.

    Classroom activities are balanced between outdoor "free play" and supervised learning centers, designed to stimulate and challenge the young minds and bodies.

name: CHILDRENS LEARNING PLACE INFANT TOODLER
detail:
State agencies regulate and overseethe quality and compliance of every childcare center.  At Children's Learning Place (CLP), our staff is trained to follow systems that have been designed to not only meet state regulatory standards, but where possible, exceed them.

We monitor our staff in order to maintain the highest standards for security, safety and health as well as curriculum education and staff performance.  In addition, our directors are responsible for conducting evaluations monthly.  Routine procedures must be executed by Teachers and Directors to ensure all quality standards are met. They include a daily school check list and elaborate monthly and quarterly evaluations. There are management and staff evaluations, daily communications between the school, the director, and parents.  These evaluations are further critiqued by the executive director.

To further warranty the soundness and inclusiveness of our school, Parent Surveys are utilized in conjunction with Parent-Teacher meetings.  These surveys and meetings are studied to be sure of the effectiveness of our school and, in addition, offer parent feedback.

Definitive rules and regulations govern our school:
    We strive at all times to keep the health and contentment of our children first and foremost.
    Our schools are cleaned and maintained under the strictest of procedures.
    There are routine assessments for compliance of curriculum, procedures and the general happiness and well being of each child.
    We have consistent evaluations for maintenance and cleanliness of our schools.
    Directors and staff are obligated to fulfill their duties to the highest degree.
    We sponsor continuing education courses for our staff.
    We set the standards high and expect those standards to be respected and fulfilled.

detail:
The Ridgeland Apartments and Children’s Program provides subsidized and permanent housing, along with comprehensive support services to homeless victims and survivors of domestic violence.

This two-phase program was established in 1991 and helps families transition from homelessness into permanent housing, while developing skills to maintain an independent and secure lifestyle.

Phase One, is a two-year program that includes subsidized rent and a full range of supportive services for the family. In Phase Two, having successfully completed Phase One, the family can choose to become a permanent tenant paying full-market rent.

name: CENTRO NUESTRO CHILD DEV CTR AFTER SCH
DOUGLAS-TUBMAN CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
The Douglass-Tubman Child Development Center was established in 1983 by a community-based group organized by Reverend Gilbert O. Leigh. It was incorporated as the Douglass-Tubman Youth Ministries, Inc. as a 501 © (3) corporation and remains under the leadership of Rev. Leigh.  Gradually, the organization hired staff and expanded to include a structured afterschool program and employment training.  In 1960, Douglass-Tubman was offered the opportunity to lease a former pre-school and Head Start facility in the Austin community.  The organization converted this facility into a daycare center and undertook further programmatic expansion.  From this 15,000 square foot, single-story facility at Chicago and Lavergne Avenue, The Douglass-Tubman today provides comprehensive family support services, centered on the parent-child relationship.  These services include a licensed full-day pre-school and after-school programs, parent education classes, individual and groups counseling for parents and youth, and a food for needy residents of the Austin and Grand Crossing communities.  Approximately 500 individual families are served each year.  All of those served are African-American and have household incomes at or below the federal poverty level. 

Douglass-Tubman Child Development Center is licensed by the Illinois Department of Human Services. It was the recipient of a United Way Venture Grant, and is funded by the City of Chicago as well as the State of Illinois. The organization maintains working relationships with social service agencies serving the Austin and North Lawndale communities, including the Wholistic Center, Lutheran Family Services, Love in Action Ministry, and Cook County Family Health Center; as well as local schools and area churches.  Douglass-Tubman also coordinates its activities with those of city-wide programs and agencies, such as ChildServ, Prevention Partnership, Catholic Charities, the Chicago Park District, and the Chicago Board of Education.

name: RESURRECTION PRE-SCHOOL AND AFTER SCHOOL
detail: Begun in 1970 by Resurrection Lutheran Church, Resurrection Preschool & Toddler Program has been offering a high quality education for 2-5 year olds since its inception. We also place emphasis on balancing child-selected activities with teacher-directed activities.

Even if your child already goes to preschool, this is a great resource for games and activities when they are at home. Chalk Preschool Online is an excellent booster to their learning. And it can give you some free time!

Educating children is our mission - sharing it with you is our responsibility. We believe it is crucial for all children to have access to an early education program, and that should come at NO COST to you.

name: GATEWAY MONTESSORI SCHOOL INC
detail:
Gateway Montessori is a small, family-centered, not-for-profit educational institution located in a vibrant, multi-cultural Chicago neighborhood. Our school currently has one Community (ages 15 months to 3 years), two Children’s Houses (ages 3 to 6 years), and a Saturday morning Parent-Child Class (3 to 18 months). Our elementary classroom is open and we are currently accepting application. Parents with children who are 6 years old and have previous Montessori experience are welcome to apply.

Part of our commitment to quality Montessori education is to mentor and/or sponsor interested persons in becoming trained. To date, Gateway has helped 6 persons acquire their Montessori diplomas.

All our guides (teachers) hold Montessori diplomas as well as college degrees, and all our classrooms are equipped with AMI-approved Montessori materials. Gateway is licensed by both the Illinois Department of Child and Family Services and the City of Chicago. The Community is accredited by Association Montessori Internationale (AMI), the organization founded by Dr. Maria Montessori herself in 1929.

Gateway Montessori is an excellent school that provides a high-quality, Montessori-based, child-centered education by nurturing the potential within each child.

name: CHICAGO YOUTH CENTERS DOROTHY GAUTREAUX
detail:
The center is named after Dorothy Gautreaux, a Civil Rights activist and community organizer who fought for housing equality. She was an Altgeld resident who was instrumental in winning class-action lawsuits against the Chicago Housing Authority for unjust public housing practices, including segregation. The Gautreaux Program, named after her, was a nationwide initiative that desegregated public housing and improved quality of life for program members.

The center offers quality Early Childhood Education programming. In addition, the center benefits from CYC partnerships that provide additional services, including family literacy, computer literacy and the Chicago Alternative Policing Strategy program. The center’s goal is to give children the tools, support and guidance they need to reach their full potential through the following age-specific programs:

name: CEFS HEAD START 0-5 PROGRAM-EFFINGHAM
detail:
The Head Start 0-5 Program is a free federally-funded program that provides services to pregnant women and children ages 0-5 that meet the Federal Income Guidelines. Currently the program benefits the families of 467 preschool children and 72 pregnant women, infants, and toddlers in the seven counties served by C.E.F.S. Head Start offers both a preschool center-based program for children ages 3-5 and a home-based program for all children and pregnant women.

Head Start is serving children in 7 Illinois Counties including: Christian County, Clay County, Effingham county, Fayette County, Montgomery County, Moultrie County, Shelby County.

Head Start provides comprehensive services which include not only educational experiences, but also focuses on nutrition, medical, dental, and mental health access, and transportation. Because family life is the key to the growth and enrichment of every child, Head Start, together with community partners, offers opportunities and support to improve the entire family’s quality of life. Parents can participate in Head Start by volunteering in the classroom and serving on the policy council and parent committees.

The goal of the Head Start 0-5 Program is to help all children reach their full potential. This is why up to 10% of the Head Start’s enrollment can be “over income” families. Plus, a minimum of 10% of the slots are made available to special needs children regardless of income. The Head Start 0-5 Program is funded by the Department of Health and Human Services.

name: LITTLE RED RIDING HOOD DES PLAINES, INC
detail:
Little Red Riding Hood, Inc. is a daycare center located on Chicago's Northwest side. We opened our doors in 2008 and have been proud to serve our community ever since.

We serve children from ages 2 through 6. Our center offers three spacious classrooms stocked with plenty of toys and educational materials and painted and furnished with bright, cheerful colors that instantly captivate the imaginations of our children. In addition, we have a large, enclosed outdoor play area complete with many slides and climbing areas that we use every single day, weather permitting. We also have a fully-stocked kitchen where we personally prepare every single meal enjoyed by the children of Little Red Riding Hood, Inc. You may find pictures of our center located throughout the other tabs of this website but please do not hesitate to contact us in order to arrange a visit!

The classic tale of Little Red Riding Hood, or "Czerwony Kapturek" as it is known in Polish, tells of a little girl who sets off through the woods to visit her grandmother but is met along the way by a mischievous wolf. The wolf succeeds in learning where the young girl's grandmother lives and is able to arrive there first, devouring the poor grandmother and planning a similar fate for Little Red Riding Hood. Fortunately, a brave hunter intervenes just in time and is able to save both Little Red Riding Hood and her grandmother.

We take this story as the inspiration for our daycare because, much as Little Red Riding Hood was fooled and almost eaten by the wolf because she was travelling alone, our children need our help and guidance in order to thrive as they grow up in the world.

Our philosophy is based on the knowledge that all children are unique, with individual potentials and gifts which must be discovered and nurtured to fruition. We believe that every child has their own time-clock for development, and that the only person they need to be better than is who they were yesterday. Our teachers work hard to determine what each child knows and what they are capable of. Then we create an individualized program especially designed to build upon that knowledge, and to enhance not only the quality of learning, but the love of learning as well.

name: Teenchy Weenchy Daycare & Learning Center Inc.
A CHILD'S PLACE OF VOLO, INC.
detail:
A Child’s Place was founded in March of 2003 by Francine Maze, as an in-home daycare center out of her house in Gurnee, Illinois. After working for two years in the childcare industry, Francine found many flaws with the way in which they were run, and the enormous cost parents were paying for below average child care. Francine’s goal was to create a safe, loving and nurturing environment that made parents feel comfortable while they were at work, while ensuring that their children were educated and prepared for their futures. She also wanted to make sure that this could be done at an affordable price for the working families of the Gurnee community.

In 2005, Francine decided to take her vision to the next level, and located a new building in McHenry Illinois, that would accommodate about 100 children. She knew that by applying the principles she founded the in-home daycare center on to a larger group of families, she could impact many more children. The facility opened in April of 2005 with a few children enrolled. Within weeks, the McHenry facility grew quickly, and reached its capacity by the end of the Spring of 2005. Parents enjoyed the creative environment that was provided and appreciated that the price was reasonable. With the help of a wonderful staff, the McHenry childcare center was the place to be

In 2008, with the help of her husband Brian, Francine decided to expand the business into a new venture in Volo Illinois. Partnering with the Platford Corporation and First Midwest Bank, she was able to improve upon her original building design to a more open floor plan, that was even more inviting to children and families. With a truly unique design, the facility was very colorful, innovative and functional, in order allow each child to reach their potential. The staff was trained on many new techniques on how to care for and educate children of all ages. The Volo facility reached its capacity within the first 4 months of opening.

In 2009, the lease at the McHenry facility was ending and there was an opportunity to build a free standing facility down the road. This building design would take some of the advancements from Volo, and put them into a larger facility, to accommodate the waiting list of families that wanted to register for the program. In November 2009, A Child’s Place officially moved into it’s current home in the Adams Commercial Park. With the help of the State Bank of the Lakes, Francine was able to reach her dream of owning her own facility, and designing it to meet all of the needs of a State of the Art childcare center. The large open floor plan, with a true indoor gymnasium, and new equipment raised the expectation level for the parents of McHenry, who truly deserved it. The children love coming to their “Apple” school every day.

The future of A Child’s Place is very bright. In August of 2011 the Big Hollow School District, in Ingleside Illinois, contracted with A Child’s Place of Volo to run an on-site before and after school program. It is very exciting to know that a school district would trust our center on operating such a project. Currently the Big Hollow program is serving over 30 families in the Fox Lake, Ingleside, Round Lake and Volo communities. Finally these families have a great environment to send their children to before and after school. In addition, by the end of 2011, A Child’s Place once again partnered with State Bank of the Lakes and Quincy Construction to purchase a lot in Antioch for its third location. This center, located on the corner of Deep Lake Rd. and Rt. 173, will serve Antioch, Lake Villa, and the many commuters coming from Wisconsin. The center opened on August 24, 2012 to meet the childcare needs of the area, and allow school-age parents to have a center that is close to home. This center serves the residents of the community and families with children in District 34.We are very excited about the current status and future of A Child’s Place, and want each and every family to know that we understand that your child is your most precious gift in life. Caring for your child is an honor and a blessing. We promise to provide quality care for your child in a safe, healthy, and caring environment. We built our centers based on this principle and will continue to work hard and improve so that your child has the best childcare experience possible. Our motto has always been, and will continue to be “Preparing Children for a Lifetime of Learning”.

detail:

name: LIL' EINSTEIN'S INSTITUTE FOR SCHOLARS
detail:
Welcome to the Lil Einstein’s Institute for Scholars, Early Childhood Center.

My child care business was created with two concepts in mind:

(1) To provide quality childcare for parents working various shift, weekends, and holidays.

(2) Impact the minds of young children with positive reinforcement that will encourage alternatives to the negative factors that plague our neighborhoods.

This center is unique in that it is broken up into 2 phases.  The first phase is for infants to preschoolers. The second will be kindergarten to pre-teen.

Welcome to Phase 1. Both programs include ongoing supervision, program structure, positive youth-adult relationships, and programming with opportunity for independence and choice.

My infant/preschool program is centered around safety, security and sanitation. Hand sanitizers have been mounted in each classroom for staff usage. Disposable Potty Toppers are in each bathroom. These are disposable stick-in-place toilet covers. They are soft, comfortable, blocks wetness  and are oversized which prevents fingers/bottoms from touching germy surfaces.

The entire center (inside/outside) is under surveillance. For an additional fee you will be able to log-in with a secure password and see what is going on in your child’s class.

The core components of this organization bring a wide variety of expertise. My Director has a Master’s degree in Family Services & a Bachelor’s degree in Child Development with an emphasis in Leadership.  She has worked in day care and child enrichment settings and has been trained on everything from, incorporating health education into the classroom to Infant massage.

Some of our goals in caring for your child(ren) are to: provide a safe haven for them to learn life skills thru social interacting and sound doctrine. With the insight they learn here I hope they will be able to use it as a foundation to make smarter and wiser choices. Once you know better you should do better. If we do not invest in our kids now, the streets will gladly do it for us later.

I am licensed by the City of Chicago & The Department of Children and Family Services to operate a center with a maximum capacity of 28-30 children.  The children will be broken up into three (3) groups based on age and level of maturity.

The children will be classified in the following groups:

(1) Infants/toddlers-Sesame Babies (6wks-23mon)their classroom will be decorated with the theme of Sesame Street and majority of their toys will also reflect these characters. (2) 2 yr olds Care Bears (24mon-35yrs) this classroom will be full of Care Bears on the walls and throughout the classroom.  (3) 3-5 yr. olds their classroom  is the theme of Super Why and the Super Readers.

The center is divided into 2 major sections the infants & toddlers will have furniture and toys designed to enhance their visual perception, gross motor skills and the other side will be geared toward learning and fundamental play.  The center is equipped with computers, lab tops, DVD, VCR and CD’s so that they can benefit from various learning sources.

Choosing which type of early education program is best for you and your child is a decision that requires much thought and consideration.

Research and experience clearly shows that a child's early years are the crucial years for development. It’s a time when young children set the foundation for success. Our dedication to the youth of our community is shown through our exclusive approach of incorporating early education into the childcare program. 
 
We invite you to tour our classrooms, visit our teachers, and talk with our parents.  At the end of the day, you know what is best for your child and should feel comfortable and confident in their future.

name: SMALL WORLD LEARNING CENTER INC
detail:
Small World will provide a stimulating learning environment to enable your child to grow and develop emotionally, socially, physically, and intellectually. We will help your child be all that he/she can be.

All staff have approved background checks from the Department of Children and Family Services.

All staff are certified in C.P.R. and First Aid.

Mission
To Nurture children and provide them with the academic, social & emotional skills to be highly successful in school and life

name: SONBEAM CHRISTIAN PRESCHOOL

name: SPENCER LOOMIS
detail: The mission of Community Unit School District 95 is to inspire all students to be passionate, continuous learners and to prepare them with the skills to achieve their goals and flourish as responsible, caring citizens in a global community.

name: SPRINGFIELD URBAN LEAGUE HEAD START
detail:
The mission of the Springfield Urban League is to empower African-Americans, other emerging ethnic groups and those who struggle to secure economic self-reliance, parity, power, and civil rights.

In order to implement the mission of our movement, the Springfield Urban League employs a strategy of:

    Civic Engagement & Social Justice Empowerment
    Economic and Workforce Empowerment
    Education & Youth Empowerment
    Health and Quality of Life Empowerment

name: ST. STEPHEN LUTH CHURCH NURS - PRE-SCH.
STACY JOS DAYCARE
detail:
Staci Jo’s Day Care has a purpose to provide quality pre-school and early childhood development program serving children. The primary goal of the center is to create a fun and safe setting in which children will find warmth, comfort, and understanding, as well as opportunities for movement, exploration, and self-discovery based on individual need, interest, and abilities.

We see children as active learners with the teachers serving as guides and facilitators. Daily activities help children develop a positive self image and experience the freedom to learn and grow with confidence. Children enjoy successes that lead to greater self-confidence and independence. Play is cherished and play spaces are rich with learning opportunities. Children participate in a variety of individual and group activities designed to develop language and cognitive readiness skills enhancing physical, social, emotional and overall growth, skills and attitudes which will increase their ability to succeed in life and school.

Our goal is to build your trust by being professional, dependable, honest and most of importantly caring for your child the same way we would want our own children to be cared for. We feel that good communication between parents and providers is an
important part of quality daycare. Because of this we are committed to creating a strong bond with you and your child, helping to ensure the best start to your child’s life as well as creating a community where parents and teachers learn from each other. Our staff members are partners with our parents working together to meet both the needs of the children and their families.

Our organization values people, the children in our care, their parents, and our employees. We continually work to earn the trust placed in us. We strive each day to be the best provider of early child hood education we possibly can.

name: STAR KIDS MATH AND SCIENCE ACADEMY INC
detail:
Star Kids Math and Science Academy provides quality childcare through nurturing and innovative methods of learning.  Our program strives for excellence by placing quality first. We believe exposing children to a wide range of experience through carefully designed thematic investigations prepares our children to think critically. Our curriculum nurtures the whole child and supports social, emotional, physical and intellectual growth. We inspire a joy for learning…

Our amazing curriculum fosters developmentally appropriate hands-on activities which include:
    Loving structured nurturing environment
    Full Time and Part Time Schedules
    Weekly Themes
    Skilled based Activities
    Sensory-based projects
    Spanish
    Theatrical Dance
    Field Trips
    And much more…

Star Kids Math and Science Academy is located in the heart of Chicago’s Beverly/Morgan Park neighborhood.  We are open Monday – Friday from 7:00am to 5:00pm. We provide quality child care services to children ages 6 weeks to 5 years.  We also offer Before/After care and Summer Camp for children 6 years – 12 years. Individualized tutoring is available for school age children, ask for details.

name: SUNSHINE EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: Welcome to our web site, and thank you for taking the time to learn more about Sunshine Early Learning Center . We offer care for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years. We have an exceptional preschool program for children as young as 2 years of age. Sunshine Early Learning Center is a privately owned facility where your child comes first. We encourage you to get in touch and see for yourself what makes Sunshine different than the others-- we always appreciate your feedback....

name: TAKEDA CENTER FOR CHILD DEVELOPMENT
detail: At Bright Horizons®, we’re right there with your child – providing an engaging, flexible curriculum that’s designed to inspire children at every age and stage. Built around extensive research, 21st-century technology, and developmentally- appropriate instruction, our carefully planned curriculum introduces and reinforces concepts of math, science, language, social awareness, environment, art, and health. We look forward to sharing this experience with your family and partnering with you on your child’s educational journey.

name: THE CHILDRENS PLACE LEARNING ACADEMY INC
THE LEAF PROGRAM DAY CARE CENTER
THE LOVE BUG ROOM
detail: The purpose of The LoveBug Room is to provide quality childcare in a Christian Science atmosphere for families in the Principia/Elsah community.

name: TOTS EXPRESS LEARNING CENTER
detail:
Tots Express Learning Center is a very unique Day-Care. Our children learn from every direction. Tots Express consists of six classrooms, full staff teachers and assistant teachers, full staff kitchen, and toddler sized bathrooms. Our children share in daily activities and fun! Sometimes you will catch students mimicking their teachers and begin teaching other students their colors, days of the week, shapes and other things... Tots Express strives for perfection in the education of our children. 

Tots Express' programs go beyond traditional finger-painting and crayons (through we have this, too) the diversity of artistic experiences we offer our students is worlds beyond anything Chicago has seen before. Our programs nurture each student’s creative vision provide ample opportunity for students to fully explore their creative sides.

Tots Express offers an equally unique and successful academic curriculum with proven results. Our curriculum centers on a hands-on, engaging approach towards learning that creates a fun and emotionally supportive place for everyone that encourages independence and accommodates each student’s personal pace and learning style. Students of all ages have thrived and excelled in academically, with a consistent pattern of students being accepted into many of the city’s top primary schools. 

Tots Express Learning Center’s students are constantly exposed to the wonders of the world around them. There are so many exciting places to explore right here in the city, and we take a great joy in adventuring with our students. From the zoo and the aquarium, to nature parks and museums, to plays for children, Tots students go on field trips every other month of the year.Except August& September.

We also take great care to expose our students to environmentally-friendly learning programs. Living in an urban environment, our students often miss out on seeing much of what nature has to offer, which makes it even more important that every student experiences "The OutDoor Classroom which offers hands-on natural science experiences.

name: WCCS EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail: West Central Community Services, Inc. is the grantee for a Federally funded preschool program called Head Start. We provide children with a center-based school readiness program. Head Start experience has shown that the needs of children vary considerably from community to community and that to serve those needs effectively, programs should be individualized. Head Start is successful in providing children and families with high-quality school readiness programs because we follow very specific guidance from the Office of Head Start. Check them out!

name: WHIZ KIDS NURSERY CENTER INC II
YMCA ORR FAMILY DEVELOPMENT CENTER
detail:
Willow Chicago's doors are open to everyone in our city - wherever you are on your spiritual journey and no matter what your background is – you are welcome here.

Willow Chicago services take place at the historic Auditorium Theatre (50 Congress Parkway) at 10am every Sunday.

name: MONTESSORI CHILDRENS GARDEN
detail:
Located in Aurora, Illinois on the DuPage and Kane County lines, Montessori Children’s Garden has served the Fox Valley area for 15 years.  Our student body is composed of children from many western Chicago suburbs, including Aurora, Naperville, Oswego and Plainfield. We currently offer programs for preschool, kindergarten and elementary age students. We have three 3 to 6 year old classrooms and one elementary classroom. Our preschool and kindergarten programs are available with a half-day, all day or extended day schedule.  Extended day hours are available for all programs, for families in need of child care solutions.  For students that move into other schools beyond their preschool years at Montessori Children's Garden, parents can be assured that their children are well prepared for the curriculum of one of our nearby school districts: 202, 203, 204 and 308.

Although serving the community for much longer as the premier Montessori school in the area, our own “yellow school house” was built in 2004, with the needs of our young students in mind. We are proud of our uniquely talented and caring staff, who averages 11+ years of tenure with Montessori Children's Garden, and has been a cornerstone of our success as a Montessori school. We believe that a strong relationship between the parents and teachers is key to developing a triangle of communication - students, parents, and teachers working together for the benefit of the child.

name: LAMBS OF FAITH EARLY CHILDHOOD CENTER
detail:
At Faith we provide young children, ages two to five years old with a nurturing Christ-centered environment that builds on their intellectual and spiritual development.  We share God’s word with the children and their families through prayers, Bible stories and a once a month chapel service.

Our curriculum allows young children to learn and explore in an environment that provides experiences to build on language and literacy skills, math, science, social studies, fine arts, social/emotional skills and spirituality.  Our teachers have bachelor’s degrees and experience working in the education field.  Our preschool is licensed by the Illinois Department of Children and Family Services.

name: KNOWLEDGE UNVIERSE ED LLC DBA CHAMPIONS
KLC DBA CHAMPIONS@PRAIRIE
detail: Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not.
business hours:
Before School: held at Centennial School
After School: 2:30pm - 6:00pm

name: PICKET FENCE DAYCARE & LEARNING CENTER
detail:
As parents and teachers, we are interested in good beginnings for young children. The right start in early years is an invaluable aid to the continuous unfolding of a child’s potential. Our curriculum is activity based and we believe children learn through play. We would like to offer your child a stimulating, secure and warm home away from home. Children are special and we believe in praising them for their accomplishments. Each child will be able to progress at his/her own pace, so that he/she can experiment, discover and learn. We will also try to develop their independence and confidence. We provide a learning environment with many experiences that children will investigate, represent and share.

Our loving and supportive staff respects each child’s individual capabilities and nurtures their self-esteem and creativity. Through encouraging self-expression, play and initiating choices of materials and equipment, we promote each child’s emotional, social, cognitive, language and physical development.

Our staff also sees family as partners in each child’s development and encourages ongoing communication and input.

name: PIERSON HILLS EARLY HEAD START
detail: We at PCCEO Head Start and Early Head Start identify ourselves as partners in the delivery of high quality, comprehensive services to 781 economically-challenged families and children in Peoria County.

name: KLC DBA CHAMPIONS@CENTENNIAL
detail:
Champions has a great solution for busy working families: activities that combine fun and learning, together with the safety and convenience of a high-quality program right inside your school. Champions offers a variety of group and individual activities designed to keep your child exploring and growing. From art, dramatic play, math and science to problem-solving, language, motor skills and more, we help your child continue learning and developing essential life skills – whether school is in session or not. 

A loving, safe, fun environment with trusted adults to care for and guide your child is the foundation of all our programs. What sets us apart are our highly trained educators who deliver the thorough and engaging Early Foundations curriculum for infants through 6-year-olds. While your child is feeling cared for and having fun, our professional teachers are skillfully fostering your child's cognitive, emotional, social, and physical development to its greatest potential. Our curriculum and methods also prepare students for seamless transitions into each next level of education. Once in Kindergarten, our Extension and Enrichment Program collaborates with Woodland Primary to reinforce and extend your child's learning day, thus maximizing his/her readiness for first grade. And while loving staff and rich curriculum are essential, we also commit to ongoing teacher coaching, extensive evaluations, and continual professional development that result in the highest quality education and care for your child.
business hours:
Before School: 6:45am - school starts
After School: 2:20pm - 6:00pm

name: WAUKEGAN EARLY LEARNING CENTER
detail:
One Hope United Child Development Centers cater to the individual needs of each community, child and family in our care. We nurture children’s growth and partner with parents to help children become independent, self-confident, inquisitive learners.

Our centers use the Creative Curriculum, through which teachers design a classroom environment that includes learning centers such as blocks, dramatic play, art, library, math and science, sand and water, music and movement, cooking, literacy and computers. Through active involvement with this environment, children learn to understand the world around them, make choices and explore through hands-on activities.

Also, our Healthy Lifestyles curriculum brings nature and sustainable living concepts into the classroom by emphasizing exercise, healthy routines, nutritional practices and environmental awareness. Daily indoor or outdoor activities that promote this philosophy are embedded into our school readiness program through experiences such as cooking, maintaining center gardens and creatively using recycled material. Field trips and events encouraging family participation are part of the curriculum at all One Hope United child development centers.

We implement the Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) philosophy in our School Age programs, using hands-on activities and problem-solving to enhance academic performance.

One Hope United’s centers also incorporate group activities to build language and social skills, while time in the gym or at the playground strengthens their bodies. We believe in nurturing each child’s mind, body and soul.

name: My Little School Daycare & Preschool
detail: New Daycare in Belleville, 6wks to school age. Now pre enrolling. Hot meals served,preschool program,bright rooms, large plaground, great staff. All staff are fingerprinted,background checked,CPR certifited and drug tested. Very clean Daycare Center.

name: Tish's Town of Tots Child Care Center
